var book = {
	"name": "Genesis",
	"numChapters": 50,
	"chapters": {
		"1": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">1 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1A\"></sup>In the beginning <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1B\"></sup>God <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1C\"></sup>created the heavens and the earth.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The earth was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2D\"></sup>formless and void, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2E\"></sup>darkness was over the surface of the deep, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2F\"></sup>the Spirit of God <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2G\"></sup>was moving over the surface of the waters.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-3H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-3H\"></sup>God said, “Let there be light”; and there was light.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>God saw that the light was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4I\"></sup>good; and God <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-4J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-4J\"></sup>separated the light from the darkness.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5K\"></sup>God called the light day, and the darkness He called night. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-5L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-5L\"></sup>there was evening and there was morning, one day.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then God said, “Let there be an <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-6M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-6M\"></sup>expanse in the midst of the waters, and let it separate the waters from the waters.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>God made the expanse, and separated <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7N\"></sup>the waters which were below the expanse from the waters <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-7O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-7O\"></sup>which were above the expanse; and it was so.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>God called the expanse heaven. And there was evening and there was morning, a second day.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then God said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9P\"></sup>Let the waters below the heavens be gathered into one place, and let <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-9Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-9Q\"></sup>the dry land appear”; and it was so.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>God called the dry land earth, and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-10R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-10R\"></sup>gathering of the waters He called seas; and God saw that it was good.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then God said, “Let the earth sprout <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-11S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-11S\"></sup>vegetation, plants yielding seed, <i>and</i> fruit trees on the earth bearing fruit after their kind with seed in them”; and it was so.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The earth brought forth vegetation, plants yielding seed after their kind, and trees bearing fruit with seed in them, after their kind; and God saw that it was good.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>There was evening and there was morning, a third day.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then God said, “Let there be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-14T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-14T\"></sup>lights in the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-14U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-14U\"></sup>expanse of the heavens to separate the day from the night, and let them be for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-14V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-14V\"></sup>signs and for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-14W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-14W\"></sup>seasons and for days and years;",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>and let them be for lights in the expanse of the heavens to give light on the earth”; and it was so.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>God made the two great lights, the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-16X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-16X\"></sup>greater light to govern the day, and the lesser light to govern the night; <i>He made</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-16Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-16Y\"></sup>the stars also.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-17Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-17Z\"></sup>God placed them in the expanse of the heavens to give light on the earth,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>and to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-18AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-18AA\"></sup>govern the day and the night, and to separate the light from the darkness; and God saw that it was good.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>There was evening and there was morning, a fourth day.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Then God said, “Let the waters teem with swarms of living creatures, and let birds fly above the earth in the open expanse of the heavens.”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>God created <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21AB\"></sup>the great sea monsters and every living creature that moves, with which the waters swarmed after their kind, and every winged bird after its kind; and God saw that it was good.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>God blessed them, saying, “Be fruitful and multiply, and fill the waters in the seas, and let birds multiply on the earth.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>There was evening and there was morning, a fifth day.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-24AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-24AC\"></sup>Then God said, “Let the earth bring forth living creatures after their kind: cattle and creeping things and beasts of the earth after their kind”; and it was so.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>God made the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-25AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-25AD\"></sup>beasts of the earth after their kind, and the cattle after their kind, and everything that creeps on the ground after its kind; and God saw that it was good.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Then God said, “Let <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-26AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-26AE\"></sup>Us make <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-26AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-26AF\"></sup>man in Our image, according to Our likeness; and let them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-26AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-26AG\"></sup>rule over the fish of the sea and over the birds of the sky and over the cattle and over all the earth, and over every creeping thing that creeps on the earth.”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>God created man <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-27AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-27AH\"></sup>in His own image, in the image of God He created him; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-27AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-27AI\"></sup>male and female He created them.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>God blessed them; and God said to them, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-28AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-28AJ\"></sup>Be fruitful and multiply, and fill the earth, and subdue it; and rule over the fish of the sea and over the birds of the sky and over every living thing that moves on the earth.”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Then God said, “Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-29AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-29AK\"></sup>I have given you every plant yielding seed that is on the surface of all the earth, and every tree which has fruit yielding seed; it shall be food for you;",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-30AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-30AL\"></sup>to every beast of the earth and to every bird of the sky and to every thing that moves on the earth which has life, <i>I have given</i> every green plant for food”; and it was so.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>God saw all that He had made, and behold, it was very <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-31AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-31AM\"></sup>good. And there was evening and there was morning, the sixth day."
		},
		"2": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">2 </span>Thus the heavens and the earth were completed, and all <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-32A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-32A\"></sup>their hosts.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>By <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-33B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-33B\"></sup>the seventh day God completed His work which He had done, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-33C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-33C\"></sup>He rested on the seventh day from all His work which He had done.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then God blessed the seventh day and sanctified it, because in it He rested from all His work which God had created and made.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-35D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-35D\"></sup>This is the account of the heavens and the earth when they were created, in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-35E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-35E\"></sup>the day that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God made earth and heaven.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-36F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-36F\"></sup>Now no shrub of the field was yet in the earth, and no plant of the field had yet sprouted, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-36G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-36G\"></sup>for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God had not sent rain upon the earth, and there was no man to cultivate the ground.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>But a mist used to rise from the earth and water the whole surface of the ground.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God formed man of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-38H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-38H\"></sup>dust from the ground, and breathed into his nostrils the breath of life; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-38I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-38I\"></sup>man became a living being.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God planted a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-39J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-39J\"></sup>garden toward the east, in Eden; and there He placed the man whom He had formed.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Out of the ground the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God caused to grow <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-40K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-40K\"></sup>every tree that is pleasing to the sight and good for food; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-40L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-40L\"></sup>the tree of life also in the midst of the garden, and the tree of the knowledge of good and evil.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Now a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-41M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-41M\"></sup>river flowed out of Eden to water the garden; and from there it divided and became four rivers.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The name of the first is Pishon; it flows around the whole land of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-42N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-42N\"></sup>Havilah, where there is gold.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The gold of that land is good; the bdellium and the onyx stone are there.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The name of the second river is Gihon; it flows around the whole land of Cush.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The name of the third river is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-45O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-45O\"></sup>Tigris; it flows east of Assyria. And the fourth river is the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-45P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-45P\"></sup>Euphrates.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God took the man and put him into the garden of Eden to cultivate it and keep it.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-47Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-47Q\"></sup>commanded the man, saying, “From any tree of the garden you may eat freely;",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>but from the tree of the knowledge of good and evil you shall not eat, for in the day that you eat from it <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-48R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-48R\"></sup>you will surely die.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God said, “It is not good for the man to be alone; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-49S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-49S\"></sup>I will make him a helper suitable for him.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-50T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-50T\"></sup>Out of the ground the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God formed every beast of the field and every bird of the sky, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-50U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-50U\"></sup>brought <i>them</i> to the man to see what he would call them; and whatever the man called a living creature, that was its name.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>The man gave names to all the cattle, and to the birds of the sky, and to every beast of the field, but for Adam there was not found <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-51V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-51V\"></sup>a helper suitable for him.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>So the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God caused a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-52W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-52W\"></sup>deep sleep to fall upon the man, and he slept; then He took one of his ribs and closed up the flesh at that place.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God fashioned into a woman <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-53X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-53X\"></sup>the rib which He had taken from the man, and brought her to the man.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>The man said,“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-54Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-54Y\"></sup>This is now bone of my bones,And flesh of my flesh;She shall be called Woman,Because she was taken out of Man.”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-55Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-55Z\"></sup>For this reason a man shall leave his father and his mother, and be joined to his wife; and they shall become one flesh.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-56AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-56AA\"></sup>And the man and his wife were both naked and were not ashamed."
		},
		"3": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">3 </span>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-57A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-57A\"></sup>the serpent was more crafty than any beast of the field which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God had made. And he said to the woman, “Indeed, has God said, ‘You shall not eat from any tree of the garden’?”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The woman said to the serpent, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-58B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-58B\"></sup>From the fruit of the trees of the garden we may eat;",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>but from the fruit of the tree which is in the middle of the garden, God has said, ‘You shall not eat from it or touch it, or you will die.’”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-60C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-60C\"></sup>The serpent said to the woman, “You surely will not die!",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>For God knows that in the day you eat from it your eyes will be opened, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-61D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-61D\"></sup>you will be like God, knowing good and evil.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-62E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-62E\"></sup>When the woman saw that the tree was good for food, and that it was a delight to the eyes, and that the tree was desirable to make <i>one</i> wise, she took from its fruit and ate; and she gave also to her husband with her, and he ate.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then the eyes of both of them were opened, and they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-63F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-63F\"></sup>knew that they were naked; and they sewed fig leaves together and made themselves loin coverings.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>They heard the sound of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-64G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-64G\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God walking in the garden in the cool of the day, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-64H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-64H\"></sup>and the man and his wife hid themselves from the presence of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God among the trees of the garden.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God called to the man, and said to him, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-65I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-65I\"></sup>Where are you?”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>He said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-66J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-66J\"></sup>I heard the sound of You in the garden, and I was afraid because I was naked; so I hid myself.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And He said, “Who told you that you were naked? Have you eaten from the tree of which I commanded you not to eat?”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-68K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-68K\"></sup>The man said, “The woman whom You gave <i>to be</i> with me, she gave me from the tree, and I ate.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God said to the woman, “What is this you have done?” And the woman said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-69L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-69L\"></sup>The serpent deceived me, and I ate.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God said to the serpent,“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-70M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-70M\"></sup>Because you have done this,Cursed are you more than all cattle,And more than every beast of the field;On your belly you will go,And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-70N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-70N\"></sup>dust you will eatAll the days of your life;",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And I will put <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-71O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-71O\"></sup>enmityBetween you and the woman,And between your seed and her seed;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-71P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-71P\"></sup>He shall bruise you on the head,And you shall bruise him on the heel.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>To the woman He said,“I will greatly multiplyYour pain in childbirth,In pain you will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-72Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-72Q\"></sup>bring forth children;Yet your desire will be for your husband,And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-72R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-72R\"></sup>he will rule over you.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then to Adam He said, “Because you have listened to the voice of your wife, and have eaten from the tree about which I commanded you, saying, ‘You shall not eat from it’;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-73S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-73S\"></sup>Cursed is the ground because of you;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-73T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-73T\"></sup>In toil you will eat of itAll the days of your life.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>“Both thorns and thistles it shall grow for you;And you will eat the plants of the field;",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>By the sweat of your faceYou will eat bread,Till you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-75U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-75U\"></sup>return to the ground,Because <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-75V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-75V\"></sup>from it you were taken;For you are dust,And to dust you shall return.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Now the man called his wife’s name <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-76W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-76W\"></sup>Eve, because she was the mother of all <i>the</i> living.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God made garments of skin for Adam and his wife, and clothed them.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God said, “Behold, the man has become like one of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-78X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-78X\"></sup>Us, knowing good and evil; and now, he might stretch out his hand, and take also from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-78Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-78Y\"></sup>the tree of life, and eat, and live forever”—",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>therefore the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God sent him out from the garden of Eden, to cultivate the ground from which he was taken.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-80Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-80Z\"></sup>He drove the man out; and at the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-80AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-80AA\"></sup>east of the garden of Eden He stationed the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-80AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-80AB\"></sup>cherubim and the flaming sword which turned every direction to guard the way to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-80AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-80AC\"></sup>the tree of life."
		},
		"4": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">4 </span>Now the man had relations with his wife Eve, and she conceived and gave birth to Cain, and she said, “I have gotten a manchild with <i>the help of</i> the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Again, she gave birth to his brother Abel. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-82A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-82A\"></sup>Abel was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-82B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-82B\"></sup>a keeper of flocks, but Cain was a tiller of the ground.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>So it came about in the course of time that Cain brought an offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> of the fruit of the ground.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-84C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-84C\"></sup>Abel, on his part also brought of the firstlings of his flock and of their fat portions. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-84D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-84D\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had regard for Abel and for his offering;",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-85E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-85E\"></sup>for Cain and for his offering He had no regard. So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-85F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-85F\"></sup>Cain became very angry and his countenance fell.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Cain, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-86G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-86G\"></sup>Why are you angry? And why has your countenance fallen?",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-87H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-87H\"></sup>If you do well, will not <i>your countenance</i> be lifted up? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-87I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-87I\"></sup>And if you do not do well, sin is crouching at the door; and its desire is for you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-87J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-87J\"></sup>but you must master it.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Cain told Abel his brother. And it came about when they were in the field, that Cain rose up against Abel his brother and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-88K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-88K\"></sup>killed him.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Cain, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-89L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-89L\"></sup>Where is Abel your brother?” And he said, “I do not know. Am I my brother’s keeper?”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>He said, “What have you done? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-90M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-90M\"></sup>The voice of your brother’s blood is crying to Me from the ground.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-91N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-91N\"></sup>you are cursed from the ground, which has opened its mouth to receive your brother’s blood from your hand.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-92O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-92O\"></sup>When you cultivate the ground, it will no longer yield its strength to you; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-92P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-92P\"></sup>you will be a vagrant and a wanderer on the earth.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Cain said to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, “My punishment is too great to bear!",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Behold, You have <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-94Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-94Q\"></sup>driven me this day from the face of the ground; and from Your face I will be hidden, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-94R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-94R\"></sup>I will be a vagrant and a wanderer on the earth, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-94S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-94S\"></sup>whoever finds me will kill me.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>So the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to him, “Therefore whoever kills Cain, vengeance will be taken on him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-95T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-95T\"></sup>sevenfold.” And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-95U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-95U\"></sup>appointed a sign for Cain, so that no one finding him would slay him.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then Cain went out from the presence <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-96V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-96V\"></sup>of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and settled in the land of Nod, east of Eden.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Cain had relations with his wife and she conceived, and gave birth to Enoch; and he built a city, and called the name of the city Enoch, after the name of his son.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Now to Enoch was born Irad, and Irad became the father of Mehujael, and Mehujael became the father of Methushael, and Methushael became the father of Lamech.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Lamech took to himself <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-99W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-99W\"></sup>two wives: the name of the one was Adah, and the name of the other, Zillah.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Adah gave birth to Jabal; he was the father of those who dwell in tents and <i>have</i> livestock.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>His brother’s name was Jubal; he was the father of all those who play the lyre and pipe.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>As for Zillah, she also gave birth to Tubal-cain, the forger of all implements of bronze and iron; and the sister of Tubal-cain was Naamah.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Lamech said to his wives,“Adah and Zillah,Listen to my voice,You wives of Lamech,Give heed to my speech,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-103X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-103X\"></sup>For I have killed a man for wounding me;And a boy for striking me;",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>If Cain is avenged <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-104Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-104Y\"></sup>sevenfold,Then Lamech seventy-sevenfold.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-105Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-105Z\"></sup>Adam had relations with his wife again; and she gave birth to a son, and named him Seth, for, <i>she said</i>, “God has appointed me another offspring in place of Abel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-105AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-105AA\"></sup>for Cain killed him.”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>To Seth, to him also <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-106AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-106AB\"></sup>a son was born; and he called his name Enosh. Then <i>men</i> began <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-106AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-106AC\"></sup>to call upon the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>."
		},
		"5": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">5 </span>This is the book of the generations of Adam. In the day when God created man, He made him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-107A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-107A\"></sup>in the likeness of God.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He created them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-108B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-108B\"></sup>male and female, and He <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-108C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-108C\"></sup>blessed them and named them Man in the day when they were created.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>When Adam had lived one hundred and thirty years, he became the father of <i>a son</i> in his own likeness, according to his image, and named him Seth.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then the days of Adam after he became the father of Seth were eight hundred years, and he had <i>other</i> sons and daughters.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>So all the days that Adam lived were nine hundred and thirty years, and he died.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Seth lived one hundred and five years, and became the father of Enosh.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then Seth lived eight hundred and seven years after he became the father of Enosh, and he had <i>other</i> sons and daughters.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>So all the days of Seth were nine hundred and twelve years, and he died.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Enosh lived ninety years, and became the father of Kenan.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then Enosh lived eight hundred and fifteen years after he became the father of Kenan, and he had <i>other</i> sons and daughters.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>So all the days of Enosh were nine hundred and five years, and he died.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Kenan lived seventy years, and became the father of Mahalalel.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then Kenan lived eight hundred and forty years after he became the father of Mahalalel, and he had <i>other</i> sons and daughters.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>So all the days of Kenan were nine hundred and ten years, and he died.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Mahalalel lived sixty-five years, and became the father of Jared.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then Mahalalel lived eight hundred and thirty years after he became the father of Jared, and he had <i>other</i> sons and daughters.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>So all the days of Mahalalel were eight hundred and ninety-five years, and he died.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Jared lived one hundred and sixty-two years, and became the father of Enoch.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Then Jared lived eight hundred years after he became the father of Enoch, and he had <i>other</i> sons and daughters.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>So all the days of Jared were nine hundred and sixty-two years, and he died.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Enoch lived sixty-five years, and became the father of Methuselah.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then Enoch <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-128D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-128D\"></sup>walked with God three hundred years after he became the father of Methuselah, and he had <i>other</i> sons and daughters.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>So all the days of Enoch were three hundred and sixty-five years.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-130E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-130E\"></sup>Enoch walked with God; and he was not, for God <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-130F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-130F\"></sup>took him.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Methuselah lived one hundred and eighty-seven years, and became the father of Lamech.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Then Methuselah lived seven hundred and eighty-two years after he became the father of Lamech, and he had <i>other</i> sons and daughters.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>So all the days of Methuselah were nine hundred and sixty-nine years, and he died.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Lamech lived one hundred and eighty-two years, and became the father of a son.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Now he called his name Noah, saying, “This one will give us rest from our work and from the toil of our hands <i>arising</i> from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-135G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-135G\"></sup>the ground which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has cursed.”",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Then Lamech lived five hundred and ninety-five years after he became the father of Noah, and he had <i>other</i> sons and daughters.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>So all the days of Lamech were seven hundred and seventy-seven years, and he died.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Noah was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-138H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-138H\"></sup>five hundred years old, and Noah became the father of Shem, Ham, and Japheth."
		},
		"6": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">6 </span>Now it came about, when men began to multiply on the face of the land, and daughters were born to them,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>that the sons of God saw that the daughters of men were beautiful; and they took wives for themselves, whomever they chose.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-141A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-141A\"></sup>My Spirit shall not strive with man forever, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-141B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-141B\"></sup>because he also is flesh; nevertheless his days shall be one hundred and twenty years.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-142C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-142C\"></sup>Nephilim were on the earth in those days, and also afterward, when the sons of God came in to the daughters of men, and they bore <i>children</i> to them. Those were the mighty men who <i>were</i> of old, men of renown.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> saw that the wickedness of man was great on the earth, and that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-143D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-143D\"></sup>every intent of the thoughts of his heart was only evil continually.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-144E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-144E\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was sorry that He had made man on the earth, and He was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-144F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-144F\"></sup>grieved in His heart.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-145G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-145G\"></sup>I will blot out man whom I have created from the face of the land, from man to animals to creeping things and to birds of the sky; for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-145H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-145H\"></sup>I am sorry that I have made them.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-146I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-146I\"></sup>Noah <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-146J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-146J\"></sup>found favor in the eyes of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>These are <i>the records of</i> the generations of Noah. Noah was a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-147K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-147K\"></sup>righteous man, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-147L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-147L\"></sup>blameless in his time; Noah <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-147M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-147M\"></sup>walked with God.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Noah became the father of three sons: Shem, Ham, and Japheth.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Now the earth was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-149N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-149N\"></sup>corrupt in the sight of God, and the earth was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-149O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-149O\"></sup>filled with violence.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>God looked on the earth, and behold, it was corrupt; for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-150P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-150P\"></sup>all flesh had corrupted their way upon the earth.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then God said to Noah, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-151Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-151Q\"></sup>The end of all flesh has come before Me; for the earth is filled with violence because of them; and behold, I am about to destroy them with the earth.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Make for yourself an ark of gopher wood; you shall make the ark with rooms, and shall cover it inside and out with pitch.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>This is how you shall make it: the length of the ark three hundred cubits, its breadth fifty cubits, and its height thirty cubits.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>You shall make a window for the ark, and finish it to a cubit from the top; and set the door of the ark in the side of it; you shall make it with lower, second, and third decks.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-155R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-155R\"></sup>I, even I am bringing the flood of water upon the earth, to destroy all flesh in which is the breath of life, from under heaven; everything that is on the earth shall perish.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>But I will establish <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-156S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-156S\"></sup>My covenant with you; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-156T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-156T\"></sup>you shall enter the ark—you and your sons and your wife, and your sons’ wives with you.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-157U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-157U\"></sup>And of every living thing of all flesh, you shall bring two of every <i>kind</i> into the ark, to keep <i>them</i> alive with you; they shall be male and female.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-158V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-158V\"></sup>Of the birds after their kind, and of the animals after their kind, of every creeping thing of the ground after its kind, two of every <i>kind</i> will come to you to keep <i>them</i> alive.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>As for you, take for yourself some of all <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-159W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-159W\"></sup>food which is edible, and gather <i>it</i> to yourself; and it shall be for food for you and for them.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-160X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-160X\"></sup>Thus Noah did; according to all that God had commanded him, so he did."
		},
		"7": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">7 </span>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Noah, “Enter the ark, you and all your household, for you <i>alone</i> I have seen <i>to be</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-161A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-161A\"></sup>righteous before Me in this time.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>You shall take with you of every <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-162B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-162B\"></sup>clean animal by sevens, a male and his female; and of the animals that are not clean two, a male and his female;",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>also of the birds of the sky, by sevens, male and female, to keep offspring alive on the face of all the earth.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>For after <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-164C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-164C\"></sup>seven more days, I will send rain on the earth <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-164D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-164D\"></sup>forty days and forty nights; and I will blot out from the face of the land <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-164E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-164E\"></sup>every living thing that I have made.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-165F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-165F\"></sup>Noah did according to all that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded him.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Now Noah was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-166G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-166G\"></sup>six hundred years old when the flood of water came upon the earth.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-167H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-167H\"></sup>Noah and his sons and his wife and his sons’ wives with him entered the ark because of the water of the flood.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-168I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-168I\"></sup>Of clean animals and animals that are not clean and birds and everything that creeps on the ground,",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>there went into the ark to Noah by twos, male and female, as God had commanded Noah.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>It came about after <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-170J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-170J\"></sup>the seven days, that the water of the flood came upon the earth.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>In the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-171K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-171K\"></sup>six hundredth year of Noah’s life, in the second month, on the seventeenth day of the month, on the same day all <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-171L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-171L\"></sup>the fountains of the great deep burst open, and the floodgates of the sky were opened.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-172M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-172M\"></sup>The rain fell upon the earth for forty days and forty nights.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>On the very same day <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-173N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-173N\"></sup>Noah and Shem and Ham and Japheth, the sons of Noah, and Noah’s wife and the three wives of his sons with them, entered the ark,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>they and every beast after its kind, and all the cattle after their kind, and every creeping thing that creeps on the earth after its kind, and every bird after its kind, all sorts of birds.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>So they went into the ark to Noah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-175O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-175O\"></sup>by twos of all flesh in which was the breath of life.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Those that entered, male and female of all flesh, entered as God had commanded him; and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> closed <i>it</i> behind him.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then the flood came upon the earth for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-177P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-177P\"></sup>forty days, and the water increased and lifted up the ark, so that it rose above the earth.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>The water prevailed and increased greatly upon the earth, and the ark floated on the surface of the water.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>The water prevailed more and more upon the earth, so that all the high mountains everywhere under the heavens were covered.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>The water prevailed fifteen cubits higher, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-180Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-180Q\"></sup>and the mountains were covered.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-181R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-181R\"></sup>All flesh that moved on the earth perished, birds and cattle and beasts and every swarming thing that swarms upon the earth, and all mankind;",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>of all that was on the dry land, all <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-182S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-182S\"></sup>in whose nostrils was the breath of the spirit of life, died.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Thus He blotted out every living thing that was upon the face of the land, from man to animals to creeping things and to birds of the sky, and they were blotted out from the earth; and only <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-183T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-183T\"></sup>Noah was left, together with those that were with him in the ark.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-184U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-184U\"></sup>The water prevailed upon the earth one hundred and fifty days."
		},
		"8": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">8 </span>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-185A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-185A\"></sup>God remembered Noah and all the beasts and all the cattle that were with him in the ark; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-185B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-185B\"></sup>God caused a wind to pass over the earth, and the water subsided.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Also <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-186C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-186C\"></sup>the fountains of the deep and the floodgates of the sky were closed, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-186D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-186D\"></sup>the rain from the sky was restrained;",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>and the water receded steadily from the earth, and at the end <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-187E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-187E\"></sup>of one hundred and fifty days the water decreased.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>In the seventh month, on the seventeenth day of the month, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-188F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-188F\"></sup>the ark rested upon the mountains of Ararat.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The water decreased steadily until the tenth month; in the tenth month, on the first day of the month, the tops of the mountains became visible.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then it came about at the end of forty days, that Noah opened the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-190G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-190G\"></sup>window of the ark which he had made;",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>and he sent out a raven, and it flew here and there until the water was dried up from the earth.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then he sent out a dove from him, to see if the water was abated from the face of the land;",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>but the dove found no resting place for the sole of her foot, so she returned to him into the ark, for the water was on the surface of all the earth. Then he put out his hand and took her, and brought her into the ark to himself.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>So he waited yet another seven days; and again he sent out the dove from the ark.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The dove came to him toward evening, and behold, in her beak was a freshly picked olive leaf. So Noah knew that the water was abated from the earth.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then he waited yet another seven days, and sent out <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-196H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-196H\"></sup>the dove; but she did not return to him again.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Now it came about in the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-197I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-197I\"></sup>six hundred and first year, in the first <i>month</i>, on the first of the month, the water was dried up from the earth. Then Noah removed the covering of the ark, and looked, and behold, the surface of the ground was dried up.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>In the second month, on the twenty-seventh day of the month, the earth was dry.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then God spoke to Noah, saying,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>“Go out of the ark, you and your wife and your sons and your sons’ wives with you.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Bring out with you every living thing of all flesh that is with you, birds and animals and every creeping thing that creeps on the earth, that they may <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-201J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-201J\"></sup>breed abundantly on the earth, and be fruitful and multiply on the earth.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>So Noah went out, and his sons and his wife and his sons’ wives with him.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Every beast, every creeping thing, and every bird, everything that moves on the earth, went out by their families from the ark.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Then Noah built <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-204K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-204K\"></sup>an altar to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and took of every <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-204L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-204L\"></sup>clean animal and of every clean bird and offered <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-204M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-204M\"></sup>burnt offerings on the altar.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-205N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-205N\"></sup>smelled the soothing aroma; and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Himself, “I will never again <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-205O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-205O\"></sup>curse the ground on account of man, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-205P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-205P\"></sup>the intent of man’s heart is evil from his youth; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-205Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-205Q\"></sup>and I will never again destroy every living thing, as I have done.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>“While the earth remains,Seedtime and harvest,And cold and heat,And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-206R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-206R\"></sup>summer and winter,And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-206S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-206S\"></sup>day and nightShall not cease.”"
		},
		"9": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">9 </span>And God blessed Noah and his sons and said to them, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-207A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-207A\"></sup>Be fruitful and multiply, and fill the earth.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The fear of you and the terror of you will be on every beast of the earth and on every bird of the sky; with everything that creeps on the ground, and all the fish of the sea, into your hand they are given.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Every moving thing that is alive shall be food for you; I give all to you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-209B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-209B\"></sup>as <i>I gave</i> the green plant.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Only you shall not eat flesh with its life, <i>that is</i>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-210C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-210C\"></sup>its blood.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Surely I will require <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-211D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-211D\"></sup>your lifeblood; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-211E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-211E\"></sup>from every beast I will require it. And from <i>every</i> man, from every man’s brother I will require the life of man.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-212F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-212F\"></sup>Whoever sheds man’s blood,By man his blood shall be shed,For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-212G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-212G\"></sup>in the image of GodHe made man.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>“As for you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-213H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-213H\"></sup>be fruitful and multiply;Populate the earth abundantly and multiply in it.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then God spoke to Noah and to his sons with him, saying,",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“Now behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-215I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-215I\"></sup>I Myself do establish My covenant with you, and with your descendants after you;",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>and with every living creature that is with you, the birds, the cattle, and every beast of the earth with you; of all that comes out of the ark, even every beast of the earth.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>I establish My covenant with you; and all flesh shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-217J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-217J\"></sup>never again be cut off by the water of the flood, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-217K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-217K\"></sup>neither shall there again be a flood to destroy the earth.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>God said, “This is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-218L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-218L\"></sup>the sign of the covenant which I am making between Me and you and every living creature that is with you, for all successive generations;",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>I set My <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-219M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-219M\"></sup>bow in the cloud, and it shall be for a sign of a covenant between Me and the earth.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>It shall come about, when I bring a cloud over the earth, that the bow will be seen in the cloud,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-221N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-221N\"></sup>I will remember My covenant, which is between Me and you and every living creature of all flesh; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-221O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-221O\"></sup>never again shall the water become a flood to destroy all flesh.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>When the bow is in the cloud, then I will look upon it, to remember the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-222P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-222P\"></sup>everlasting covenant between God and every living creature of all flesh that is on the earth.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And God said to Noah, “This is the sign of the covenant which I have established between Me and all flesh that is on the earth.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Now the sons of Noah who came out of the ark were Shem and Ham and Japheth; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-224Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-224Q\"></sup>Ham was the father of Canaan.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>These three <i>were</i> the sons of Noah, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-225R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-225R\"></sup>from these the whole earth was populated.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Then Noah began farming and planted a vineyard.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>He drank of the wine and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-227S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-227S\"></sup>became drunk, and uncovered himself inside his tent.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Ham, the father of Canaan, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-228T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-228T\"></sup>saw the nakedness of his father, and told his two brothers outside.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>But Shem and Japheth took a garment and laid it upon both their shoulders and walked backward and covered the nakedness of their father; and their faces were turned away, so that they did not see their father’s nakedness.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>When Noah awoke from his wine, he knew what his youngest son had done to him.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>So he said,“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-231U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-231U\"></sup>Cursed be Canaan;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-231V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-231V\"></sup>A servant of servantsHe shall be to his brothers.”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>He also said,“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-232W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-232W\"></sup>Blessed be the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,The God of Shem;And let Canaan be his servant.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-233X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-233X\"></sup>May God enlarge Japheth,And let him dwell in the tents of Shem;And let Canaan be his servant.”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Noah lived three hundred and fifty years after the flood.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>So all the days of Noah were nine hundred and fifty years, and he died."
		},
		"10": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">10 </span>Now these are <i>the records of</i> the generations of Shem, Ham, and Japheth, the sons of Noah; and sons were born to them after the flood.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-237A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-237A\"></sup>The sons of Japheth <i>were</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-237B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-237B\"></sup>Gomer and Magog and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-237C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-237C\"></sup>Madai and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-237D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-237D\"></sup>Javan and Tubal and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-237E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-237E\"></sup>Meshech and Tiras.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The sons of Gomer <i>were</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-238F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-238F\"></sup>Ashkenaz and Riphath and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-238G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-238G\"></sup>Togarmah.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The sons of Javan <i>were</i> Elishah and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-239H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-239H\"></sup>Tarshish, Kittim and Dodanim.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>From these the coastlands of the nations were separated into their lands, every one according to his language, according to their families, into their nations.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-241I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-241I\"></sup>The sons of Ham <i>were</i> Cush and Mizraim and Put and Canaan.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The sons of Cush <i>were</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-242J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-242J\"></sup>Seba and Havilah and Sabtah and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-242K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-242K\"></sup>Raamah and Sabteca; and the sons of Raamah <i>were</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-242L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-242L\"></sup>Sheba and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-242M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-242M\"></sup>Dedan.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Now Cush became the father of Nimrod; he became a mighty one on the earth.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>He was a mighty hunter before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; therefore it is said, “Like Nimrod a mighty hunter before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The beginning of his kingdom was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-245N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-245N\"></sup>Babel and Erech and Accad and Calneh, in the land of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-245O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-245O\"></sup>Shinar.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>From that land he went forth <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-246P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-246P\"></sup>into Assyria, and built Nineveh and Rehoboth-Ir and Calah,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>and Resen between Nineveh and Calah; that is the great city.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Mizraim became the father of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-248Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-248Q\"></sup>Ludim and Anamim and Lehabim and Naphtuhim",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-249R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-249R\"></sup>Pathrusim and Casluhim (from which came the Philistines) and Caphtorim.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Canaan became the father of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-250S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-250S\"></sup>Sidon, his firstborn, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-250T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-250T\"></sup>Heth",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-251U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-251U\"></sup>the Jebusite and the Amorite and the Girgashite",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>and the Hivite and the Arkite and the Sinite",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>and the Arvadite and the Zemarite and the Hamathite; and afterward the families of the Canaanite were spread abroad.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-254V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-254V\"></sup>The territory of the Canaanite extended from Sidon as you go toward Gerar, as far as Gaza; as you go toward <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-254W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-254W\"></sup>Sodom and Gomorrah and Admah and Zeboiim, as far as Lasha.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>These are the sons of Ham, according to their families, according to their languages, by their lands, by their nations.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Also to Shem, the father of all the children of Eber, <i>and</i> the older brother of Japheth, children were born.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-257X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-257X\"></sup>The sons of Shem <i>were</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-257Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-257Y\"></sup>Elam and Asshur and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-257Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-257Z\"></sup>Arpachshad and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-257AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-257AA\"></sup>Lud and Aram.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>The sons of Aram <i>were</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-258AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-258AB\"></sup>Uz and Hul and Gether and Mash.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Arpachshad became the father of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-259AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-259AC\"></sup>Shelah; and Shelah became the father of Eber.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-260AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-260AD\"></sup>Two sons were born to Eber; the name of the one <i>was</i> Peleg, for in his days the earth was divided; and his brother’s name <i>was</i> Joktan.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Joktan became the father of Almodad and Sheleph and Hazarmaveth and Jerah",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>and Hadoram and Uzal and Diklah",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>and Obal and Abimael and Sheba",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>and Ophir and Havilah and Jobab; all these were the sons of Joktan.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Now their settlement extended from Mesha as you go toward Sephar, the hill country of the east.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>These are the sons of Shem, according to their families, according to their languages, by their lands, according to their nations.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>These are the families of the sons of Noah, according to their genealogies, by their nations; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-267AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-267AE\"></sup>out of these the nations were separated on the earth after the flood."
		},
		"11": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">11 </span>Now the whole earth used the same language and the same words.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>It came about as they journeyed east, that they found a plain in the land <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-269A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-269A\"></sup>of Shinar and settled there.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>They said to one another, “Come, let us make bricks and burn <i>them</i> thoroughly.” And they used brick for stone, and they used <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-270B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-270B\"></sup>tar for mortar.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>They said, “Come, let us build for ourselves a city, and a tower whose top <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-271C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-271C\"></sup><i>will reach</i> into heaven, and let us make for ourselves <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-271D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-271D\"></sup>a name, otherwise we <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-271E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-271E\"></sup>will be scattered abroad over the face of the whole earth.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-272F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-272F\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came down to see the city and the tower which the sons of men had built.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said, “Behold, they are one people, and they all have <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-273G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-273G\"></sup>the same language. And this is what they began to do, and now nothing which they purpose to do will be impossible for them.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Come, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-274H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-274H\"></sup>let Us go down and there <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-274I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-274I\"></sup>confuse their language, so that they will not understand one another’s speech.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>So the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-275J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-275J\"></sup>scattered them abroad from there over the face of the whole earth; and they stopped building the city.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Therefore its name was called <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-276K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-276K\"></sup>Babel, because there the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> confused the language of the whole earth; and from there the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> scattered them abroad over the face of the whole earth.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-277L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-277L\"></sup>These are <i>the records of</i> the generations of Shem. Shem was one hundred years old, and became the father of Arpachshad two years after the flood;",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>and Shem lived five hundred years after he became the father of Arpachshad, and he had <i>other</i> sons and daughters.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Arpachshad lived thirty-five years, and became the father of Shelah;",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>and Arpachshad lived four hundred and three years after he became the father of Shelah, and he had <i>other</i> sons and daughters.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Shelah lived thirty years, and became the father of Eber;",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>and Shelah lived four hundred and three years after he became the father of Eber, and he had <i>other</i> sons and daughters.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Eber lived thirty-four years, and became the father of Peleg;",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>and Eber lived four hundred and thirty years after he became the father of Peleg, and he had <i>other</i> sons and daughters.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Peleg lived thirty years, and became the father of Reu;",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>and Peleg lived two hundred and nine years after he became the father of Reu, and he had <i>other</i> sons and daughters.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Reu lived thirty-two years, and became the father of Serug;",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>and Reu lived two hundred and seven years after he became the father of Serug, and he had <i>other</i> sons and daughters.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Serug lived thirty years, and became the father of Nahor;",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>and Serug lived two hundred years after he became the father of Nahor, and he had <i>other</i> sons and daughters.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Nahor lived twenty-nine years, and became the father of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-291M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-291M\"></sup>Terah;",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>and Nahor lived one hundred and nineteen years after he became the father of Terah, and he had <i>other</i> sons and daughters.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Terah lived seventy years, and became <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-293N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-293N\"></sup>the father of Abram, Nahor and Haran.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Now these are <i>the records of</i> the generations of Terah. Terah became the father of Abram, Nahor and Haran; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-294O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-294O\"></sup>Haran became the father of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-294P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-294P\"></sup>Lot.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Haran died in the presence of his father Terah in the land of his birth, in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-295Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-295Q\"></sup>Ur of the Chaldeans.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Abram and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-296R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-296R\"></sup>Nahor took wives for themselves. The name of Abram’s wife was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-296S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-296S\"></sup>Sarai; and the name of Nahor’s wife was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-296T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-296T\"></sup>Milcah, the daughter of Haran, the father of Milcah and Iscah.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-297U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-297U\"></sup>Sarai was barren; she had no child.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Terah took Abram his son, and Lot the son of Haran, his grandson, and Sarai his daughter-in-law, his son Abram’s wife; and they went out together from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-298V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-298V\"></sup>Ur of the Chaldeans in order to enter the land of Canaan; and they went as far as Haran, and settled there.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>The days of Terah were two hundred and five years; and Terah died in Haran."
		},
		"12": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">12 </span>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-300A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-300A\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Abram,“Go forth from your country,And from your relativesAnd from your father’s house,To the land which I will show you;",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-301B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-301B\"></sup>I will make you a great nation,And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-301C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-301C\"></sup>I will bless you,And make your name great;And so <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-301D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-301D\"></sup>you shall be a blessing;",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-302E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-302E\"></sup>I will bless those who bless you,And the one who curses you I will curse.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-302F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-302F\"></sup>And in you all the families of the earth will be blessed.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>So Abram went forth as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had spoken to him; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-303G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-303G\"></sup>Lot went with him. Now Abram was seventy-five years old when he departed from Haran.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Abram took Sarai his wife and Lot his nephew, and all their <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-304H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-304H\"></sup>possessions which they had accumulated, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-304I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-304I\"></sup>the persons which they had acquired in Haran, and they set out for the land of Canaan; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-304J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-304J\"></sup>thus they came to the land of Canaan.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Abram passed through the land as far as the site of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-305K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-305K\"></sup>Shechem, to the oak of Moreh. Now the Canaanite <i>was</i> then in the land.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-306L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-306L\"></sup>appeared to Abram and said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-306M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-306M\"></sup>To your descendants I will give this land.” So he built <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-306N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-306N\"></sup>an altar there to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> who had appeared to him.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then he proceeded from there to the mountain on the east of Bethel, and pitched his tent, with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-307O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-307O\"></sup>Bethel on the west and Ai on the east; and there he built an altar to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-307P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-307P\"></sup>called upon the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Abram journeyed on, continuing toward <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-308Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-308Q\"></sup>the Negev.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Now there was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-309R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-309R\"></sup>a famine in the land; so Abram went down to Egypt to sojourn there, for the famine was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-309S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-309S\"></sup>severe in the land.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>It came about when he came near to Egypt, that he said to Sarai his wife, “See now, I know that you are a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-310T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-310T\"></sup>beautiful woman;",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-311U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-311U\"></sup>and when the Egyptians see you, they will say, ‘This is his wife’; and they will kill me, but they will let you live.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Please say that you are <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-312V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-312V\"></sup>my sister so that it may go well with me because of you, and that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-312W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-312W\"></sup>I may live on account of you.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>It came about when Abram came into Egypt, the Egyptians saw that the woman was very beautiful.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Pharaoh’s officials saw her and praised her to Pharaoh; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-314X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-314X\"></sup>the woman was taken into Pharaoh’s house.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Therefore <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-315Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-315Y\"></sup>he treated Abram well for her sake; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-315Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-315Z\"></sup>gave him sheep and oxen and donkeys and male and female servants and female donkeys and camels.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>But the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-316AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-316AA\"></sup>struck Pharaoh and his house with great plagues because of Sarai, Abram’s wife.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then Pharaoh called Abram and said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-317AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-317AB\"></sup>What is this you have done to me? Why did you not tell me that she was your wife?",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Why did you say, ‘She is my sister,’ so that I took her for my wife? Now then, here is your wife, take her and go.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Pharaoh commanded <i>his</i> men concerning him; and they escorted him away, with his wife and all that belonged to him."
		},
		"13": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">13 </span>So Abram went up from Egypt to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-320A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-320A\"></sup>the Negev, he and his wife and all that belonged to him, and Lot with him.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Now Abram was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-321B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-321B\"></sup>very rich in livestock, in silver and in gold.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>He went on his journeys from the Negev as far as Bethel, to the place where his tent had been at the beginning, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-322C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-322C\"></sup>between Bethel and Ai,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>to the place of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-323D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-323D\"></sup>altar which he had made there formerly; and there Abram called on the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-324E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-324E\"></sup>Lot, who went with Abram, also had flocks and herds and tents.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-325F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-325F\"></sup>the land could not sustain them while dwelling together, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-325G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-325G\"></sup>for their possessions were so great that they were not able to remain together.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-326H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-326H\"></sup>And there was strife between the herdsmen of Abram’s livestock and the herdsmen of Lot’s livestock. Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-326I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-326I\"></sup>the Canaanite and the Perizzite were dwelling then in the land.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-327J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-327J\"></sup>So Abram said to Lot, “Please let there be no strife between you and me, nor between my herdsmen and your herdsmen, for we are brothers.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Is not the whole land before you? Please separate from me; if <i>to</i> the left, then I will go to the right; or if <i>to</i> the right, then I will go to the left.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Lot lifted up his eyes and saw all the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-329K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-329K\"></sup>valley of the Jordan, that it was well watered everywhere—<i>this was</i> before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-329L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-329L\"></sup>destroyed Sodom and Gomorrah—like <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-329M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-329M\"></sup>the garden of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-329N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-329N\"></sup>like the land of Egypt as you go to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-329O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-329O\"></sup>Zoar.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>So Lot chose for himself all the valley of the Jordan, and Lot journeyed eastward. Thus they separated from each other.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Abram settled in the land of Canaan, while Lot settled in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-331P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-331P\"></sup>the cities of the valley, and moved his tents as far as Sodom.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-332Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-332Q\"></sup>the men of Sodom were wicked exceedingly and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-332R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-332R\"></sup>sinners against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Abram, after Lot had separated from him, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-333S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-333S\"></sup>Now lift up your eyes and look from the place where you are, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-333T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-333T\"></sup>northward and southward and eastward and westward;",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-334U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-334U\"></sup>for all the land which you see, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-334V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-334V\"></sup>I will give it to you and to your descendants forever.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>I will make your descendants <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-335W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-335W\"></sup>as the dust of the earth, so that if anyone can number the dust of the earth, then your descendants can also be numbered.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Arise, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-336X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-336X\"></sup>walk about the land through its length and breadth; for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-336Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-336Y\"></sup>I will give it to you.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then Abram moved his tent and came and dwelt by the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-337Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-337Z\"></sup>oaks of Mamre, which are in Hebron, and there he built <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-337AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-337AA\"></sup>an altar to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>."
		},
		"14": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">14 </span>And it came about in the days of Amraphel king of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-338A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-338A\"></sup>Shinar, Arioch king of Ellasar, Chedorlaomer king of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-338B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-338B\"></sup>Elam, and Tidal king of Goiim,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><i>that</i> they made war with Bera king of Sodom, and with Birsha king of Gomorrah, Shinab king of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-339C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-339C\"></sup>Admah, and Shemeber king of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-339D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-339D\"></sup>Zeboiim, and the king of Bela (that is, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-339E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-339E\"></sup>Zoar).",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>All these came as allies to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-340F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-340F\"></sup>the valley of Siddim (that is, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-340G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-340G\"></sup>the Salt Sea).",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Twelve years they had served Chedorlaomer, but the thirteenth year they rebelled.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>In the fourteenth year Chedorlaomer and the kings that were with him, came and defeated the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-342H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-342H\"></sup>Rephaim in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-342I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-342I\"></sup>Ashteroth-karnaim and the Zuzim in Ham and the Emim in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-342J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-342J\"></sup>Shaveh-kiriathaim,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-343K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-343K\"></sup>Horites in their Mount Seir, as far as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-343L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-343L\"></sup>El-paran, which is by the wilderness.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then they turned back and came to En-mishpat (that is, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-344M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-344M\"></sup>Kadesh), and conquered all the country of the Amalekites, and also the Amorites, who lived in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-344N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-344N\"></sup>Hazazon-tamar.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And the king of Sodom and the king of Gomorrah and the king of Admah and the king of Zeboiim and the king of Bela (that is, Zoar) came out; and they arrayed for battle against them in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-345O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-345O\"></sup>the valley of Siddim,",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>against Chedorlaomer king of Elam and Tidal king of Goiim and Amraphel king of Shinar and Arioch king of Ellasar—four kings against five.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Now the valley of Siddim was full of tar pits; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-347P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-347P\"></sup>the kings of Sodom and Gomorrah fled, and they fell into them. But those who survived fled to the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-347Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-347Q\"></sup>hill country.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then they took all the goods of Sodom and Gomorrah and all their food supply, and departed.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>They also took Lot, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-349R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-349R\"></sup>Abram’s nephew, and his possessions and departed, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-349S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-349S\"></sup>for he was living in Sodom.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then a fugitive came and told Abram the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-350T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-350T\"></sup>Hebrew. Now he was living by the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-350U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-350U\"></sup>oaks of Mamre the Amorite, brother of Eshcol and brother of Aner, and these were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-350V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-350V\"></sup>allies with Abram.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>When Abram heard that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-351W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-351W\"></sup>his relative had been taken captive, he led out his trained men, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-351X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-351X\"></sup>born in his house, three hundred and eighteen, and went in pursuit as far as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-351Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-351Y\"></sup>Dan.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-352Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-352Z\"></sup>He divided his forces against them by night, he and his servants, and defeated them, and pursued them as far as Hobah, which is north of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-352AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-352AA\"></sup>Damascus.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>He <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-353AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-353AB\"></sup>brought back all the goods, and also brought back <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-353AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-353AC\"></sup>his relative Lot with his possessions, and also the women, and the people.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then after his return from the defeat of Chedorlaomer and the kings who were with him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-354AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-354AD\"></sup>the king of Sodom went out to meet him at the valley of Shaveh (that is, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-354AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-354AE\"></sup>the King’s Valley).",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-355AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-355AF\"></sup>Melchizedek king of Salem brought out <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-355AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-355AG\"></sup>bread and wine; now he was a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-355AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-355AH\"></sup>priest of God Most High.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>He blessed him and said,“Blessed be Abram of God Most High,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-356AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-356AI\"></sup>Possessor of heaven and earth;",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And blessed be God Most High,Who has delivered your enemies into your hand.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-357AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-357AJ\"></sup>He gave him a tenth of all.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>The king of Sodom said to Abram, “Give the people to me and take the goods for yourself.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Abram said to the king of Sodom, “I have sworn to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-359AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-359AK\"></sup>God Most High, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-359AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-359AL\"></sup>possessor of heaven and earth,",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-360AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-360AM\"></sup>I will not take a thread or a sandal thong or anything that is yours, for fear you would say, ‘I have made Abram rich.’",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>I will take nothing except what the young men have eaten, and the share of the men who went with me, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-361AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-361AN\"></sup>Aner, Eshcol, and Mamre; let them take their share.”"
		},
		"15": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">15 </span>After these things <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-362A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-362A\"></sup>the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came to Abram in a vision, saying,“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-362B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-362B\"></sup>Do not fear, Abram,I am <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-362C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-362C\"></sup>a shield to you;Your <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-362D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-362D\"></sup>reward shall be very great.”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Abram said, “O Lord <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">God</span>, what will You give me, since I am childless, and the heir of my house is Eliezer of Damascus?”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And Abram said, “Since You have given no offspring to me, one <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-364E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-364E\"></sup>born in my house is my heir.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then behold, the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came to him, saying, “This man will not be your heir; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-365F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-365F\"></sup>but one who will come forth from your own body, he shall be your heir.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And He took him outside and said, “Now look toward the heavens, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-366G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-366G\"></sup>count the stars, if you are able to count them.” And He said to him, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-366H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-366H\"></sup>So shall your descendants be.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-367I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-367I\"></sup>Then he believed in the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; and He reckoned it to him as righteousness.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And He said to him, “I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> who brought you out of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-368J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-368J\"></sup>Ur of the Chaldeans, to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-368K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-368K\"></sup>give you this land to possess it.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>He said, “O Lord <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">God</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-369L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-369L\"></sup>how may I know that I will possess it?”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>So He said to him, “Bring Me a three year old heifer, and a three year old female goat, and a three year old ram, and a turtledove, and a young pigeon.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then he brought all these to Him and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-371M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-371M\"></sup>cut them in two, and laid each half opposite the other; but he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-371N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-371N\"></sup>did not cut the birds.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The birds of prey came down upon the carcasses, and Abram drove them away.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Now when the sun was going down, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-373O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-373O\"></sup>a deep sleep fell upon Abram; and behold, terror <i>and</i> great darkness fell upon him.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><i>God</i> said to Abram, “Know for certain that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-374P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-374P\"></sup>your descendants will be strangers in a land that is not theirs, where <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-374Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-374Q\"></sup>they will be enslaved and oppressed <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-374R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-374R\"></sup>four hundred years.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>But I will also judge the nation whom they will serve, and afterward they will come out <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-375S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-375S\"></sup>with many possessions.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>As for you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-376T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-376T\"></sup>you shall go to your fathers in peace; you will be buried at a good old age.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-377U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-377U\"></sup>the fourth generation they will return here, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-377V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-377V\"></sup>the iniquity of the Amorite is not yet complete.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>It came about when the sun had set, that it was very dark, and behold, <i>there appeared</i> a smoking oven and a flaming torch which <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-378W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-378W\"></sup>passed between these pieces.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>On that day the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> made a covenant with Abram, saying,“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-379X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-379X\"></sup>To your descendants I have given this land,From <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-379Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-379Y\"></sup>the river of Egypt as far as the great river, the river Euphrates:",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-380Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-380Z\"></sup>the Kenite and the Kenizzite and the Kadmonite",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>and the Hittite and the Perizzite and the Rephaim",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>and the Amorite and the Canaanite and the Girgashite and the Jebusite.”"
		},
		"16": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">16 </span>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-383A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-383A\"></sup>Sarai, Abram’s wife had borne him no <i>children</i>, and she had <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-383B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-383B\"></sup>an Egyptian maid whose name was Hagar.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>So Sarai said to Abram, “Now behold, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has prevented me from bearing <i>children</i>. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-384C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-384C\"></sup>Please go in to my maid; perhaps I will obtain children through her.” And Abram listened to the voice of Sarai.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>After Abram had lived <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-385D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-385D\"></sup>ten years in the land of Canaan, Abram’s wife Sarai took Hagar the Egyptian, her maid, and gave her to her husband Abram as his wife.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>He went in to Hagar, and she conceived; and when she saw that she had conceived, her mistress was despised in her sight.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And Sarai said to Abram, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-387E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-387E\"></sup>May the wrong done me be upon you. I gave my maid into your arms, but when she saw that she had conceived, I was despised in her sight. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-387F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-387F\"></sup>May the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> judge between you and me.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>But Abram said to Sarai, “Behold, your maid is in your power; do to her what is good in your sight.” So Sarai treated her harshly, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-388G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-388G\"></sup>she fled from her presence.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-389H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-389H\"></sup>the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> found her by a spring of water in the wilderness, by the spring on the way to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-389I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-389I\"></sup>Shur.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>He said, “Hagar, Sarai’s maid, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-390J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-390J\"></sup>where have you come from and where are you going?” And she said, “I am fleeing from the presence of my mistress Sarai.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to her, “Return to your mistress, and submit yourself to her authority.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Moreover, the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-392K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-392K\"></sup>angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to her, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-392L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-392L\"></sup>I will greatly multiply your descendants so that they will be too many to count.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to her further,“Behold, you are with child,And you will bear a son;And you shall call his name Ishmael,Because <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-393M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-393M\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has given heed to your affliction.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>“He will be a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-394N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-394N\"></sup>wild donkey of a man,His hand <i>will be</i> against everyone,And everyone’s hand <i>will be</i> against him;And he will live <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-394O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-394O\"></sup>to the east of all his brothers.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then she called the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> who spoke to her, “You are a God who sees”; for she said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-395P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-395P\"></sup>Have I even remained alive here after seeing Him?”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Therefore the well was called Beer-lahai-roi; behold, it is between <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-396Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-396Q\"></sup>Kadesh and Bered.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>So Hagar bore Abram a son; and Abram called the name of his son, whom Hagar bore, Ishmael.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Abram was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-398R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-398R\"></sup>eighty-six years old when Hagar bore Ishmael to him."
		},
		"17": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">17 </span>Now when Abram was ninety-nine years old, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-399A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-399A\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> appeared to Abram and said to him,“I am God <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-399B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-399B\"></sup>Almighty;Walk before Me, and be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-399C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-399C\"></sup>blameless.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“I will establish My <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-400D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-400D\"></sup>covenant between Me and you,And I will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-400E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-400E\"></sup>multiply you exceedingly.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Abram <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-401F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-401F\"></sup>fell on his face, and God talked with him, saying,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>“As for Me, behold, My covenant is with you,And you will be the father of a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-402G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-402G\"></sup>multitude of nations.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>“No longer shall your name be called Abram,But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-403H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-403H\"></sup>your name shall be Abraham;For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-403I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-403I\"></sup>I have made you the father of a multitude of nations.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>I will make you exceedingly fruitful, and I will make nations of you, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-404J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-404J\"></sup>kings will come forth from you.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>I will establish My covenant between Me and you and your descendants after you throughout their generations for an <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-405K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-405K\"></sup>everlasting covenant, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-405L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-405L\"></sup>to be God to you and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-405M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-405M\"></sup>to your descendants after you.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-406N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-406N\"></sup>I will give to you and to your descendants after you, the land of your sojournings, all the land of Canaan, for an everlasting possession; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-406O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-406O\"></sup>I will be their God.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>God said further to Abraham, “Now as for you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-407P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-407P\"></sup>you shall keep My covenant, you and your descendants after you throughout their generations.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-408Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-408Q\"></sup>This is My covenant, which you shall keep, between Me and you and your descendants after you: every male among you shall be circumcised.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-409R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-409R\"></sup>you shall be circumcised in the flesh of your foreskin, and it shall be the sign of the covenant between Me and you.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And every male among you who is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-410S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-410S\"></sup>eight days old shall be circumcised throughout your generations, a <i>servant</i> who is born in the house or who is bought with money from any foreigner, who is not of your descendants.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>A <i>servant</i> who is born in your house or <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-411T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-411T\"></sup>who is bought with your money shall surely be circumcised; thus shall My covenant be in your flesh for an everlasting covenant.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>But an uncircumcised male who is not circumcised in the flesh of his foreskin, that person shall be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-412U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-412U\"></sup>cut off from his people; he has broken My covenant.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then God said to Abraham, “As for Sarai your wife, you shall not call her name Sarai, but Sarah <i>shall be</i> her name.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>I will bless her, and indeed I will give you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-414V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-414V\"></sup>a son by her. Then I will bless her, and she shall be <i>a mother of</i> nations; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-414W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-414W\"></sup>kings of peoples will come from her.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then Abraham <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-415X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-415X\"></sup>fell on his face and laughed, and said in his heart, “Will a child be born to a man one hundred years old? And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-415Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-415Y\"></sup>will Sarah, who is ninety years old, bear <i>a child</i>?”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And Abraham said to God, “Oh that Ishmael might live before You!”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>But God said, “No, but Sarah your wife will bear you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-417Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-417Z\"></sup>a son, and you shall call his name Isaac; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-417AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-417AA\"></sup>I will establish My covenant with him for an everlasting covenant for his descendants after him.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>As for Ishmael, I have heard you; behold, I will bless him, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-418AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-418AB\"></sup>will make him fruitful and will multiply him exceedingly. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-418AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-418AC\"></sup>He shall become the father of twelve princes, and I will make him a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-418AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-418AD\"></sup>great nation.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>But My covenant I will establish with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-419AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-419AE\"></sup>Isaac, whom <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-419AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-419AF\"></sup>Sarah will bear to you at this season next year.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>When He finished talking with him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-420AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-420AG\"></sup>God went up from Abraham.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Then Abraham took Ishmael his son, and all <i>the servants</i> who were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-421AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-421AH\"></sup>born in his house and all who were bought with his money, every male among the men of Abraham’s household, and circumcised the flesh of their foreskin in the very same day, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-421AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-421AI\"></sup>as God had said to him.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Now Abraham was ninety-nine years old when <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-422AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-422AJ\"></sup>he was circumcised in the flesh of his foreskin.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-423AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-423AK\"></sup>Ishmael his son was thirteen years old when he was circumcised in the flesh of his foreskin.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>In the very same day Abraham was circumcised, and Ishmael his son.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>All the men of his household, who were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-425AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-425AL\"></sup>born in the house or bought with money from a foreigner, were circumcised with him."
		},
		"18": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">18 </span>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-426A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-426A\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> appeared to him by the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-426B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-426B\"></sup>oaks of Mamre, while he was sitting at the tent door in the heat of the day.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>When he lifted up his eyes and looked, behold, three <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-427C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-427C\"></sup>men were standing opposite him; and when he saw <i>them</i>, he ran from the tent door to meet them and bowed himself to the earth,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>and said, “My Lord, if now I have found favor in Your sight, please do not pass Your servant by.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Please let a little water be brought and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-429D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-429D\"></sup>wash your feet, and rest yourselves under the tree;",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>and I will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-430E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-430E\"></sup>bring a piece of bread, that you may refresh yourselves; after that you may go on, since you have visited your servant.” And they said, “So do, as you have said.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So Abraham hurried into the tent to Sarah, and said, “Quickly, prepare three measures of fine flour, knead <i>it</i> and make bread cakes.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Abraham also ran to the herd, and took a tender and choice calf and gave <i>it</i> to the servant, and he hurried to prepare it.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>He took curds and milk and the calf which he had prepared, and placed <i>it</i> before them; and he was standing by them under the tree as they ate.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then they said to him, “Where is Sarah your wife?” And he said, “There, in the tent.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>He said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-435F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-435F\"></sup>I will surely return to you at this time next year; and behold, Sarah your wife will have a son.” And Sarah was listening at the tent door, which was behind him.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-436G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-436G\"></sup>Abraham and Sarah were old, advanced in age; Sarah was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-436H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-436H\"></sup>past childbearing.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Sarah laughed to herself, saying, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-437I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-437I\"></sup>After I have become old, shall I have pleasure, my <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-437J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-437J\"></sup>lord being old also?”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Abraham, “Why did Sarah laugh, saying, ‘Shall I indeed bear <i>a child</i>, when I am <i>so</i> old?’",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-439K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-439K\"></sup>Is anything too difficult for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>? At the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-439L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-439L\"></sup>appointed time I will return to you, at this time next year, and Sarah will have a son.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Sarah denied <i>it</i> however, saying, “I did not laugh”; for she was afraid. And He said, “No, but you did laugh.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-441M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-441M\"></sup>the men rose up from there, and looked down toward Sodom; and Abraham was walking with them to send them off.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-442N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-442N\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said, “Shall I hide from Abraham <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-442O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-442O\"></sup>what I am about to do,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>since Abraham will surely become a great and mighty nation, and in him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-443P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-443P\"></sup>all the nations of the earth will be blessed?",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>For I have <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-444Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-444Q\"></sup>chosen him, so that he may <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-444R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-444R\"></sup>command his children and his household after him to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-444S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-444S\"></sup>keep the way of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> by doing righteousness and justice, so that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> may bring upon Abraham <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-444T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-444T\"></sup>what He has spoken about him.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-445U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-445U\"></sup>The outcry of Sodom and Gomorrah is indeed great, and their sin is exceedingly grave.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>I will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-446V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-446V\"></sup>go down now, and see if they have done entirely according to its outcry, which has come to Me; and if not, I will know.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-447W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-447W\"></sup>the men turned away from there and went toward Sodom, while Abraham was still standing before <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-447X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-447X\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Abraham came near and said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-448Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-448Y\"></sup>Will You indeed sweep away the righteous with the wicked?",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Suppose there are fifty righteous within the city; will You indeed sweep <i>it</i> away and not spare the place for the sake of the fifty righteous who are in it?",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Far be it from You to do such a thing, to slay the righteous with the wicked, so that the righteous and the wicked are <i>treated</i> alike. Far be it from You! Shall not <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-450Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-450Z\"></sup>the Judge of all the earth deal justly?”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>So the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-451AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-451AA\"></sup>If I find in Sodom fifty righteous within the city, then I will spare the whole place on their account.”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And Abraham replied, “Now behold, I have ventured to speak to the Lord, although I am <i>but</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-452AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-452AB\"></sup>dust and ashes.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Suppose the fifty righteous are lacking five, will You destroy the whole city because of five?” And He said, “I will not destroy <i>it</i> if I find forty-five there.”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>He spoke to Him yet again and said, “Suppose forty are found there?” And He said, “I will not do <i>it</i> on account of the forty.”",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Then he said, “Oh may the Lord not be angry, and I shall speak; suppose thirty are found there?” And He said, “I will not do <i>it</i> if I find thirty there.”",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>And he said, “Now behold, I have ventured to speak to the Lord; suppose twenty are found there?” And He said, “I will not destroy <i>it</i> on account of the twenty.”",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Then he said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-457AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-457AC\"></sup>Oh may the Lord not be angry, and I shall speak only this once; suppose ten are found there?” And He said, “I will not destroy <i>it</i> on account of the ten.”",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>As soon as He had finished speaking to Abraham <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-458AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-458AD\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> departed, and Abraham returned to his place."
		},
		"19": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">19 </span>Now the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-459A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-459A\"></sup>two angels came to Sodom in the evening as Lot was sitting in the gate of Sodom. When <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-459B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-459B\"></sup>Lot saw <i>them</i>, he rose to meet them and bowed down <i>with his</i> face to the ground.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And he said, “Now behold, my lords, please turn aside into your servant’s house, and spend the night, and wash your feet; then you may rise early and go on your way.” They said however, “No, but we shall spend the night in the square.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Yet he urged them strongly, so they turned aside to him and entered his house; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-461C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-461C\"></sup>and he prepared a feast for them, and baked unleavened bread, and they ate.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Before they lay down, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-462D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-462D\"></sup>the men of the city, the men of Sodom, surrounded the house, both young and old, all the people from every quarter;",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>and they called to Lot and said to him, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-463E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-463E\"></sup>Where are the men who came to you tonight? Bring them out to us that we may have relations with them.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>But Lot went out to them at the doorway, and shut the door behind him,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>and said, “Please, my brothers, do not act wickedly.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Now behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-466F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-466F\"></sup>I have two daughters who have not had relations with man; please let me bring them out to you, and do to them whatever you like; only do nothing to these men, inasmuch as they have come under the shelter of my roof.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>But they said, “Stand aside.” Furthermore, they said, “This one came in as an alien, and already <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-467G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-467G\"></sup>he is acting like a judge; now we will treat you worse than them.” So they pressed hard against Lot and came near to break the door.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-468H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-468H\"></sup>the men reached out their hands and brought Lot into the house with them, and shut the door.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-469I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-469I\"></sup>They struck the men who were at the doorway of the house with blindness, both small and great, so that they wearied <i>themselves trying</i> to find the doorway.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then the <i>two</i> men said to Lot, “Whom else have you here? A son-in-law, and your sons, and your daughters, and whomever you have in the city, bring <i>them</i> out of the place;",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>for we are about to destroy this place, because <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-471J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-471J\"></sup>their outcry has become so great before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-471K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-471K\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has sent us to destroy it.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Lot went out and spoke to his sons-in-law, who were to marry his daughters, and said, “Up, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-472L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-472L\"></sup>get out of this place, for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will destroy the city.” <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-472M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-472M\"></sup>But he appeared to his sons-in-law to be jesting.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>When morning dawned, the angels urged Lot, saying, “Up, take your wife and your two daughters who are here, or you will be swept away in the punishment of the city.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>But he hesitated. So the men <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-474N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-474N\"></sup>seized his hand and the hand of his wife and the hands of his two daughters, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-474O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-474O\"></sup>the compassion of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <i>was</i> upon him; and they brought him out, and put him outside the city.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>When they had brought them outside, one said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-475P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-475P\"></sup>Escape for your life! <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-475Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-475Q\"></sup>Do not look behind you, and do not stay anywhere in the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-475R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-475R\"></sup>valley; escape to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-475S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-475S\"></sup>the mountains, or you will be swept away.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>But Lot said to them, “Oh no, my lords!",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Now behold, your servant has found favor in your sight, and you have magnified your lovingkindness, which you have shown me by saving my life; but I cannot escape to the mountains, for the disaster will overtake me and I will die;",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>now behold, this town is near <i>enough</i> to flee to, and it is small. Please, let me escape there (is it not small?) that my life may be saved.”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>He said to him, “Behold, I grant you this request also, not to overthrow the town of which you have spoken.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Hurry, escape there, for I cannot do anything until you arrive there.” Therefore the name of the town was called <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-480T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-480T\"></sup>Zoar.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>The sun had risen over the earth when Lot came to Zoar.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-482U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-482U\"></sup>rained on Sodom and Gomorrah brimstone and fire from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> out of heaven,",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-483V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-483V\"></sup>He overthrew those cities, and all the valley, and all the inhabitants of the cities, and what grew on the ground.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>But his wife, from behind him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-484W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-484W\"></sup>looked <i>back</i>, and she became a pillar of salt.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Now Abraham arose early in the morning <i>and went</i> to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-485X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-485X\"></sup>the place where he had stood before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>;",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>and he looked down toward Sodom and Gomorrah, and toward all the land of the valley, and he saw, and behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-486Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-486Y\"></sup>the smoke of the land ascended like the smoke of a furnace.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Thus it came about, when God destroyed the cities of the valley, that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-487Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-487Z\"></sup>God remembered Abraham, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-487AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-487AA\"></sup>sent Lot out of the midst of the overthrow, when He overthrew the cities in which Lot lived.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Lot went up from Zoar, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-488AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-488AB\"></sup>stayed in the mountains, and his two daughters with him; for he was afraid to stay in Zoar; and he stayed in a cave, he and his two daughters.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Then the firstborn said to the younger, “Our father is old, and there is not a man on earth to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-489AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-489AC\"></sup>come in to us after the manner of the earth.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Come, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-490AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-490AD\"></sup>let us make our father drink wine, and let us lie with him that we may preserve our family through our father.”",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>So they made their father drink wine that night, and the firstborn went in and lay with her father; and he did not know when she lay down or when she arose.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>On the following day, the firstborn said to the younger, “Behold, I lay last night with my father; let us make him drink wine tonight also; then you go in and lie with him, that we may preserve our family through our father.”",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>So they made their father drink wine that night also, and the younger arose and lay with him; and he did not know when she lay down or when she arose.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Thus both the daughters of Lot were with child by their father.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>The firstborn bore a son, and called his name <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-495AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-495AE\"></sup>Moab; he is the father of the Moabites to this day.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>As for the younger, she also bore a son, and called his name Ben-ammi; he is the father of the sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-496AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-496AF\"></sup>Ammon to this day."
		},
		"20": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">20 </span>Now Abraham journeyed from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-497A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-497A\"></sup>there toward the land of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-497B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-497B\"></sup>the Negev, and settled between Kadesh and Shur; then he sojourned in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-497C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-497C\"></sup>Gerar.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Abraham said of Sarah his wife, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-498D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-498D\"></sup>She is my sister.” So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-498E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-498E\"></sup>Abimelech king of Gerar sent and took Sarah.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-499F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-499F\"></sup>But God came to Abimelech in a dream of the night, and said to him, “Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-499G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-499G\"></sup>you are a dead man because of the woman whom you have taken, for she is married.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Now Abimelech had not come near her; and he said, “Lord, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-500H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-500H\"></sup>will You slay a nation, even <i>though</i> blameless?",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Did he not himself say to me, ‘She is my sister’? And she <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-501I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-501I\"></sup>herself said, ‘He is my brother.’ In <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-501J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-501J\"></sup>the integrity of my heart and the innocence of my hands I have done this.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then God said to him in the dream, “Yes, I know that in the integrity of your heart you have done this, and I also <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-502K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-502K\"></sup>kept you from sinning against Me; therefore I did not let you touch her.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Now therefore, restore the man’s wife, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-503L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-503L\"></sup>he is a prophet, and he will pray for you and you will live. But if you do not restore <i>her</i>, know that you shall surely die, you and all who are yours.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>So Abimelech arose early in the morning and called all his servants and told all these things in their hearing; and the men were greatly frightened.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-505M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-505M\"></sup>Then Abimelech called Abraham and said to him, “What have you done to us? And how have I sinned against you, that you have brought on me and on my kingdom <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-505N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-505N\"></sup>a great sin? You have done to me things that ought not to be done.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And Abimelech said to Abraham, “What have you encountered, that you have done this thing?”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Abraham said, “Because I thought, surely there is no <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-507O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-507O\"></sup>fear of God in this place, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-507P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-507P\"></sup>they will kill me because of my wife.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Besides, she actually is my sister, the daughter of my father, but not the daughter of my mother, and she became my wife;",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>and it came about, when <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-509Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-509Q\"></sup>God caused me to wander from my father’s house, that I said to her, ‘This is the kindness which you will show to me: everywhere we go, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-509R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-509R\"></sup>say of me, “He is my brother.”’”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-510S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-510S\"></sup>Abimelech then took sheep and oxen and male and female servants, and gave them to Abraham, and restored his wife Sarah to him.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Abimelech said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-511T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-511T\"></sup>Behold, my land is before you; settle wherever you please.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>To Sarah he said, “Behold, I have given your <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-512U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-512U\"></sup>brother a thousand pieces of silver; behold, it is your vindication before all who are with you, and before all men you are cleared.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-513V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-513V\"></sup>Abraham prayed to God, and God healed Abimelech and his wife and his maids, so that they bore <i>children</i>.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-514W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-514W\"></sup>For the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had closed fast all the wombs of the household of Abimelech because of Sarah, Abraham’s wife."
		},
		"21": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">21 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-515A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-515A\"></sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> took note of Sarah as He had said, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> did for Sarah as He had promised.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-516B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-516B\"></sup>So Sarah conceived and bore a son to Abraham in his old age, at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-516C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-516C\"></sup>the appointed time of which God had spoken to him.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Abraham called the name of his son who was born to him, whom Sarah bore to him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-517D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-517D\"></sup>Isaac.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then Abraham circumcised his son Isaac when he was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-518E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-518E\"></sup>eight days old, as God had commanded him.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Now Abraham was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-519F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-519F\"></sup>one hundred years old when his son Isaac was born to him.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Sarah said, “God has made <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-520G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-520G\"></sup>laughter for me; everyone who hears will laugh with me.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And she said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-521H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-521H\"></sup>Who would have said to Abraham that Sarah would nurse children? Yet I have borne him a son in his old age.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The child grew and was weaned, and Abraham made a great feast on the day that Isaac was weaned.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Now Sarah saw <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-523I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-523I\"></sup>the son of Hagar the Egyptian, whom she had borne to Abraham, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-523J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-523J\"></sup>mocking.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Therefore she said to Abraham, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-524K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-524K\"></sup>Drive out this maid and her son, for the son of this maid shall not be an heir with my son Isaac.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-525L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-525L\"></sup>The matter distressed Abraham greatly because of his son.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>But God said to Abraham, “Do not be distressed because of the lad and your maid; whatever Sarah tells you, listen to her, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-526M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-526M\"></sup>through Isaac your descendants shall be named.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-527N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-527N\"></sup>the son of the maid I will make a nation also, because he is your descendant.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>So Abraham rose early in the morning and took bread and a skin of water and gave <i>them</i> to Hagar, putting <i>them</i> on her shoulder, and <i>gave her</i> the boy, and sent her away. And she departed and wandered about in the wilderness of Beersheba.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>When the water in the skin was used up, she left the boy under one of the bushes.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then she went and sat down opposite him, about a bowshot away, for she said, “Do not let me see the boy die.” And she sat opposite him, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-530O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-530O\"></sup>lifted up her voice and wept.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>God <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-531P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-531P\"></sup>heard the lad crying; and the angel of God called to Hagar from heaven and said to her, “What is the matter with you, Hagar? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-531Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-531Q\"></sup>Do not fear, for God has heard the voice of the lad where he is.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Arise, lift up the lad, and hold him by the hand, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-532R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-532R\"></sup>for I will make a great nation of him.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Then God <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-533S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-533S\"></sup>opened her eyes and she saw <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-533T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-533T\"></sup>a well of water; and she went and filled the skin with water and gave the lad a drink.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-534U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-534U\"></sup>God was with the lad, and he grew; and he lived in the wilderness and became an archer.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-535V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-535V\"></sup>He lived in the wilderness of Paran, and his mother took a wife for him from the land of Egypt.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Now it came about at that time that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-536W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-536W\"></sup>Abimelech and Phicol, the commander of his army, spoke to Abraham, saying, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-536X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-536X\"></sup>God is with you in all that you do;",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>now therefore, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-537Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-537Y\"></sup>swear to me here by God that you will not deal falsely with me or with my offspring or with my posterity, but according to the kindness that I have shown to you, you shall show to me and to the land in which you have sojourned.”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Abraham said, “I swear it.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>But Abraham complained to Abimelech because of the well of water which the servants of Abimelech <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-539Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-539Z\"></sup>had seized.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>And Abimelech said, “I do not know who has done this thing; you did not tell me, nor did I hear of it until today.”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Abraham took sheep and oxen and gave them to Abimelech, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-541AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-541AA\"></sup>the two of them made a covenant.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Then Abraham set seven ewe lambs of the flock by themselves.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Abimelech said to Abraham, “What do these seven ewe lambs mean, which you have set by themselves?”",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>He said, “You shall take these seven ewe lambs from my hand so that it may be a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-544AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-544AB\"></sup>witness to me, that I dug this well.”",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Therefore he called that place <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-545AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-545AC\"></sup>Beersheba, because there the two of them took an oath.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>So they made a covenant at Beersheba; and Abimelech and Phicol, the commander of his army, arose and returned to the land of the Philistines.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup><i>Abraham</i> planted a tamarisk tree at Beersheba, and there <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-547AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-547AD\"></sup>he called on the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-547AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-547AE\"></sup>Everlasting God.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>And Abraham sojourned <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-548AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-548AF\"></sup>in the land of the Philistines for many days."
		},
		"22": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">22 </span>Now it came about after these things, that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-549A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-549A\"></sup>God tested Abraham, and said to him, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-549B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-549B\"></sup>Abraham!” And he said, “Here I am.”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He said, “Take now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-550C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-550C\"></sup>your son, your only son, whom you love, Isaac, and go to the land of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-550D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-550D\"></sup>Moriah, and offer him there as a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-550E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-550E\"></sup>burnt offering on one of the mountains of which I will tell you.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>So Abraham rose early in the morning and saddled his donkey, and took two of his young men with him and Isaac his son; and he split wood for the burnt offering, and arose and went to the place of which God had told him.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>On the third day Abraham raised his eyes and saw the place from a distance.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Abraham said to his young men, “Stay here with the donkey, and I and the lad will go over there; and we will worship and return to you.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Abraham took the wood of the burnt offering and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-554F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-554F\"></sup>laid it on Isaac his son, and he took in his hand the fire and the knife. So the two of them walked on together.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Isaac spoke to Abraham his father and said, “My father!” And he said, “Here I am, my son.” And he said, “Behold, the fire and the wood, but where is the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-555G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-555G\"></sup>lamb for the burnt offering?”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Abraham said, “God will provide for Himself the lamb for the burnt offering, my son.” So the two of them walked on together.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then they came to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-557H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-557H\"></sup>the place of which God had told him; and Abraham built <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-557I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-557I\"></sup>the altar there and arranged the wood, and bound his son Isaac and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-557J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-557J\"></sup>laid him on the altar, on top of the wood.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Abraham stretched out his hand and took the knife to slay his son.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-559K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-559K\"></sup>the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> called to him from heaven and said, “Abraham, Abraham!” And he said, “Here I am.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>He said, “Do not stretch out your hand against the lad, and do nothing to him; for now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-560L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-560L\"></sup>I know that you fear God, since you have not withheld <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-560M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-560M\"></sup>your son, your only son, from Me.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then Abraham raised his eyes and looked, and behold, behind <i>him</i> a ram caught in the thicket by his horns; and Abraham went and took the ram and offered him up for a burnt offering in the place of his son.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Abraham called the name of that place The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> Will Provide, as it is said to this day, “In the mount of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-562N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-562N\"></sup>it will be provided.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> called to Abraham a second time from heaven,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>and said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-564O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-564O\"></sup>By Myself I have sworn, declares the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, because you have done this thing and have not withheld your son, your only son,",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>indeed I will greatly bless you, and I will greatly <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-565P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-565P\"></sup>multiply your seed as the stars of the heavens and as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-565Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-565Q\"></sup>the sand which is on the seashore; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-565R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-565R\"></sup>your seed shall possess the gate of their enemies.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-566S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-566S\"></sup>In your seed all the nations of the earth shall be blessed, because you have <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-566T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-566T\"></sup>obeyed My voice.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-567U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-567U\"></sup>So Abraham returned to his young men, and they arose and went together to Beersheba; and Abraham lived at Beersheba.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Now it came about after these things, that it was told Abraham, saying, “Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-568V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-568V\"></sup>Milcah also has borne children to your brother Nahor:",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Uz his firstborn and Buz his brother and Kemuel the father of Aram",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>and Chesed and Hazo and Pildash and Jidlaph and Bethuel.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Bethuel became the father of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-571W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-571W\"></sup>Rebekah; these eight Milcah bore to Nahor, Abraham’s brother.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>His concubine, whose name was Reumah, also bore Tebah and Gaham and Tahash and Maacah."
		},
		"23": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">23 </span>Now Sarah lived one hundred and twenty-seven years; <i>these were</i> the years of the life of Sarah.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Sarah died in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-574A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-574A\"></sup>Kiriath-arba (that is, Hebron) in the land of Canaan; and Abraham went in to mourn for Sarah and to weep for her.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then Abraham rose from before his dead, and spoke to the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-575B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-575B\"></sup>sons of Heth, saying,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>“I am <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-576C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-576C\"></sup>a stranger and a sojourner among you; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-576D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-576D\"></sup>give me a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-576E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-576E\"></sup>burial site among you that I may bury my dead out of my sight.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The sons of Heth answered Abraham, saying to him,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>“Hear us, my lord, you are a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-578F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-578F\"></sup>mighty prince among us; bury your dead in the choicest of our graves; none of us will refuse you his grave for burying your dead.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>So Abraham rose and bowed to the people of the land, the sons of Heth.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And he spoke with them, saying, “If it is your wish <i>for me</i> to bury my dead out of my sight, hear me, and approach <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-580G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-580G\"></sup>Ephron the son of Zohar for me,",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>that he may give me the cave of Machpelah which he owns, which is at the end of his field; for the full price let him give it to me in your presence for a burial site.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Now Ephron was sitting among the sons of Heth; and Ephron the Hittite answered Abraham in the hearing of the sons of Heth; <i>even</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-582H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-582H\"></sup>of all who went in at the gate of his city, saying,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“No, my lord, hear me; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-583I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-583I\"></sup>I give you the field, and I give you the cave that is in it. In the presence of the sons of my people I give it to you; bury your dead.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And Abraham bowed before the people of the land.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>He spoke to Ephron in the hearing of the people of the land, saying, “If you will only please listen to me; I will give the price of the field, accept <i>it</i> from me that I may bury my dead there.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then Ephron answered Abraham, saying to him,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>“My lord, listen to me; a piece of land worth four hundred <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-587J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-587J\"></sup>shekels of silver, what is that between me and you? So bury your dead.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Abraham listened to Ephron; and Abraham <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-588K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-588K\"></sup>weighed out for Ephron the silver which he had named in the hearing of the sons of Heth, four hundred shekels of silver, commercial standard.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-589L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-589L\"></sup>Ephron’s field, which was in Machpelah, which faced Mamre, the field and cave which was in it, and all the trees which were in the field, that were within all the confines of its border, were deeded over",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>to Abraham for a possession <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-590M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-590M\"></sup>in the presence of the sons of Heth, before all who went in at the gate of his city.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>After this, Abraham buried Sarah his wife in the cave of the field at Machpelah facing Mamre (that is, Hebron) in the land of Canaan.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>So the field and the cave that is in it, were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-592N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-592N\"></sup>deeded over to Abraham for a burial site by the sons of Heth."
		},
		"24": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">24 </span>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-593A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-593A\"></sup>Abraham was old, advanced in age; and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-593B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-593B\"></sup>blessed Abraham in every way.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Abraham said to his servant, the oldest of his household, who had <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-594C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-594C\"></sup>charge of all that he owned, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-594D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-594D\"></sup>Please place your hand under my thigh,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>and I will make you swear by the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-595E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-595E\"></sup>the God of heaven and the God of earth, that you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-595F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-595F\"></sup>shall not take a wife for my son from the daughters of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-595G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-595G\"></sup>the Canaanites, among whom I live,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>but you will go to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-596H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-596H\"></sup>my country and to my relatives, and take a wife for my son Isaac.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The servant said to him, “Suppose the woman is not willing to follow me to this land; should I take your son back to the land from where you came?”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then Abraham said to him, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-598I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-598I\"></sup>Beware that you do not take my son back there!",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-599J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-599J\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of heaven, who took me from my father’s house and from the land of my birth, and who spoke to me and who swore to me, saying, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-599K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-599K\"></sup>To your descendants I will give this land,’ He will send <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-599L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-599L\"></sup>His angel before you, and you will take a wife for my son from there.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>But if the woman is not willing to follow you, then you will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-600M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-600M\"></sup>be free from this my oath; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-600N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-600N\"></sup>only do not take my son back there.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>So the servant <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-601O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-601O\"></sup>placed his hand under the thigh of Abraham his master, and swore to him concerning this matter.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then the servant took ten camels from the camels of his master, and set out with a variety of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-602P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-602P\"></sup>good things of his master’s in his hand; and he arose and went to Mesopotamia, to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-602Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-602Q\"></sup>the city of Nahor.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>He made the camels kneel down outside the city by <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-603R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-603R\"></sup>the well of water at evening time, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-603S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-603S\"></sup>the time when women go out to draw water.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>He said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-604T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-604T\"></sup>O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of my master Abraham, please <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-604U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-604U\"></sup>grant me success today, and show lovingkindness to my master Abraham.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-605V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-605V\"></sup>I am standing by the spring, and the daughters of the men of the city are coming out to draw water;",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>now may it be that the girl to whom I say, ‘Please let down your jar so that I may drink,’ and who answers, ‘Drink, and I will water your camels also’—<i>may</i> she <i>be the one</i> whom You have appointed for Your servant Isaac; and by this I will know that You have shown lovingkindness to my master.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-607W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-607W\"></sup>Before he had finished speaking, behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-607X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-607X\"></sup>Rebekah who was born to Bethuel the son of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-607Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-607Y\"></sup>Milcah, the wife of Abraham’s brother Nahor, came out with her jar on her shoulder.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The girl was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-608Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-608Z\"></sup>very beautiful, a virgin, and no man had had relations with her; and she went down to the spring and filled her jar and came up.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then the servant ran to meet her, and said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-609AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-609AA\"></sup>Please let me drink a little water from your jar.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-610AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-610AB\"></sup>She said, “Drink, my lord”; and she quickly lowered her jar to her hand, and gave him a drink.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Now when she had finished giving him a drink, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-611AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-611AC\"></sup>she said, “I will draw also for your camels until they have finished drinking.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>So she quickly emptied her jar into the trough, and ran back to the well to draw, and she drew for all his camels.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-613AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-613AD\"></sup>Meanwhile, the man was gazing at her in silence, to know whether the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had made his journey successful or not.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>When the camels had finished drinking, the man took a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-614AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-614AE\"></sup>gold ring weighing a half-shekel and two bracelets for her wrists weighing ten shekels in gold,",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>and said, “Whose daughter are you? Please tell me, is there room for us to lodge in your father’s house?”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>She said to him, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-616AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-616AF\"></sup>I am the daughter of Bethuel, the son of Milcah, whom she bore to Nahor.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Again she said to him, “We have plenty of both straw and feed, and room to lodge in.”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Then the man <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-618AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-618AG\"></sup>bowed low and worshiped the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>He said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-619AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-619AH\"></sup>Blessed be the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of my master Abraham, who has not forsaken <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-619AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-619AI\"></sup>His lovingkindness and His truth toward my master; as for me, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-619AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-619AJ\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has guided me in the way to the house of my master’s brothers.”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-620AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-620AK\"></sup>the girl ran and told her mother’s household about these things.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Now Rebekah had a brother whose name was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-621AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-621AL\"></sup>Laban; and Laban ran outside to the man at the spring.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>When he saw the ring and the bracelets on his sister’s wrists, and when he heard the words of Rebekah his sister, saying, “This is what the man said to me,” he went to the man; and behold, he was standing by the camels at the spring.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>And he said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-623AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-623AM\"></sup>Come in, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-623AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-623AN\"></sup>blessed of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>! Why do you stand outside since <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-623AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-623AO\"></sup>I have prepared the house, and a place for the camels?”",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>So the man entered the house. Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-624AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-624AP\"></sup>Laban unloaded the camels, and he gave straw and feed to the camels, and water to wash his feet and the feet of the men who were with him.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>But when <i>food</i> was set before him to eat, he said, “I will not eat until I have told my business.” And he said, “Speak on.”",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>So he said, “I am <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-626AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-626AQ\"></sup>Abraham’s servant.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has greatly <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-627AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-627AR\"></sup>blessed my master, so that he has become rich; and He has given him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-627AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-627AS\"></sup>flocks and herds, and silver and gold, and servants and maids, and camels and donkeys.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-628AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-628AT\"></sup>Sarah my master’s wife bore a son to my master in her old age, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-628AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-628AU\"></sup>he has given him all that he has.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-629AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-629AV\"></sup>My master made me swear, saying, ‘You shall not take a wife for my son from the daughters of the Canaanites, in whose land I live;",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>but you shall go to my father’s house and to my relatives, and take a wife for my son.’",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-631AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-631AW\"></sup>I said to my master, ‘Suppose the woman does not follow me.’",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>He said to me, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-632AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-632AX\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, before whom I have <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-632AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-632AY\"></sup>walked, will send <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-632AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-632AZ\"></sup>His angel with you to make your journey successful, and you will take a wife for my son from my relatives and from my father’s house;",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-633BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-633BA\"></sup>then you will be free from my oath, when you come to my relatives; and if they do not give her to you, you will be free from my oath.’",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>“So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-634BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-634BB\"></sup>I came today to the spring, and said, ‘O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of my master Abraham, if now You will make my journey on which I go <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-634BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-634BC\"></sup>successful;",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-635BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-635BD\"></sup>I am standing by the spring, and may it be that the maiden who comes out to draw, and to whom I say, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-635BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-635BE\"></sup>Please let me drink a little water from your jar”;",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>and she will say to me, “You drink, and I will draw for your camels also”; let her be the woman whom the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has appointed for my master’s son.’",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>“Before I had finished <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-637BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-637BF\"></sup>speaking in my heart, behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-637BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-637BG\"></sup>Rebekah came out with her jar on her shoulder, and went down to the spring and drew, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-637BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-637BH\"></sup>I said to her, ‘Please let me drink.’",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>She quickly lowered her jar from her <i>shoulder</i>, and said, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-638BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-638BI\"></sup>Drink, and I will water your camels also’; so I drank, and she watered the camels also.",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-639BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-639BJ\"></sup>Then I asked her, and said, ‘Whose daughter are you?’ And she said, ‘The daughter of Bethuel, Nahor’s son, whom Milcah bore to him’; and I put the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-639BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-639BK\"></sup>ring on her nose, and the bracelets on her wrists.",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>And I <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-640BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-640BL\"></sup>bowed low and worshiped the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and blessed the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of my master Abraham, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-640BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-640BM\"></sup>who had guided me in the right way to take the daughter of my master’s kinsman for his son.",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>So now if you are going to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-641BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-641BN\"></sup>deal kindly and truly with my master, tell me; and if not, let me know, that I may turn to the right hand or the left.”",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>Then Laban and Bethuel replied, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-642BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-642BO\"></sup>The matter comes from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-642BP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BP&quot;&gt;BP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-642BP\"></sup><i>so</i> we cannot speak to you bad or good.",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>Here is Rebekah before you, take <i>her</i> and go, and let her be the wife of your master’s son, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has spoken.”",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>When Abraham’s servant heard their words, he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-644BQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BQ&quot;&gt;BQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-644BQ\"></sup>bowed himself to the ground before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"53": "<sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup>The servant brought out <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-645BR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BR&quot;&gt;BR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-645BR\"></sup>articles of silver and articles of gold, and garments, and gave them to Rebekah; he also gave precious things to her brother and to her mother.",
			"54": "<sup class=\"versenum\">54 </sup>Then he and the men who were with him ate and drank and spent the night. When they arose in the morning, he said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-646BS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BS&quot;&gt;BS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-646BS\"></sup>Send me away to my master.”",
			"55": "<sup class=\"versenum\">55 </sup>But her brother and her mother said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-647BT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BT&quot;&gt;BT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-647BT\"></sup>Let the girl stay with us <i>a few</i> days, say ten; afterward she may go.”",
			"56": "<sup class=\"versenum\">56 </sup>He said to them, “Do not delay me, since <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-648BU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BU&quot;&gt;BU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-648BU\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has prospered my way. Send me away that I may go to my master.”",
			"57": "<sup class=\"versenum\">57 </sup>And they said, “We will call the girl and consult her wishes.”",
			"58": "<sup class=\"versenum\">58 </sup>Then they called Rebekah and said to her, “Will you go with this man?” And she said, “I will go.”",
			"59": "<sup class=\"versenum\">59 </sup>Thus they sent away their sister Rebekah and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-651BV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BV&quot;&gt;BV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-651BV\"></sup>her nurse with Abraham’s servant and his men.",
			"60": "<sup class=\"versenum\">60 </sup>They blessed Rebekah and said to her,“May you, our sister,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-652BW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BW&quot;&gt;BW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-652BW\"></sup>Become thousands of ten thousands,And may <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-652BX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BX&quot;&gt;BX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-652BX\"></sup>your descendants possessThe gate of those who hate them.”",
			"61": "<sup class=\"versenum\">61 </sup>Then Rebekah arose with her maids, and they mounted the camels and followed the man. So the servant took Rebekah and departed.",
			"62": "<sup class=\"versenum\">62 </sup>Now Isaac had come from going to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-654BY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BY&quot;&gt;BY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-654BY\"></sup>Beer-lahai-roi; for he was living in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-654BZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BZ&quot;&gt;BZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-654BZ\"></sup>the Negev.",
			"63": "<sup class=\"versenum\">63 </sup>Isaac went out <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-655CA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CA&quot;&gt;CA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-655CA\"></sup>to meditate in the field toward evening; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-655CB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CB&quot;&gt;CB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-655CB\"></sup>he lifted up his eyes and looked, and behold, camels were coming.",
			"64": "<sup class=\"versenum\">64 </sup>Rebekah lifted up her eyes, and when she saw Isaac she dismounted from the camel.",
			"65": "<sup class=\"versenum\">65 </sup>She said to the servant, “Who is that man walking in the field to meet us?” And the servant said, “He is my master.” Then she took her veil and covered herself.",
			"66": "<sup class=\"versenum\">66 </sup>The servant told Isaac all the things that he had done.",
			"67": "<sup class=\"versenum\">67 </sup>Then Isaac brought her into his mother Sarah’s tent, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-659CC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CC&quot;&gt;CC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-659CC\"></sup>he took Rebekah, and she became his wife, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-659CD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CD&quot;&gt;CD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-659CD\"></sup>he loved her; thus Isaac was comforted after <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-659CE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CE&quot;&gt;CE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-659CE\"></sup>his mother’s death."
		},
		"25": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">25 </span>Now Abraham took another wife, whose name was Keturah.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-661A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-661A\"></sup>She bore to him Zimran and Jokshan and Medan and Midian and Ishbak and Shuah.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Jokshan became the father of Sheba and Dedan. And the sons of Dedan were Asshurim and Letushim and Leummim.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The sons of Midian <i>were</i> Ephah and Epher and Hanoch and Abida and Eldaah. All these <i>were</i> the sons of Keturah.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-664B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-664B\"></sup>Now Abraham gave all that he had to Isaac;",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>but to the sons of his concubines, Abraham gave gifts while he was still living, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-665C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-665C\"></sup>sent them away from his son Isaac eastward, to the land of the east.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>These are all the years of Abraham’s life that he lived, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-666D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-666D\"></sup>one hundred and seventy-five years.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Abraham breathed his last and died <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-667E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-667E\"></sup>in a ripe old age, an old man and satisfied <i>with life</i>; and he was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-667F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-667F\"></sup>gathered to his people.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then his sons Isaac and Ishmael buried him in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-668G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-668G\"></sup>the cave of Machpelah, in the field of Ephron the son of Zohar the Hittite, facing Mamre,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-669H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-669H\"></sup>the field which Abraham purchased from the sons of Heth; there Abraham was buried with Sarah his wife.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>It came about after the death of Abraham, that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-670I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-670I\"></sup>God blessed his son Isaac; and Isaac lived by <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-670J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-670J\"></sup>Beer-lahai-roi.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Now these are <i>the records of</i> the generations of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-671K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-671K\"></sup>Ishmael, Abraham’s son, whom Hagar the Egyptian, Sarah’s maid, bore to Abraham;",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>and these are the names of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-672L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-672L\"></sup>the sons of Ishmael, by their names, in the order of their birth: Nebaioth, the firstborn of Ishmael, and Kedar and Adbeel and Mibsam",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>and Mishma and Dumah and Massa,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Hadad and Tema, Jetur, Naphish and Kedemah.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>These are the sons of Ishmael and these are their names, by their villages, and by their camps; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-675M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-675M\"></sup>twelve princes according to their tribes.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>These are the years of the life of Ishmael, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-676N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-676N\"></sup>one hundred and thirty-seven years; and he breathed his last and died, and was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-676O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-676O\"></sup>gathered to his people.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>They settled from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-677P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-677P\"></sup>Havilah to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-677Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-677Q\"></sup>Shur which is east of Egypt as one goes toward Assyria; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-677R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-677R\"></sup>he settled in defiance of all his relatives.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Now these are <i>the records of</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-678S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-678S\"></sup>the generations of Isaac, Abraham’s son: Abraham became the father of Isaac;",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>and Isaac was forty years old when he took <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-679T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-679T\"></sup>Rebekah, the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-679U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-679U\"></sup>daughter of Bethuel the Aramean of Paddan-aram, the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-679V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-679V\"></sup>sister of Laban the Aramean, to be his wife.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Isaac prayed to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> on behalf of his wife, because she was barren; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-680W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-680W\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> answered him and Rebekah his wife <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-680X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-680X\"></sup>conceived.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>But the children struggled together within her; and she said, “If it is so, why then am I <i>this way</i>?” So she went to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-681Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-681Y\"></sup>inquire of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to her,“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-682Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-682Z\"></sup>Two nations are in your womb;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-682AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-682AA\"></sup>And two peoples will be separated from your body;And one people shall be stronger than the other;And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-682AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-682AB\"></sup>the older shall serve the younger.”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>When her days to be delivered were fulfilled, behold, there were twins in her womb.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Now the first came forth red, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-684AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-684AC\"></sup>all over like a hairy garment; and they named him Esau.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Afterward his brother came forth with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-685AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-685AD\"></sup>his hand holding on to Esau’s heel, so <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-685AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-685AE\"></sup>his name was called Jacob; and Isaac was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-685AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-685AF\"></sup>sixty years old when she gave birth to them.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>When the boys grew up, Esau became a skillful hunter, a man of the field, but Jacob was a peaceful man, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-686AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-686AG\"></sup>living in tents.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Now Isaac loved Esau, because he had <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-687AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-687AH\"></sup>a taste for game, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-687AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-687AI\"></sup>but Rebekah loved Jacob.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>When Jacob had cooked <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-688AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-688AJ\"></sup>stew, Esau came in from the field and he was famished;",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>and Esau said to Jacob, “Please let me have a swallow of that red stuff there, for I am famished.” Therefore his name was called Edom.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>But Jacob said, “First sell me your <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-690AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-690AK\"></sup>birthright.”",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Esau said, “Behold, I am about to die; so of what <i>use</i> then is the birthright to me?”",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>And Jacob said, “First swear to me”; so he swore to him, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-692AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-692AL\"></sup>sold his birthright to Jacob.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Then Jacob gave Esau bread and lentil stew; and he ate and drank, and rose and went on his way. Thus Esau despised his birthright."
		},
		"26": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">26 </span>Now there was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-694A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-694A\"></sup>a famine in the land, besides the previous famine that had occurred in the days of Abraham. So Isaac went to Gerar, to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-694B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-694B\"></sup>Abimelech king of the Philistines.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-695C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-695C\"></sup>appeared to him and said, “Do not go down to Egypt; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-695D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-695D\"></sup>stay in the land of which I shall tell you.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Sojourn in this land and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-696E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-696E\"></sup>I will be with you and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-696F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-696F\"></sup>bless you, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-696G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-696G\"></sup>to you and to your descendants I will give all these lands, and I will establish <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-696H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-696H\"></sup>the oath which I swore to your father Abraham.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-697I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-697I\"></sup>I will multiply your descendants as the stars of heaven, and will give your descendants all these lands; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-697J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-697J\"></sup>by your descendants all the nations of the earth shall be blessed;",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>because Abraham <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-698K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-698K\"></sup>obeyed Me and kept My charge, My commandments, My statutes and My laws.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So Isaac lived in Gerar.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>When the men of the place asked about his wife, he said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-700L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-700L\"></sup>She is my sister,” for he was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-700M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-700M\"></sup>afraid to say, “my wife,” <i>thinking</i>, “the men of the place might kill me on account of Rebekah, for she is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-700N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-700N\"></sup>beautiful.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>It came about, when he had been there a long time, that Abimelech king of the Philistines looked out through a window, and saw, and behold, Isaac was caressing his wife Rebekah.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then Abimelech called Isaac and said, “Behold, certainly she is your wife! How then did you say, ‘She is my sister’?” And Isaac said to him, “Because I said, ‘I might die on account of her.’”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-703O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-703O\"></sup>Abimelech said, “What is this you have done to us? One of the people might easily have lain with your wife, and you would have brought guilt upon us.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>So Abimelech charged all the people, saying, “He who <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-704P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-704P\"></sup>touches this man or his wife shall surely be put to death.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Now Isaac sowed in that land and reaped in the same year a hundredfold. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-705Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-705Q\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> blessed him,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>and the man <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-706R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-706R\"></sup>became rich, and continued to grow richer until he became very wealthy;",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-707S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-707S\"></sup>he had possessions of flocks and herds and a great household, so that the Philistines envied him.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-708T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-708T\"></sup>all the wells which his father’s servants had dug in the days of Abraham his father, the Philistines stopped up by filling them with earth.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then Abimelech said to Isaac, “Go away from us, for you are <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-709U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-709U\"></sup>too powerful for us.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And Isaac departed from there and camped in the valley of Gerar, and settled there.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then Isaac dug again the wells of water which had been dug in the days of his father Abraham, for the Philistines had stopped them up after the death of Abraham; and he gave them the same names which his father had given them.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>But when Isaac’s servants dug in the valley and found there a well of flowing water,",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>the herdsmen of Gerar <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-713V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-713V\"></sup>quarreled with the herdsmen of Isaac, saying, “The water is ours!” So he named the well Esek, because they contended with him.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then they dug another well, and they quarreled over it too, so he named it Sitnah.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>He moved away from there and dug another well, and they did not quarrel over it; so he named it Rehoboth, for he said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-715W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-715W\"></sup>At last the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has made room for us, and we will be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-715X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-715X\"></sup>fruitful in the land.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Then he went up from there to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-716Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-716Y\"></sup>Beersheba.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-717Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-717Z\"></sup>appeared to him the same night and said,“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-717AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-717AA\"></sup>I am the God of your father Abraham;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-717AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-717AB\"></sup>Do not fear, for I am with you.I <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-717AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-717AC\"></sup>will bless you, and multiply your descendants,For the sake of My servant Abraham.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>So he built an <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-718AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-718AD\"></sup>altar there and called upon the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and pitched his tent there; and there Isaac’s servants dug a well.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-719AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-719AE\"></sup>Abimelech came to him from Gerar with his adviser Ahuzzath and Phicol the commander of his army.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Isaac said to them, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-720AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-720AF\"></sup>Why have you come to me, since you hate me and have sent me away from you?”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>They said, “We see plainly <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-721AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-721AG\"></sup>that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has been with you; so we said, ‘Let there now be an oath between us, <i>even</i> between you and us, and let us make a covenant with you,",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>that you will do us no harm, just as we have not touched you and have done to you nothing but good and have sent you away in peace. You are now the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-722AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-722AH\"></sup>blessed of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.’”",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-723AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-723AI\"></sup>he made them a feast, and they ate and drank.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>In the morning they arose early and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-724AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-724AJ\"></sup>exchanged oaths; then Isaac sent them away and they departed from him in peace.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Now it came about on the same day, that Isaac’s servants came in and told him about the well which they had dug, and said to him, “We have found water.”",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>So he called it Shibah; therefore the name of the city is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-726AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-726AK\"></sup>Beersheba to this day.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>When Esau was forty years old <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-727AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-727AL\"></sup>he married Judith the daughter of Beeri the Hittite, and Basemath the daughter of Elon the Hittite;",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-728AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-728AM\"></sup>they brought grief to Isaac and Rebekah."
		},
		"27": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">27 </span>Now it came about, when Isaac was old and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-729A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-729A\"></sup>his eyes were too dim to see, that he called his <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-729B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-729B\"></sup>older son Esau and said to him, “My son.” And he said to him, “Here I am.”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-730C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-730C\"></sup>Isaac said, “Behold now, I am old <i>and</i> I do not know the day of my death.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Now then, please take your gear, your quiver and your bow, and go out to the field and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-731D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-731D\"></sup>hunt game for me;",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>and prepare a savory dish for me such as I love, and bring it to me that I may eat, so that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-732E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-732E\"></sup>my soul may bless you before I die.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Rebekah was listening while Isaac spoke to his son Esau. So when Esau went to the field to hunt for game to bring <i>home</i>,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-734F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-734F\"></sup>Rebekah said to her son Jacob, “Behold, I heard your father speak to your brother Esau, saying,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>‘Bring me <i>some</i> game and prepare a savory dish for me, that I may eat, and bless you in the presence of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> before my death.’",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Now therefore, my son, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-736G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-736G\"></sup>listen to me as I command you.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Go now to the flock and bring me two choice young goats from there, that I may prepare them <i>as</i> a savory dish for your father, such as he loves.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then you shall bring <i>it</i> to your father, that he may eat, so that he may bless you before his death.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Jacob answered his mother Rebekah, “Behold, Esau my brother is a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-739H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-739H\"></sup>hairy man and I am a smooth man.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-740I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-740I\"></sup>Perhaps my father will feel me, then I will be as a deceiver in his sight, and I will bring upon myself a curse and not a blessing.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>But his mother said to him, “Your curse be on me, my son; only <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-741J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-741J\"></sup>obey my voice, and go, get <i>them</i> for me.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>So he went and got <i>them</i>, and brought <i>them</i> to his mother; and his mother made savory food such as his father loved.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then Rebekah took the best <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-743K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-743K\"></sup>garments of Esau her elder son, which were with her in the house, and put them on Jacob her younger son.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And she put the skins of the young goats on his hands and on the smooth part of his neck.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>She also gave the savory food and the bread, which she had made, to her son Jacob.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then he came to his father and said, “My father.” And he said, “Here I am. Who are you, my son?”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Jacob said to his father, “I am Esau your firstborn; I have done as you told me. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-747L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-747L\"></sup>Get up, please, sit and eat of my game, that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-747M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-747M\"></sup>you may bless me.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Isaac said to his son, “How is it that you have <i>it</i> so quickly, my son?” And he said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-748N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-748N\"></sup>Because the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God caused <i>it</i> to happen to me.”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then Isaac said to Jacob, “Please come close, that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-749O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-749O\"></sup>I may feel you, my son, whether you are really my son Esau or not.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>So Jacob came close to Isaac his father, and he felt him and said, “The voice is the voice of Jacob, but the hands are the hands of Esau.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>He did not recognize him, because his hands were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-751P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-751P\"></sup>hairy like his brother Esau’s hands; so he blessed him.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And he said, “Are you really my son Esau?” And he said, “I am.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>So he said, “Bring <i>it</i> to me, and I will eat of my son’s game, that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-753Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-753Q\"></sup>I may bless you.” And he brought <i>it</i> to him, and he ate; he also brought him wine and he drank.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Then his father Isaac said to him, “Please come close and kiss me, my son.”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>So he came close and kissed him; and when he smelled the smell of his garments, he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-755R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-755R\"></sup>blessed him and said,“See, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-755S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-755S\"></sup>the smell of my sonIs like the smell of a field <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-755T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-755T\"></sup>which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has blessed;",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Now may <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-756U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-756U\"></sup>God give you of the dew of heaven,And of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-756V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-756V\"></sup>fatness of the earth,And an abundance of grain and new wine;",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-757W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-757W\"></sup>May peoples serve you,And nations bow down to you;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-757X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-757X\"></sup>Be master of your brothers,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-757Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-757Y\"></sup>And may your mother’s sons bow down to you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-757Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-757Z\"></sup>Cursed be those who curse you,And blessed be those who bless you.”",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Now it came about, as soon as Isaac had finished blessing Jacob, and Jacob had hardly gone out from the presence of Isaac his father, that Esau his brother came in from his hunting.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Then he also made savory food, and brought it to his father; and he said to his father, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-759AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-759AA\"></sup>Let my father arise and eat of his son’s game, that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-759AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-759AB\"></sup>you may bless me.”",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Isaac his father said to him, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-760AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-760AC\"></sup>Who are you?” And he said, “I am your son, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-760AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-760AD\"></sup>your firstborn, Esau.”",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Then Isaac trembled violently, and said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-761AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-761AE\"></sup>Who was he then that hunted game and brought <i>it</i> to me, so that I ate of all <i>of it</i> before you came, and blessed him? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-761AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-761AF\"></sup>Yes, and he shall be blessed.”",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>When Esau heard the words of his father, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-762AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-762AG\"></sup>he cried out with an exceedingly great and bitter cry, and said to his father, “Bless me, <i>even</i> me also, O my father!”",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>And he said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-763AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-763AH\"></sup>Your brother came deceitfully and has taken away your blessing.”",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Then he said, “Is he not rightly named <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-764AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-764AI\"></sup>Jacob, for he has supplanted me these two times? He took away my birthright, and behold, now he has taken away my blessing.” And he said, “Have you not reserved a blessing for me?”",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>But Isaac replied to Esau, “Behold, I have made him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-765AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-765AJ\"></sup>your master, and all his relatives I have given to him as servants; and with grain and new wine I have sustained him. Now as for you then, what can I do, my son?”",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>Esau said to his father, “Do you have only one blessing, my father? Bless me, <i>even</i> me also, O my father.” So Esau lifted his voice and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-766AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-766AK\"></sup>wept.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-767AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-767AL\"></sup>Isaac his father answered and said to him,“Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-767AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-767AM\"></sup>away from the fertility of the earth shall be your dwelling,And away from the dew of heaven from above.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>“By your sword you shall live,And your brother <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-768AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-768AN\"></sup>you shall serve;But it shall come about <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-768AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-768AO\"></sup>when you become restless,That you will break his yoke from your neck.”",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>So Esau <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-769AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-769AP\"></sup>bore a grudge against Jacob because of the blessing with which his father had blessed him; and Esau said to himself, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-769AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-769AQ\"></sup>The days of mourning for my father are near; then I will kill my brother Jacob.”",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>Now when the words of her elder son Esau were reported to Rebekah, she sent and called her younger son Jacob, and said to him, “Behold your brother Esau is consoling himself concerning you <i>by planning</i> to kill you.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>Now therefore, my son, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-771AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-771AR\"></sup>obey my voice, and arise, flee to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-771AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-771AS\"></sup>Haran, to my brother <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-771AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-771AT\"></sup>Laban!",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>Stay with him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-772AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-772AU\"></sup>a few days, until your brother’s fury subsides,",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>until your brother’s anger against you subsides and he forgets <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-773AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-773AV\"></sup>what you did to him. Then I will send and get you from there. Why should I be bereaved of you both in one day?”",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>Rebekah said to Isaac, “I am tired of living because of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-774AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-774AW\"></sup>the daughters of Heth; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-774AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-774AX\"></sup>if Jacob takes a wife from the daughters of Heth, like these, from the daughters of the land, what good will my life be to me?”"
		},
		"28": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">28 </span>So Isaac called Jacob and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-775A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-775A\"></sup>blessed him and charged him, and said to him, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-775B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-775B\"></sup>You shall not take a wife from the daughters of Canaan.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Arise, go to Paddan-aram, to the house of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-776C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-776C\"></sup>Bethuel your mother’s father; and from there take to yourself a wife from the daughters of Laban your mother’s brother.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>May <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-777D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-777D\"></sup>God Almighty <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-777E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-777E\"></sup>bless you and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-777F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-777F\"></sup>make you fruitful and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-777G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-777G\"></sup>multiply you, that you may become a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-777H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-777H\"></sup>company of peoples.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>May He also give you the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-778I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-778I\"></sup>blessing of Abraham, to you and to your descendants with you, that you may <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-778J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-778J\"></sup>possess the land of your <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-778K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-778K\"></sup>sojournings, which God gave to Abraham.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-779L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-779L\"></sup>Isaac sent Jacob away, and he went to Paddan-aram to Laban, son of Bethuel the Aramean, the brother of Rebekah, the mother of Jacob and Esau.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Now Esau saw that Isaac had blessed Jacob and sent him away to Paddan-aram to take to himself a wife from there, <i>and that</i> when he blessed him he charged him, saying, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-780M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-780M\"></sup>You shall not take a wife from the daughters of Canaan,”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>and that Jacob had obeyed his father and his mother and had gone to Paddan-aram.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>So Esau saw that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-782N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-782N\"></sup>the daughters of Canaan displeased his father Isaac;",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>and Esau went to Ishmael, and married, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-783O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-783O\"></sup>besides the wives that he had, Mahalath the daughter of Ishmael, Abraham’s son, the sister of Nebaioth.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then Jacob departed from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-784P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-784P\"></sup>Beersheba and went toward <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-784Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-784Q\"></sup>Haran.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>He came to a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-785R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-785R\"></sup>certain place and spent the night there, because the sun had set; and he took one of the stones of the place and put it under his head, and lay down in that place.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-786S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-786S\"></sup>He had a dream, and behold, a ladder was set on the earth with its top reaching to heaven; and behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-786T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-786T\"></sup>the angels of God were ascending and descending on it.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-787U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-787U\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> stood above it and said, “I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-787V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-787V\"></sup>the God of your father Abraham and the God of Isaac; the land on which you lie, I will give it <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-787W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-787W\"></sup>to you and to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-787X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-787X\"></sup>your descendants.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Your descendants will also be like <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-788Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-788Y\"></sup>the dust of the earth, and you will spread out <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-788Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-788Z\"></sup>to the west and to the east and to the north and to the south; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-788AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-788AA\"></sup>in you and in your descendants shall all the families of the earth be blessed.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-789AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-789AB\"></sup>I am with you and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-789AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-789AC\"></sup>will keep you wherever you go, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-789AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-789AD\"></sup>will bring you back to this land; for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-789AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-789AE\"></sup>I will not leave you until I have done what I have promised you.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then Jacob <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-790AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-790AF\"></sup>awoke from his sleep and said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-790AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-790AG\"></sup>Surely the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is in this place, and I did not know it.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>He was afraid and said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-791AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-791AH\"></sup>How awesome is this place! This is none other than the house of God, and this is the gate of heaven.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>So Jacob rose early in the morning, and took <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-792AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-792AI\"></sup>the stone that he had put under his head and set it up as a pillar and poured oil on its top.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>He called the name of that place <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-793AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-793AJ\"></sup>Bethel; however, previously the name of the city had been <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-793AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-793AK\"></sup>Luz.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Then Jacob <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-794AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-794AL\"></sup>made a vow, saying, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-794AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-794AM\"></sup>If God will be with me and will keep me on this journey that I take, and will give me <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-794AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-794AN\"></sup>food to eat and garments to wear,",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-795AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-795AO\"></sup>I return to my father’s house in safety, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-795AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-795AP\"></sup>then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will be my God.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>This stone, which I have set up as a pillar, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-796AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-796AQ\"></sup>will be God’s house, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-796AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-796AR\"></sup>of all that You give me I will surely give a tenth to You.”"
		},
		"29": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">29 </span>Then Jacob went on his journey, and came to the land of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-797A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-797A\"></sup>the sons of the east.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He looked, and saw <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-798B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-798B\"></sup>a well in the field, and behold, three flocks of sheep were lying there beside it, for from that well they watered the flocks. Now the stone on the mouth of the well was large.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>When all the flocks were gathered there, they would then roll the stone from the mouth of the well and water the sheep, and put the stone back in its place on the mouth of the well.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Jacob said to them, “My brothers, where are you from?” And they said, “We are from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-800C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-800C\"></sup>Haran.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>He said to them, “Do you know Laban the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-801D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-801D\"></sup>son of Nahor?” And they said, “We know <i>him</i>.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And he said to them, “Is it well with him?” And they said, “It is well, and here is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-802E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-802E\"></sup>Rachel his daughter coming with the sheep.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>He said, “Behold, it is still high day; it is not time for the livestock to be gathered. Water the sheep, and go, pasture them.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>But they said, “We cannot, until all the flocks are gathered, and they roll the stone from the mouth of the well; then we water the sheep.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>While he was still speaking with them, Rachel came with her father’s sheep, for she was a shepherdess.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>When Jacob saw Rachel the daughter of Laban his mother’s brother, and the sheep of Laban his mother’s brother, Jacob went up and rolled the stone from the mouth of the well and watered the flock of Laban his mother’s brother.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then Jacob <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-807F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-807F\"></sup>kissed Rachel, and lifted his voice and wept.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Jacob told Rachel that he was a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-808G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-808G\"></sup>relative of her father and that he was Rebekah’s son, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-808H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-808H\"></sup>she ran and told her father.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>So when <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-809I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-809I\"></sup>Laban heard the news of Jacob his sister’s son, he ran to meet him, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-809J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-809J\"></sup>embraced him and kissed him and brought him to his house. Then he related to Laban all these things.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Laban said to him, “Surely you are <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-810K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-810K\"></sup>my bone and my flesh.” And he stayed with him a month.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then Laban said to Jacob, “Because you are my relative, should you therefore serve me for nothing? Tell me, what shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-811L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-811L\"></sup>your wages be?”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Now Laban had two daughters; the name of the older was Leah, and the name of the younger was Rachel.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And Leah’s eyes were weak, but Rachel was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-813M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-813M\"></sup>beautiful of form and face.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Now Jacob <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-814N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-814N\"></sup>loved Rachel, so he said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-814O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-814O\"></sup>I will serve you seven years for your younger daughter Rachel.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Laban said, “It is better that I give her to you than to give her to another man; stay with me.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>So Jacob served seven years for Rachel and they seemed to him but a few days <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-816P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-816P\"></sup>because of his love for her.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then Jacob said to Laban, “Give <i>me</i> my wife, for my time is completed, that I may <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-817Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-817Q\"></sup>go in to her.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Laban gathered all the men of the place and made a feast.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Now in the evening he took his daughter Leah, and brought her to him; and <i>Jacob</i> went in to her.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Laban also gave his maid Zilpah to his daughter Leah as a maid.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>So it came about in the morning that, behold, it was Leah! And he said to Laban, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-821R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-821R\"></sup>What is this you have done to me? Was it not for Rachel that I served with you? Why then have you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-821S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-821S\"></sup>deceived me?”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>But Laban said, “It is not the practice in our place to marry off the younger before the firstborn.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Complete the week of this one, and we will give you the other also for the service which <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-823T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-823T\"></sup>you shall serve with me for another seven years.”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Jacob did so and completed her week, and he gave him his daughter Rachel as his wife.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Laban also gave his maid Bilhah to his daughter Rachel as her maid.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>So <i>Jacob</i> went in to Rachel also, and indeed <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-826U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-826U\"></sup>he loved Rachel more than Leah, and he served with Laban for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-826V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-826V\"></sup>another seven years.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Now the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> saw that Leah was unloved, and He opened her womb, but Rachel was barren.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Leah conceived and bore a son and named him Reuben, for she said, “Because the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-828W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-828W\"></sup>seen my affliction; surely now my husband will love me.”",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Then she conceived again and bore a son and said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-829X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-829X\"></sup>Because the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has heard that I am unloved, He has therefore given me this <i>son</i> also.” So she named him Simeon.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>She conceived again and bore a son and said, “Now this time my husband will become attached to me, because I have borne him three sons.” Therefore he was named <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-830Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-830Y\"></sup>Levi.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>And she conceived again and bore a son and said, “This time I will praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.” Therefore she named him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-831Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-831Z\"></sup>Judah. Then she stopped bearing."
		},
		"30": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">30 </span>Now when Rachel saw that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-832A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-832A\"></sup>she bore Jacob no children, she became jealous of her sister; and she said to Jacob, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-832B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-832B\"></sup>Give me children, or else I die.”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Then Jacob’s anger burned against Rachel, and he said, “Am I in the place of God, who has <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-833C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-833C\"></sup>withheld from you the fruit of the womb?”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>She said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-834D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-834D\"></sup>Here is my maid Bilhah, go in to her that she may <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-834E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-834E\"></sup>bear on my knees, that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-834F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-834F\"></sup>through her I too may have children.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-835G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-835G\"></sup>she gave him her maid Bilhah as a wife, and Jacob went in to her.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Bilhah conceived and bore Jacob a son.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then Rachel said, “God has <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-837H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-837H\"></sup>vindicated me, and has indeed heard my voice and has given me a son.” Therefore she named him Dan.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Rachel’s maid Bilhah conceived again and bore Jacob a second son.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>So Rachel said, “With mighty wrestlings I have wrestled with my sister, <i>and</i> I have indeed prevailed.” And she named him Naphtali.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>When Leah saw that she had stopped bearing, she took her maid Zilpah and gave her to Jacob as a wife.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Leah’s maid Zilpah bore Jacob a son.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then Leah said, “How fortunate!” So she named him Gad.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Leah’s maid Zilpah bore Jacob a second son.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then Leah said, “Happy am I! For women <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-844I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-844I\"></sup>will call me happy.” So she named him Asher.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Now in the days of wheat harvest Reuben went and found <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-845J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-845J\"></sup>mandrakes in the field, and brought them to his mother Leah. Then Rachel said to Leah, “Please give me some of your son’s mandrakes.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>But she said to her, “Is it a small matter for you to take my husband? And would you take my son’s mandrakes also?” So Rachel said, “Therefore he may lie with you tonight in return for your son’s mandrakes.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>When Jacob came in from the field in the evening, then Leah went out to meet him and said, “You must come in to me, for I have surely hired you with my son’s mandrakes.” So he lay with her that night.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>God gave heed to Leah, and she conceived and bore Jacob a fifth son.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then Leah said, “God has given me my wages because I gave my maid to my husband.” So she named him Issachar.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Leah conceived again and bore a sixth son to Jacob.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Then Leah said, “God has endowed me with a good gift; now my husband will dwell with me, because I have borne him six sons.” So she named him Zebulun.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Afterward she bore a daughter and named her Dinah.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-853K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-853K\"></sup>God remembered Rachel, and God gave heed to her and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-853L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-853L\"></sup>opened her womb.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>So she conceived and bore a son and said, “God has <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-854M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-854M\"></sup>taken away my reproach.”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>She named him Joseph, saying, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-855N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-855N\"></sup>May the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> give me another son.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Now it came about when Rachel had borne Joseph, that Jacob said to Laban, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-856O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-856O\"></sup>Send me away, that I may go to my own place and to my own country.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Give <i>me</i> my wives and my children <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-857P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-857P\"></sup>for whom I have served you, and let me depart; for you yourself know my service which I have rendered you.”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>But Laban said to him, “If now it pleases you, <i>stay with me</i>; I have divined <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-858Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-858Q\"></sup>that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has blessed me on your account.”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>He continued, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-859R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-859R\"></sup>Name me your wages, and I will give it.”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>But he said to him, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-860S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-860S\"></sup>You yourself know how I have served you and how your cattle have fared with me.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>For you had little before I came and it has increased to a multitude, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has blessed you wherever I turned. But now, when shall I provide for my own household also?”",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>So he said, “What shall I give you?” And Jacob said, “You shall not give me anything. If you will do this <i>one</i> thing for me, I will again pasture <i>and</i> keep your flock:",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>let me pass through your entire flock today, removing from there every <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-863T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-863T\"></sup>speckled and spotted sheep and every black one among the lambs and the spotted and speckled among the goats; and <i>such</i> shall be my wages.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>So my honesty will answer for me later, when you come concerning my wages. Every one that is not speckled and spotted among the goats and black among the lambs, <i>if found</i> with me, will be considered stolen.”",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Laban said, “Good, let it be according to your word.”",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>So he removed on that day the striped and spotted male goats and all the speckled and spotted female goats, every one with white in it, and all the black ones among the sheep, and gave them into the care of his sons.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>And he put <i>a distance of</i> three days’ journey between himself and Jacob, and Jacob fed the rest of Laban’s flocks.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Then Jacob took fresh rods of poplar and almond and plane trees, and peeled white stripes in them, exposing the white which <i>was</i> in the rods.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>He set the rods which he had peeled in front of the flocks in the gutters, <i>even</i> in the watering troughs, where the flocks came to drink; and they mated when they came to drink.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>So the flocks mated by the rods, and the flocks brought forth striped, speckled, and spotted.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>Jacob separated the lambs, and made the flocks face toward the striped and all the black in the flock of Laban; and he put his own herds apart, and did not put them with Laban’s flock.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>Moreover, whenever the stronger of the flock were mating, Jacob would place the rods in the sight of the flock in the gutters, so that they might mate by the rods;",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>but when the flock was feeble, he did not put <i>them</i> in; so the feebler were Laban’s and the stronger Jacob’s.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-874U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-874U\"></sup>the man became exceedingly prosperous, and had large flocks and female and male servants and camels and donkeys."
		},
		"31": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">31 </span>Now Jacob heard the words of Laban’s sons, saying, “Jacob has taken away all that was our father’s, and from what belonged to our father he has made all this wealth.”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Jacob saw the attitude of Laban, and behold, it was not <i>friendly</i> toward him as formerly.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Jacob, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-877A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-877A\"></sup>Return to the land of your fathers and to your relatives, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-877B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-877B\"></sup>I will be with you.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>So Jacob sent and called Rachel and Leah to his flock in the field,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>and said to them, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-879C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-879C\"></sup>I see your father’s attitude, that it is not <i>friendly</i> toward me as formerly, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-879D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-879D\"></sup>the God of my father has been with me.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-880E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-880E\"></sup>You know that I have served your father with all my strength.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Yet your father has <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-881F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-881F\"></sup>cheated me and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-881G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-881G\"></sup>changed my wages ten times; however, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-881H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-881H\"></sup>God did not allow him to hurt me.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>If <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-882I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-882I\"></sup>he spoke thus, ‘The speckled shall be your wages,’ then all the flock brought forth speckled; and if he spoke thus, ‘The striped shall be your wages,’ then all the flock brought forth striped.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Thus God has <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-883J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-883J\"></sup>taken away your father’s livestock and given <i>them</i> to me.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And it came about at the time when the flock were mating that I lifted up my eyes and saw in a dream, and behold, the male goats which were mating <i>were</i> striped, speckled, and mottled.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-885K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-885K\"></sup>the angel of God said to me in the dream, ‘Jacob,’ and I said, ‘Here I am.’",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>He said, ‘Lift up now your eyes and see <i>that</i> all the male goats which are mating are striped, speckled, and mottled; for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-886L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-886L\"></sup>I have seen all that Laban has been doing to you.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>I am <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-887M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-887M\"></sup>the God <i>of</i> Bethel, where you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-887N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-887N\"></sup>anointed a pillar, where you made a vow to Me; now arise, leave this land, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-887O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-887O\"></sup>return to the land of your birth.’”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Rachel and Leah said to him, “Do we still have any portion or inheritance in our father’s house?",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Are we not reckoned by him as foreigners? For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-889P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-889P\"></sup>he has sold us, and has also entirely consumed our purchase price.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Surely all the wealth which God has taken away from our father belongs to us and our children; now then, do whatever God has said to you.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then Jacob arose and put his children and his wives upon camels;",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>and he drove away all his livestock and all his property which he had gathered, his acquired livestock which he had gathered in Paddan-aram, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-892Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-892Q\"></sup>to go to the land of Canaan to his father Isaac.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>When Laban had gone to shear his flock, then Rachel stole the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-893R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-893R\"></sup>household idols that were her father’s.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And Jacob deceived Laban the Aramean by not telling him that he was fleeing.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>So he fled with all that he had; and he arose and crossed the <i>Euphrates</i> River, and set his face toward the hill country of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-895S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-895S\"></sup>Gilead.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>When it was told Laban on the third day that Jacob had fled,",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>then he took his kinsmen with him and pursued him <i>a distance of</i> seven days’ journey, and he overtook him in the hill country of Gilead.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-898T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-898T\"></sup>God came to Laban the Aramean in a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-898U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-898U\"></sup>dream of the night and said to him, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-898V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-898V\"></sup>Be careful that you do not speak to Jacob either good or bad.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Laban caught up with Jacob. Now Jacob had pitched his tent in the hill country, and Laban with his kinsmen camped in the hill country of Gilead.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Then Laban said to Jacob, “What have you done by deceiving me and carrying away my daughters like captives of the sword?",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Why did you flee secretly and deceive me, and did not tell me so that I might have sent you away with joy and with songs, with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-901W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-901W\"></sup>timbrel and with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-901X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-901X\"></sup>lyre;",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>and did not allow me <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-902Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-902Y\"></sup>to kiss my sons and my daughters? Now you have done foolishly.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>It is in my power to do you harm, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-903Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-903Z\"></sup>the God of your father spoke to me last night, saying, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-903AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-903AA\"></sup>Be careful not to speak either good or bad to Jacob.’",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Now you have indeed gone away because you longed greatly for your father’s house; <i>but</i> why did you steal <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-904AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-904AB\"></sup>my gods?”",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Then Jacob replied to Laban, “Because I was afraid, for I thought that you would take your daughters from me by force.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-906AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-906AC\"></sup>The one with whom you find your gods shall not live; in the presence of our kinsmen point out what is yours among my belongings and take <i>it</i> for yourself.” For Jacob did not know that Rachel had stolen them.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>So Laban went into Jacob’s tent and into Leah’s tent and into the tent of the two maids, but he did not find <i>them</i>. Then he went out of Leah’s tent and entered Rachel’s tent.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Now Rachel had taken the household idols and put them in the camel’s saddle, and she sat on them. And Laban felt through all the tent but did not find <i>them</i>.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>She said to her father, “Let not my lord be angry that I cannot <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-909AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-909AD\"></sup>rise before you, for the manner of women is upon me.” So he searched but did not find the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-909AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-909AE\"></sup>household idols.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Then Jacob became angry and contended with Laban; and Jacob said to Laban, “What is my transgression? What is my sin that you have hotly pursued me?",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Though you have felt through all my goods, what have you found of all your household goods? Set <i>it</i> here before my kinsmen and your kinsmen, that they may decide between us two.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>These twenty years I <i>have been</i> with you; your ewes and your female goats have not miscarried, nor have I eaten the rams of your flocks.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>That which was torn <i>of beasts</i> I did not bring to you; I bore the loss of it myself. You required it of my hand <i>whether</i> stolen by day or stolen by night.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup><i>Thus</i> I was: by day the heat consumed me and the frost by night, and my sleep fled from my eyes.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>These twenty years I have been in your house; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-915AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-915AF\"></sup>I served you fourteen years for your two daughters and six years for your flock, and you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-915AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-915AG\"></sup>changed my wages ten times.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>If <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-916AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-916AH\"></sup>the God of my father, the God of Abraham, and the fear of Isaac, had not been for me, surely now you would have sent me away empty-handed. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-916AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-916AI\"></sup>God has seen my affliction and the toil of my hands, so He <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-916AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-916AJ\"></sup>rendered judgment last night.”",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>Then Laban replied to Jacob, “The daughters are my daughters, and the children are my children, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-917AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-917AK\"></sup>the flocks are my flocks, and all that you see is mine. But what can I do this day to these my daughters or to their children whom they have borne?",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>So now come, let us <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-918AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-918AL\"></sup>make a covenant, you and I, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-918AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-918AM\"></sup>let it be a witness between you and me.”",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>Then Jacob took <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-919AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-919AN\"></sup>a stone and set it up <i>as</i> a pillar.",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>Jacob said to his kinsmen, “Gather stones.” So they took stones and made a heap, and they ate there by the heap.",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>Now Laban <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-921AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-921AO\"></sup>called it Jegar-sahadutha, but Jacob called it Galeed.",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>Laban said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-922AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-922AP\"></sup>This heap is a witness between you and me this day.” Therefore it was named Galeed,",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-923AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-923AQ\"></sup>Mizpah, for he said, “May the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> watch between you and me when we are absent one from the other.",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>If you mistreat my daughters, or if you take wives besides my daughters, <i>although</i> no man is with us, see, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-924AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-924AR\"></sup>God is witness between you and me.”",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>Laban said to Jacob, “Behold this heap and behold the pillar which I have set between you and me.",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>This heap is a witness, and the pillar is a witness, that I will not pass by this heap to you for harm, and you will not pass by this heap and this pillar to me, for harm.",
			"53": "<sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-927AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-927AS\"></sup>The God of Abraham and the God of Nahor, the God of their father, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-927AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-927AT\"></sup>judge between us.” So Jacob swore by <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-927AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-927AU\"></sup>the fear of his father Isaac.",
			"54": "<sup class=\"versenum\">54 </sup>Then Jacob <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-928AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-928AV\"></sup>offered a sacrifice on the mountain, and called his kinsmen to the meal; and they ate the meal and spent the night on the mountain.",
			"55": "<sup class=\"versenum\">55 </sup>Early in the morning Laban arose, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-929AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-929AW\"></sup>kissed his sons and his daughters and blessed them. Then Laban departed and returned to his place."
		},
		"32": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">32 </span>Now as Jacob went on his way, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-930A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-930A\"></sup>the angels of God met him.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Jacob said when he saw them, “This is God’s camp.” So he named that place <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-931B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-931B\"></sup>Mahanaim.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then Jacob <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-932C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-932C\"></sup>sent messengers before him to his brother Esau in the land of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-932D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-932D\"></sup>Seir, the country of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-932E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-932E\"></sup>Edom.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>He also commanded them saying, “Thus you shall say to my lord Esau: ‘Thus says your servant Jacob, “I have sojourned with Laban, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-933F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-933F\"></sup>stayed until now;",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-934G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-934G\"></sup>I have oxen and donkeys <i>and</i> flocks and male and female servants; and I have sent to tell my lord, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-934H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-934H\"></sup>that I may find favor in your sight.”’”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The messengers returned to Jacob, saying, “We came to your brother Esau, and furthermore <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-935I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-935I\"></sup>he is coming to meet you, and four hundred men are with him.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then Jacob was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-936J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-936J\"></sup>greatly afraid and distressed; and he divided the people who were with him, and the flocks and the herds and the camels, into two companies;",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>for he said, “If Esau comes to the one company and attacks it, then the company which is left will escape.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Jacob said, “O <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-938K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-938K\"></sup>God of my father Abraham and God of my father Isaac, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, who said to me, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-938L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-938L\"></sup>Return to your country and to your relatives, and I will prosper you,’",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>I am unworthy <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-939M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-939M\"></sup>of all the lovingkindness and of all the faithfulness which You have shown to Your servant; for with my staff <i>only</i> I crossed this Jordan, and now I have become two companies.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-940N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-940N\"></sup>Deliver me, I pray, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-940O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-940O\"></sup>from the hand of my brother, from the hand of Esau; for I fear him, that he will come and attack me <i>and</i> the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-940P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-940P\"></sup>mothers with the children.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>For You said, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-941Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-941Q\"></sup>I will surely prosper you and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-941R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-941R\"></sup>make your descendants as the sand of the sea, which is too great to be numbered.’”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>So he spent the night there. Then he selected from what he had with him a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-942S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-942S\"></sup>present for his brother Esau:",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>two hundred female goats and twenty male goats, two hundred ewes and twenty rams,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>thirty milking camels and their colts, forty cows and ten bulls, twenty female donkeys and ten male donkeys.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>He delivered <i>them</i> into the hand of his servants, every drove by itself, and said to his servants, “Pass on before me, and put a space between droves.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>He commanded the one in front, saying, “When my brother Esau meets you and asks you, saying, ‘To whom do you belong, and where are you going, and to whom do these <i>animals</i> in front of you belong?’",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>then you shall say, ‘<i>These</i> belong to your servant Jacob; it is a present sent to my lord Esau. And behold, he also is behind us.’”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Then he commanded also the second and the third, and all those who followed the droves, saying, “After this manner you shall speak to Esau when you find him;",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>and you shall say, ‘Behold, your servant Jacob also is behind us.’” For he said, “I will appease him with the present that goes before me. Then afterward I will see his face; perhaps he will accept me.”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>So the present passed on before him, while he himself spent that night in the camp.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Now he arose that same night and took his two wives and his two maids and his eleven children, and crossed the ford of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-951T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-951T\"></sup>Jabbok.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>He took them and sent them across the stream. And he sent across whatever he had.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Then Jacob was left alone, and a man <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-953U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-953U\"></sup>wrestled with him until daybreak.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>When he saw that he had not prevailed against him, he touched the socket of his thigh; so the socket of Jacob’s thigh was dislocated while he wrestled with him.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Then he said, “Let me go, for the dawn is breaking.” But he said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-955V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-955V\"></sup>I will not let you go unless you bless me.”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>So he said to him, “What is your name?” And he said, “Jacob.”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-957W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-957W\"></sup>He said, “Your name shall no longer be Jacob, but Israel; for you have striven with God and with men and have prevailed.”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-958X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-958X\"></sup>Jacob asked him and said, “Please tell me your name.” But he said, “Why is it that you ask my name?” And he blessed him there.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>So Jacob named the place Peniel, for <i>he said</i>, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-959Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-959Y\"></sup>I have seen God face to face, yet my life has been preserved.”",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Now the sun rose upon him just as he crossed over <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-960Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-960Z\"></sup>Penuel, and he was limping on his thigh.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Therefore, to this day the sons of Israel do not eat the sinew of the hip which is on the socket of the thigh, because he touched the socket of Jacob’s thigh in the sinew of the hip."
		},
		"33": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">33 </span>Then Jacob lifted his eyes and looked, and behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-962A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-962A\"></sup>Esau was coming, and four hundred men with him. So he divided the children among Leah and Rachel and the two maids.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He put the maids and their children in front, and Leah and her children next, and Rachel and Joseph last.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>But he himself passed on ahead of them and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-964B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-964B\"></sup>bowed down to the ground seven times, until he came near to his brother.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then Esau ran to meet him and embraced him, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-965C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-965C\"></sup>fell on his neck and kissed him, and they wept.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>He lifted his eyes and saw the women and the children, and said, “Who are these with you?” So he said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-966D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-966D\"></sup>The children whom God has graciously given your servant.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then the maids came near with their children, and they bowed down.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Leah likewise came near with her children, and they bowed down; and afterward Joseph came near with Rachel, and they bowed down.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And he said, “What do you mean by <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-969E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-969E\"></sup>all this company which I have met?” And he said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-969F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-969F\"></sup>To find favor in the sight of my lord.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>But Esau said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-970G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-970G\"></sup>I have plenty, my brother; let what you have be your own.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Jacob said, “No, please, if now I have found favor in your sight, then take my present from my hand, for I see your face as one sees the face of God, and you have received me favorably.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Please take my <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-972H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-972H\"></sup>gift which has been brought to you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-972I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-972I\"></sup>because God has dealt graciously with me and because I have plenty.” Thus he urged him and he took <i>it</i>.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then Esau said, “Let us take our journey and go, and I will go before you.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>But he said to him, “My lord knows that the children are frail and that the flocks and herds which are nursing are a care to me. And if they are driven hard one day, all the flocks will die.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Please let my lord pass on before his servant, and I will proceed at my leisure, according to the pace of the cattle that are before me and according to the pace of the children, until I come to my lord at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-975J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-975J\"></sup>Seir.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Esau said, “Please let me leave with you some of the people who are with me.” But he said, “What need is there? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-976K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-976K\"></sup>Let me find favor in the sight of my lord.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>So Esau returned that day on his way to Seir.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Jacob journeyed to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-978L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-978L\"></sup>Succoth, and built for himself a house and made booths for his livestock; therefore the place is named Succoth.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Now Jacob came safely to the city of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-979M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-979M\"></sup>Shechem, which is in the land of Canaan, when he came from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-979N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-979N\"></sup>Paddan-aram, and camped before the city.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-980O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-980O\"></sup>He bought the piece of land where he had pitched his tent from the hand of the sons of Hamor, Shechem’s father, for one hundred pieces of money.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Then he erected there an altar and called it El-Elohe-Israel."
		},
		"34": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">34 </span>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-982A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-982A\"></sup>Dinah the daughter of Leah, whom she had borne to Jacob, went out to visit the daughters of the land.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>When Shechem the son of Hamor <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-983B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-983B\"></sup>the Hivite, the prince of the land, saw her, he took her and lay with her by force.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>He was deeply attracted to Dinah the daughter of Jacob, and he loved the girl and spoke tenderly to her.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>So Shechem <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-985C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-985C\"></sup>spoke to his father Hamor, saying, “Get me this young girl for a wife.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Now Jacob heard that he had defiled Dinah his daughter; but his sons were with his livestock in the field, so Jacob kept silent until they came in.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then Hamor the father of Shechem went out to Jacob to speak with him.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Now the sons of Jacob came in from the field when they heard <i>it</i>; and the men were grieved, and they were very angry because he had done a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-988D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-988D\"></sup>disgraceful thing in Israel by lying with Jacob’s daughter, for such a thing ought not to be done.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>But Hamor spoke with them, saying, “The soul of my son Shechem longs for your daughter; please give her to him in marriage.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Intermarry with us; give your daughters to us and take our daughters for yourselves.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Thus you shall live with us, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-991E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-991E\"></sup>the land shall be <i>open</i> before you; live and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-991F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-991F\"></sup>trade in it and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-991G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-991G\"></sup>acquire property in it.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Shechem also said to her father and to her brothers, “If I find favor in your sight, then I will give whatever you say to me.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Ask me ever so much bridal payment and gift, and I will give according as you say to me; but give me the girl in marriage.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>But Jacob’s sons answered Shechem and his father Hamor with deceit, because he had defiled Dinah their sister.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>They said to them, “We cannot do this thing, to give our sister to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-995H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-995H\"></sup>one who is uncircumcised, for that would be a disgrace to us.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Only on this <i>condition</i> will we consent to you: if you will become like us, in that every male of you be circumcised,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>then we will give our daughters to you, and we will take your daughters for ourselves, and we will live with you and become one people.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>But if you will not listen to us to be circumcised, then we will take our daughter and go.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Now their words seemed reasonable to Hamor and Shechem, Hamor’s son.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>The young man did not delay to do the thing, because he was delighted with Jacob’s daughter. Now he was more respected than all the household of his father.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>So Hamor and his son Shechem came to the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1001I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1001I\"></sup>gate of their city and spoke to the men of their city, saying,",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>“These men are friendly with us; therefore let them live in the land and trade in it, for behold, the land is large enough for them. Let us take their daughters in marriage, and give our daughters to them.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Only on this <i>condition</i> will the men consent to us to live with us, to become one people: that every male among us be circumcised as they are circumcised.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Will not their livestock and their property and all their animals be ours? Only let us consent to them, and they will live with us.”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1005J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1005J\"></sup>All who went out of the gate of his city listened to Hamor and to his son Shechem, and every male was circumcised, all who went out of the gate of his city.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Now it came about on the third day, when they were in pain, that two of Jacob’s sons, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1006K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1006K\"></sup>Simeon and Levi, Dinah’s brothers, each took his sword and came upon the city unawares, and killed every male.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>They killed Hamor and his son Shechem with the edge of the sword, and took Dinah from Shechem’s house, and went forth.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Jacob’s sons came upon the slain and looted the city, because they had defiled their sister.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>They took their flocks and their herds and their donkeys, and that which was in the city and that which was in the field;",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>and they captured and looted all their wealth and all their little ones and their wives, even all that <i>was</i> in the houses.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Then Jacob said to Simeon and Levi, “You have <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1011L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1011L\"></sup>brought trouble on me by <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1011M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1011M\"></sup>making me odious among the inhabitants of the land, among <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1011N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1011N\"></sup>the Canaanites and the Perizzites; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1011O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1011O\"></sup>my men being few in number, they will gather together against me and attack me and I will be destroyed, I and my household.”",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>But they said, “Should he treat our sister as a harlot?”"
		},
		"35": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">35 </span>Then God said to Jacob, “Arise, go up to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1013A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1013A\"></sup>Bethel and live there, and make an altar there to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1013B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1013B\"></sup>God, who appeared to you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1013C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1013C\"></sup>when you fled from your brother Esau.”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>So Jacob said to his <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1014D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1014D\"></sup>household and to all who were with him, “Put away <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1014E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1014E\"></sup>the foreign gods which are among you, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1014F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1014F\"></sup>purify yourselves and change your garments;",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>and let us arise and go up to Bethel, and I will make <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1015G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1015G\"></sup>an altar there to God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1015H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1015H\"></sup>who answered me in the day of my distress and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1015I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1015I\"></sup>has been with me wherever I have gone.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>So they gave to Jacob all the foreign gods which they had and the rings which were in their ears, and Jacob hid them under the oak which was near Shechem.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>As they journeyed, there was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1017J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1017J\"></sup>a great terror upon the cities which were around them, and they did not pursue the sons of Jacob.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So Jacob came to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1018K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1018K\"></sup>Luz (that is, Bethel), which is in the land of Canaan, he and all the people who were with him.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1019L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1019L\"></sup>He built an altar there, and called the place El-bethel, because there God had revealed Himself to him when he fled from his brother.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1020M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1020M\"></sup>Deborah, Rebekah’s nurse, died, and she was buried below Bethel under the oak; it was named Allon-bacuth.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then God appeared to Jacob again when he came from Paddan-aram, and He <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1021N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1021N\"></sup>blessed him.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1022O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1022O\"></sup>God said to him,“Your name is Jacob;You shall no longer be called Jacob,But Israel shall be your name.”Thus He called him Israel.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>God also said to him,“I am <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1023P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1023P\"></sup>God Almighty;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1023Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1023Q\"></sup>Be fruitful and multiply;A nation and a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1023R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1023R\"></sup>company of nations shall come from you,And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1023S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1023S\"></sup>kings shall come forth from you.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1024T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1024T\"></sup>The land which I gave to Abraham and Isaac,I will give it to you,And I will give the land to your descendants after you.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1025U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1025U\"></sup>God went up from him in the place where He had spoken with him.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Jacob set up <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1026V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1026V\"></sup>a pillar in the place where He had spoken with him, a pillar of stone, and he poured out a drink offering on it; he also poured oil on it.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>So Jacob named the place where God had spoken with him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1027W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1027W\"></sup>Bethel.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then they journeyed from Bethel; and when there was still some distance to go to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1028X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1028X\"></sup>Ephrath, Rachel began to give birth and she suffered severe labor.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>When she was in severe labor the midwife said to her, “Do not fear, for now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1029Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1029Y\"></sup>you have another son.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>It came about as her soul was departing (for she died), that she named him Ben-oni; but his father called him Benjamin.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1031Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1031Z\"></sup>Rachel died and was buried on the way to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1031AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1031AA\"></sup>Ephrath (that is, Bethlehem).",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Jacob set up a pillar over her grave; that is the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1032AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1032AB\"></sup>pillar of Rachel’s grave to this day.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then Israel journeyed on and pitched his tent beyond the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1033AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1033AC\"></sup>tower of Eder.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>It came about while Israel was dwelling in that land, that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1034AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1034AD\"></sup>Reuben went and lay with Bilhah his father’s concubine, and Israel heard <i>of it</i>.Now there were twelve sons of Jacob—",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1035AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1035AE\"></sup>the sons of Leah: Reuben, Jacob’s firstborn, then Simeon and Levi and Judah and Issachar and Zebulun;",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1036AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1036AF\"></sup>the sons of Rachel: Joseph and Benjamin;",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1037AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1037AG\"></sup>the sons of Bilhah, Rachel’s maid: Dan and Naphtali;",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1038AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1038AH\"></sup>the sons of Zilpah, Leah’s maid: Gad and Asher. These are the sons of Jacob who were born to him in Paddan-aram.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Jacob came to his father Isaac at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1039AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1039AI\"></sup>Mamre of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1039AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1039AJ\"></sup>Kiriath-arba (that is, Hebron), where Abraham and Isaac had sojourned.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Now the days of Isaac were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1040AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1040AK\"></sup>one hundred and eighty years.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Isaac breathed his last and died and was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1041AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1041AL\"></sup>gathered to his people, an <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1041AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1041AM\"></sup>old man of ripe age; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1041AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1041AN\"></sup>his sons Esau and Jacob buried him."
		},
		"36": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">36 </span>Now these are <i>the records of</i> the generations of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1042A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1042A\"></sup>Esau (that is, Edom).",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Esau <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1043B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1043B\"></sup>took his wives from the daughters of Canaan: Adah the daughter of Elon the Hittite, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1043C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1043C\"></sup>Oholibamah the daughter of Anah and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1043D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1043D\"></sup>granddaughter of Zibeon the Hivite;",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>also Basemath, Ishmael’s daughter, the sister of Nebaioth.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Adah bore <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1045E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1045E\"></sup>Eliphaz to Esau, and Basemath bore Reuel,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>and Oholibamah bore Jeush and Jalam and Korah. These are the sons of Esau who were born to him in the land of Canaan.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1047F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1047F\"></sup>Then Esau took his wives and his sons and his daughters and all his household, and his livestock and all his cattle and all his goods which he had acquired in the land of Canaan, and went to <i>another</i> land away from his brother Jacob.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1048G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1048G\"></sup>For their property had become too great for them to live together, and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1048H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1048H\"></sup>land where they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1048I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1048I\"></sup>sojourned could not sustain them because of their livestock.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>So Esau lived in the hill country of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1049J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1049J\"></sup>Seir; Esau is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1049K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1049K\"></sup>Edom.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>These then are <i>the records of</i> the generations of Esau the father of the Edomites in the hill country of Seir.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>These are the names of Esau’s sons: Eliphaz the son of Esau’s wife Adah, Reuel the son of Esau’s wife Basemath.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The sons of Eliphaz were Teman, Omar, Zepho and Gatam and Kenaz.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Timna was a concubine of Esau’s son Eliphaz and she bore <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1053L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1053L\"></sup>Amalek to Eliphaz. These are the sons of Esau’s wife Adah.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>These are the sons of Reuel: Nahath and Zerah, Shammah and Mizzah. These were the sons of Esau’s wife Basemath.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>These were the sons of Esau’s wife Oholibamah, the daughter of Anah and the granddaughter of Zibeon: she bore to Esau, Jeush and Jalam and Korah.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>These are the chiefs of the sons of Esau. The sons of Eliphaz, the firstborn of Esau, are chief Teman, chief Omar, chief Zepho, chief Kenaz,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>chief Korah, chief Gatam, chief Amalek. These are the chiefs descended from Eliphaz in the land of Edom; these are the sons of Adah.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>These are the sons of Reuel, Esau’s son: chief Nahath, chief Zerah, chief Shammah, chief Mizzah. These are the chiefs descended from Reuel in the land of Edom; these are the sons of Esau’s wife Basemath.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>These are the sons of Esau’s wife Oholibamah: chief Jeush, chief Jalam, chief Korah. These are the chiefs descended from Esau’s wife Oholibamah, the daughter of Anah.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>These are the sons of Esau (that is, Edom), and these are their chiefs.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>These are the sons of Seir <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1061M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1061M\"></sup>the Horite, the inhabitants of the land: Lotan and Shobal and Zibeon and Anah,",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>and Dishon and Ezer and Dishan. These are the chiefs descended from the Horites, the sons of Seir in the land of Edom.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>The sons of Lotan were Hori and Hemam; and Lotan’s sister was Timna.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>These are the sons of Shobal: Alvan and Manahath and Ebal, Shepho and Onam.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>These are the sons of Zibeon: Aiah and Anah—he is the Anah who found the hot springs in the wilderness when he was pasturing the donkeys of his father Zibeon.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>These are the children of Anah: Dishon, and Oholibamah, the daughter of Anah.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>These are the sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1067N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1067N\"></sup>Dishon: Hemdan and Eshban and Ithran and Cheran.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>These are the sons of Ezer: Bilhan and Zaavan and Akan.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>These are the sons of Dishan: Uz and Aran.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>These are the chiefs descended from the Horites: chief Lotan, chief Shobal, chief Zibeon, chief Anah,",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>chief Dishon, chief Ezer, chief Dishan. These are the chiefs descended from the Horites, according to their <i>various</i> chiefs in the land of Seir.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Now these are the kings who reigned in the land of Edom before any <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1072O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1072O\"></sup>king reigned over the sons of Israel.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1073P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1073P\"></sup>Bela the son of Beor reigned in Edom, and the name of his city was Dinhabah.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Then Bela died, and Jobab the son of Zerah of Bozrah became king in his place.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Then Jobab died, and Husham of the land of the Temanites became king in his place.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Then Husham died, and Hadad the son of Bedad, who defeated Midian in the field of Moab, became king in his place; and the name of his city was Avith.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Then Hadad died, and Samlah of Masrekah became king in his place.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Then Samlah died, and Shaul of Rehoboth on the <i>Euphrates</i> River became king in his place.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>Then Shaul died, and Baal-hanan the son of Achbor became king in his place.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>Then Baal-hanan the son of Achbor died, and Hadar became king in his place; and the name of his city was Pau; and his wife’s name was Mehetabel, the daughter of Matred, daughter of Mezahab.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>Now these are the names of the chiefs descended from Esau, according to their families <i>and</i> their localities, by their names: chief Timna, chief Alvah, chief Jetheth,",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>chief Oholibamah, chief Elah, chief Pinon,",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>chief Kenaz, chief Teman, chief Mibzar,",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>chief Magdiel, chief Iram. These are the chiefs of Edom (that is, Esau, the father of the Edomites), according to their habitations in the land of their possession."
		},
		"37": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">37 </span>Now Jacob lived in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1085A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1085A\"></sup>the land where his father had sojourned, in the land of Canaan.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>These are <i>the records of</i> the generations of Jacob.Joseph, when <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1086B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1086B\"></sup>seventeen years of age, was pasturing the flock with his brothers while he was <i>still</i> a youth, along with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1086C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1086C\"></sup>the sons of Bilhah and the sons of Zilpah, his father’s wives. And Joseph brought back a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1086D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1086D\"></sup>bad report about them to their father.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Now Israel loved Joseph more than all his sons, because he was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1087E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1087E\"></sup>the son of his old age; and he made him a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1087F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1087F\"></sup>varicolored tunic.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>His brothers saw that their father loved him more than all his brothers; and <i>so</i> they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1088G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1088G\"></sup>hated him and could not speak to him on friendly terms.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then Joseph <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1089H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1089H\"></sup>had a dream, and when he told it to his brothers, they hated him even more.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>He said to them, “Please listen to this dream which I have had;",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>for behold, we were binding sheaves in the field, and lo, my sheaf rose up and also stood erect; and behold, your sheaves gathered around and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1091I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1091I\"></sup>bowed down to my sheaf.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then his brothers said to him, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1092J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1092J\"></sup>Are you actually going to reign over us? Or are you really going to rule over us?” So they hated him even more for his dreams and for his words.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Now he had still another dream, and related it to his brothers, and said, “Lo, I have had still another dream; and behold, the sun and the moon and eleven stars were bowing down to me.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>He related <i>it</i> to his father and to his brothers; and his father rebuked him and said to him, “What is this dream that you have had? Shall I and your mother and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1094K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1094K\"></sup>your brothers actually come to bow ourselves down before you to the ground?”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1095L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1095L\"></sup>His brothers were jealous of him, but his father <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1095M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1095M\"></sup>kept the saying <i>in mind</i>.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then his brothers went to pasture their father’s flock in Shechem.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Israel said to Joseph, “Are not your brothers pasturing <i>the flock</i> in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1097N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1097N\"></sup>Shechem? Come, and I will send you to them.” And he said to him, “I will go.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then he said to him, “Go now and see about the welfare of your brothers and the welfare of the flock, and bring word back to me.” So he sent him from the valley of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1098O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1098O\"></sup>Hebron, and he came to Shechem.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>A man found him, and behold, he was wandering in the field; and the man asked him, “What are you looking for?”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>He said, “I am looking for my brothers; please tell me where they are pasturing <i>the flock</i>.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then the man said, “They have moved from here; for I heard <i>them</i> say, ‘Let us go to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1101P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1101P\"></sup>Dothan.’” So Joseph went after his brothers and found them at Dothan.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>When they saw him from a distance and before he came close to them, they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1102Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1102Q\"></sup>plotted against him to put him to death.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>They said to one another, “Here comes this dreamer!",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Now then, come and let us kill him and throw him into one of the pits; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1104R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1104R\"></sup>we will say, ‘A wild beast devoured him.’ Then let us see what will become of his dreams!”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1105S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1105S\"></sup>Reuben heard <i>this</i> and rescued him out of their hands and said, “Let us not take his life.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Reuben further said to them, “Shed no blood. Throw him into this pit that is in the wilderness, but do not lay hands on him”—that he might rescue him out of their hands, to restore him to his father.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>So it came about, when Joseph reached his brothers, that they stripped Joseph of his tunic, the varicolored tunic that was on him;",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>and they took him and threw him into the pit. Now the pit was empty, without any water in it.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Then they sat down to eat a meal. And as they raised their eyes and looked, behold, a caravan of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1109T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1109T\"></sup>Ishmaelites was coming from Gilead, with their camels bearing <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1109U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1109U\"></sup>aromatic gum and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1109V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1109V\"></sup>balm and myrrh, on their way to bring <i>them</i> down to Egypt.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Judah said to his brothers, “What profit is it for us to kill our brother and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1110W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1110W\"></sup>cover up his blood?",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1111X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1111X\"></sup>Come and let us sell him to the Ishmaelites and not lay our hands on him, for he is our brother, our <i>own</i> flesh.” And his brothers listened <i>to him</i>.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Then some <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1112Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1112Y\"></sup>Midianite traders passed by, so they pulled <i>him</i> up and lifted Joseph out of the pit, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1112Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1112Z\"></sup>sold him to the Ishmaelites for twenty <i>shekels</i> of silver. Thus <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1112AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1112AA\"></sup>they brought Joseph into Egypt.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Now Reuben returned to the pit, and behold, Joseph was not in the pit; so he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1113AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1113AB\"></sup>tore his garments.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>He returned to his brothers and said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1114AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1114AC\"></sup>The boy is not <i>there</i>; as for me, where am I to go?”",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1115AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1115AD\"></sup>they took Joseph’s tunic, and slaughtered a male goat and dipped the tunic in the blood;",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>and they sent the varicolored tunic and brought it to their father and said, “We found this; please examine <i>it</i> to <i>see</i> whether it is your son’s tunic or not.”",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Then he examined it and said, “It is my son’s tunic. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1117AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1117AE\"></sup>A wild beast has devoured him; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1117AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1117AF\"></sup>Joseph has surely been torn to pieces!”",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>So Jacob <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1118AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1118AG\"></sup>tore his clothes, and put sackcloth on his loins and mourned for his son many days.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Then all his sons and all his daughters arose to comfort him, but he refused to be comforted. And he said, “Surely I will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1119AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1119AH\"></sup>go down to Sheol in mourning for my son.” So his father wept for him.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Meanwhile, the Midianites <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1120AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1120AI\"></sup>sold him in Egypt to Potiphar, Pharaoh’s officer, the captain of the bodyguard."
		},
		"38": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">38 </span>And it came about at that time, that Judah departed from his brothers and visited a certain <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1121A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1121A\"></sup>Adullamite, whose name was Hirah.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Judah saw there a daughter of a certain Canaanite whose name was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1122B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1122B\"></sup>Shua; and he took her and went in to her.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>So she conceived and bore a son and he named him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1123C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1123C\"></sup>Er.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then she conceived again and bore a son and named him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1124D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1124D\"></sup>Onan.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>She bore still another son and named him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1125E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1125E\"></sup>Shelah; and it was at Chezib that she bore him.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Now Judah took a wife for Er his firstborn, and her name <i>was</i> Tamar.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1127F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1127F\"></sup>Er, Judah’s firstborn, was evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, so the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> took his life.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then Judah said to Onan, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1128G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1128G\"></sup>Go in to your brother’s wife, and perform your duty as a brother-in-law to her, and raise up offspring for your brother.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Onan knew that the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1129H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1129H\"></sup>offspring would not be his; so when he went in to his brother’s wife, he wasted his seed on the ground in order not to give offspring to his brother.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>But what he did was displeasing in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; so He <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1130I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1130I\"></sup>took his life also.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then Judah said to his daughter-in-law Tamar, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1131J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1131J\"></sup>Remain a widow in your father’s house until my son Shelah grows up”; for he thought, “<i>I am afraid</i> that he too may die like his brothers.” So Tamar went and lived in her father’s house.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Now after a considerable time Shua’s daughter, the wife of Judah, died; and when the time of mourning was ended, Judah went up to his sheepshearers at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1132K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1132K\"></sup>Timnah, he and his friend Hirah the Adullamite.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>It was told to Tamar, “Behold, your father-in-law is going up to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1133L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1133L\"></sup>Timnah to shear his sheep.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>So she removed her widow’s garments and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1134M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1134M\"></sup>covered <i>herself</i> with a veil, and wrapped herself, and sat in the gateway of Enaim, which is on the road to Timnah; for she saw that Shelah had grown up, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1134N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1134N\"></sup>she had not been given to him as a wife.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>When Judah saw her, he thought she <i>was</i> a harlot, for she had covered her face.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>So he turned aside to her by the road, and said, “Here now, let me come in to you”; for he did not know that she was his daughter-in-law. And she said, “What will you give me, that you may come in to me?”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>He said, therefore, “I will send you a young goat from the flock.” She said, moreover, “Will you give a pledge until you send <i>it</i>?”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>He said, “What pledge shall I give you?” And she said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1138O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1138O\"></sup>Your seal and your cord, and your staff that is in your hand.” So he gave <i>them</i> to her and went in to her, and she conceived by him.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Then she arose and departed, and removed her veil and put on her widow’s garments.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>When Judah sent the young goat by his friend the Adullamite, to receive the pledge from the woman’s hand, he did not find her.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>He asked the men of her place, saying, “Where is the temple prostitute who was by the road at Enaim?” But they said, “There has been no temple prostitute here.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>So he returned to Judah, and said, “I did not find her; and furthermore, the men of the place said, ‘There has been no temple prostitute here.’”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Then Judah said, “Let her keep them, otherwise we will become a laughingstock. After all, I sent this young goat, but you did not find her.”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Now it was about three months later that Judah was informed, “Your daughter-in-law Tamar has played the harlot, and behold, she is also with child by harlotry.” Then Judah said, “Bring her out and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1144P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1144P\"></sup>let her be burned!”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>It was while she was being brought out that she sent to her father-in-law, saying, “I am with child by the man to whom these things belong.” And she said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1145Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1145Q\"></sup>Please examine and see, whose signet ring and cords and staff are these?”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Judah recognized <i>them</i>, and said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1146R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1146R\"></sup>She is more righteous than I, inasmuch as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1146S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1146S\"></sup>I did not give her to my son Shelah.” And he did not have relations with her again.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>It came about at the time she was giving birth, that behold, there were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1147T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1147T\"></sup>twins in her womb.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Moreover, it took place while she was giving birth, one put out a hand, and the midwife took and tied a scarlet <i>thread</i> on his hand, saying, “This one came out first.”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>But it came about as he drew back his hand, that behold, his brother came out. Then she said, “What a breach you have made for yourself!” So he was named <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1149U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1149U\"></sup>Perez.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Afterward his brother came out who had the scarlet <i>thread</i> on his hand; and he was named <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1150V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1150V\"></sup>Zerah."
		},
		"39": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">39 </span>Now Joseph had been taken down to Egypt; and Potiphar, an Egyptian officer of Pharaoh, the captain of the bodyguard, bought him from the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1151A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1151A\"></sup>Ishmaelites, who had taken him down there.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1152B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1152B\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was with Joseph, so he became a successful man. And he was in the house of his master, the Egyptian.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Now his master <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1153C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1153C\"></sup>saw that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was with him and <i>how</i> the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1153D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1153D\"></sup>caused all that he did to prosper in his hand.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>So Joseph <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1154E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1154E\"></sup>found favor in his sight and became his personal servant; and he made him overseer over his house, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1154F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1154F\"></sup>all that he owned he put in his charge.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>It came about that from the time he made him overseer in his house and over all that he owned, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1155G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1155G\"></sup>blessed the Egyptian’s house on account of Joseph; thus <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1155H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1155H\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord’s</span> blessing was upon all that he owned, in the house and in the field.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So he left everything he owned in Joseph’s charge; and with him <i>there</i> he did not concern himself with anything except the food which he ate.Now Joseph was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1156I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1156I\"></sup>handsome in form and appearance.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>It came about after these events <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1157J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1157J\"></sup>that his master’s wife looked with desire at Joseph, and she said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1157K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1157K\"></sup>Lie with me.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1158L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1158L\"></sup>he refused and said to his master’s wife, “Behold, with me <i>here</i>, my master does not concern himself with anything in the house, and he has put all that he owns in my charge.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1159M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1159M\"></sup>There is no one greater in this house than I, and he has withheld nothing from me except you, because you are his wife. How then could I do this great evil and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1159N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1159N\"></sup>sin against God?”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>As she spoke to Joseph day after day, he did not listen to her to lie beside her <i>or</i> be with her.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Now it happened one day that he went into the house to do his work, and none of the men of the household was there inside.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>She caught him by his garment, saying, “Lie with me!” And he left his garment in her hand and fled, and went outside.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>When she saw that he had left his garment in her hand and had fled outside,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>she called to the men of her household and said to them, “See, he has brought in a Hebrew to us to make sport of us; he came in to me to lie with me, and I screamed.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>When he heard that I raised my voice and screamed, he left his garment beside me and fled and went outside.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>So she left his garment beside her until his master came home.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then she <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1167O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1167O\"></sup>spoke to him with these words, “The Hebrew slave, whom you brought to us, came in to me to make sport of me;",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>and as I raised my voice and screamed, he left his garment beside me and fled outside.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Now when his master heard the words of his wife, which she spoke to him, saying, “This is what your slave did to me,” <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1169P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1169P\"></sup>his anger burned.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>So Joseph’s master took him and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1170Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1170Q\"></sup>put him into the jail, the place where the king’s prisoners were confined; and he was there in the jail.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1171R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1171R\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was with Joseph and extended kindness to him, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1171S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1171S\"></sup>gave him favor in the sight of the chief jailer.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>The chief jailer <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1172T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1172T\"></sup>committed to Joseph’s charge all the prisoners who were in the jail; so that whatever was done there, he was responsible <i>for it</i>.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1173U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1173U\"></sup>The chief jailer did not supervise anything under Joseph’s charge because <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1173V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1173V\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was with him; and whatever he did, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1173W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1173W\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> made to prosper."
		},
		"40": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">40 </span>Then it came about after these things, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1174A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1174A\"></sup>the cupbearer and the baker for the king of Egypt offended their lord, the king of Egypt.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Pharaoh was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1175B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1175B\"></sup>furious with his two officials, the chief cupbearer and the chief baker.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>So he put them in confinement in the house of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1176C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1176C\"></sup>captain of the bodyguard, in the jail, the <i>same</i> place where Joseph was imprisoned.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The captain of the bodyguard put Joseph in charge of them, and he took care of them; and they were in confinement for some time.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then the cupbearer and the baker for the king of Egypt, who were confined in jail, both had a dream the same night, each man with his <i>own</i> dream <i>and</i> each dream with its <i>own</i> interpretation.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>When Joseph came to them in the morning and observed them, behold, they were dejected.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>He asked Pharaoh’s officials who were with him in confinement in his master’s house, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1180D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1180D\"></sup>Why are your faces so sad today?”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then they said to him, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1181E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1181E\"></sup>We have had a dream and there is no one to interpret it.” Then Joseph said to them, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1181F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1181F\"></sup>Do not interpretations belong to God? Tell <i>it</i> to me, please.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>So the chief cupbearer told his dream to Joseph, and said to him, “In my dream, behold, <i>there was</i> a vine in front of me;",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>and on the vine <i>were</i> three branches. And as it was budding, its blossoms came out, <i>and</i> its clusters produced ripe grapes.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Now Pharaoh’s cup was in my hand; so I took the grapes and squeezed them into Pharaoh’s cup, and I put the cup into Pharaoh’s hand.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then Joseph said to him, “This is the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1185G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1185G\"></sup>interpretation of it: the three branches are three days;",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>within three more days Pharaoh will lift up your head and restore you to your office; and you will put Pharaoh’s cup into his hand according to your former custom when you were his cupbearer.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Only keep me in mind when it goes well with you, and please <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1187H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1187H\"></sup>do me a kindness by mentioning me to Pharaoh and get me out of this house.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1188I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1188I\"></sup>I was in fact kidnapped from the land of the Hebrews, and even here I have done nothing that they should have put me into the dungeon.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>When the chief baker saw that he had interpreted favorably, he said to Joseph, “I also <i>saw</i> in my dream, and behold, <i>there were</i> three baskets of white bread on my head;",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>and in the top basket <i>there were</i> some of all sorts of baked food for Pharaoh, and the birds were eating them out of the basket on my head.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then Joseph answered and said, “This is its interpretation: the three baskets are three days;",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>within three more days Pharaoh will lift up your head from you and will hang you on a tree, and the birds will eat your flesh off you.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Thus it came about on the third day, <i>which was</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1193J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1193J\"></sup>Pharaoh’s birthday, that he made a feast for all his servants; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1193K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1193K\"></sup>and he lifted up the head of the chief cupbearer and the head of the chief baker among his servants.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>He restored the chief cupbearer to his office, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1194L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1194L\"></sup>he put the cup into Pharaoh’s hand;",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1195M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1195M\"></sup>he hanged the chief baker, just as Joseph had interpreted to them.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Yet the chief cupbearer did not remember Joseph, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1196N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1196N\"></sup>forgot him."
		},
		"41": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">41 </span>Now it happened at the end of two full years that Pharaoh had a dream, and behold, he was standing by the Nile.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And lo, from the Nile there came up seven cows, sleek and fat; and they grazed in the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1198A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1198A\"></sup>marsh grass.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then behold, seven other cows came up after them from the Nile, ugly and gaunt, and they stood by the <i>other</i> cows on the bank of the Nile.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The ugly and gaunt cows ate up the seven sleek and fat cows. Then Pharaoh awoke.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>He fell asleep and dreamed a second time; and behold, seven ears of grain came up on a single stalk, plump and good.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then behold, seven ears, thin and scorched by the east wind, sprouted up after them.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The thin ears swallowed up the seven plump and full ears. Then Pharaoh awoke, and behold, <i>it was</i> a dream.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Now in the morning <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1204B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1204B\"></sup>his spirit was troubled, so he sent and called for all the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1204C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1204C\"></sup>magicians of Egypt, and all its <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1204D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1204D\"></sup>wise men. And Pharaoh told them his dreams, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1204E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1204E\"></sup>there was no one who could interpret them to Pharaoh.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then the chief cupbearer spoke to Pharaoh, saying, “I would make mention today of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1205F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1205F\"></sup>my <i>own</i> offenses.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Pharaoh was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1206G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1206G\"></sup>furious with his servants, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1206H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1206H\"></sup>he put me in confinement in the house of the captain of the bodyguard, <i>both</i> me and the chief baker.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1207I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1207I\"></sup>We had a dream on the same night, he and I; each of us dreamed according to the interpretation of his <i>own</i> dream.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Now a Hebrew youth <i>was</i> with us there, a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1208J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1208J\"></sup>servant of the captain of the bodyguard, and we related <i>them</i> to him, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1208K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1208K\"></sup>he interpreted our dreams for us. To each one he interpreted according to his <i>own</i> dream.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And just <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1209L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1209L\"></sup>as he interpreted for us, so it happened; he restored me in my office, but he hanged him.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then Pharaoh sent and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1210M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1210M\"></sup>called for Joseph, and they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1210N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1210N\"></sup>hurriedly brought him out of the dungeon; and when he had shaved himself and changed his clothes, he came to Pharaoh.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Pharaoh said to Joseph, “I have had a dream, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1211O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1211O\"></sup>but no one can interpret it; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1211P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1211P\"></sup>I have heard it said about you, that when you hear a dream you can interpret it.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Joseph then answered Pharaoh, saying, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1212Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1212Q\"></sup>It is not in me; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1212R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1212R\"></sup>God will give Pharaoh a favorable answer.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>So Pharaoh spoke to Joseph, “In my dream, behold, I was standing on the bank of the Nile;",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>and behold, seven cows, fat and sleek came up out of the Nile, and they grazed in the marsh grass.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Lo, seven other cows came up after them, poor and very ugly and gaunt, such as I had never seen for ugliness in all the land of Egypt;",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>and the lean and ugly cows ate up the first seven fat cows.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Yet when they had devoured them, it could not be detected that they had devoured them, for they were just as ugly as before. Then I awoke.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>I saw also in my dream, and behold, seven ears, full and good, came up on a single stalk;",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>and lo, seven ears, withered, thin, <i>and</i> scorched by the east wind, sprouted up after them;",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>and the thin ears swallowed the seven good ears. Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1220S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1220S\"></sup>I told it to the magicians, but there was no one who could explain it to me.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Now Joseph said to Pharaoh, “Pharaoh’s dreams are one <i>and the same</i>; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1221T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1221T\"></sup>God has told to Pharaoh what He is about to do.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>The seven good cows are seven years; and the seven good ears are seven years; the dreams are one <i>and the same</i>.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>The seven lean and ugly cows that came up after them are seven years, and the seven thin ears scorched by the east wind <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1223U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1223U\"></sup>will be seven years of famine.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>It is as I have spoken to Pharaoh: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1224V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1224V\"></sup>God has shown to Pharaoh what He is about to do.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1225W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1225W\"></sup>seven years of great abundance are coming in all the land of Egypt;",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>and after them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1226X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1226X\"></sup>seven years of famine will come, and all the abundance will be forgotten in the land of Egypt, and the famine will ravage the land.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>So the abundance will be unknown in the land because of that subsequent famine; for it <i>will be</i> very severe.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Now as for the repeating of the dream to Pharaoh twice, <i>it means</i> that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1228Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1228Y\"></sup>the matter is determined by God, and God will quickly bring it about.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Now let Pharaoh look for a man <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1229Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1229Z\"></sup>discerning and wise, and set him over the land of Egypt.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Let Pharaoh take action to appoint overseers in charge of the land, and let him exact a fifth <i>of the produce</i> of the land of Egypt in the seven years of abundance.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Then let them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1231AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1231AA\"></sup>gather all the food of these good years that are coming, and store up the grain for food in the cities under Pharaoh’s authority, and let them guard <i>it</i>.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Let the food become as a reserve for the land for the seven years of famine which will occur in the land of Egypt, so that the land will not perish during the famine.”",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Now the proposal seemed good to Pharaoh and to all his servants.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>Then Pharaoh said to his servants, “Can we find a man like this, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1234AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1234AB\"></sup>in whom is a divine spirit?”",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>So Pharaoh said to Joseph, “Since God has informed you of all this, there is no one so <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1235AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1235AC\"></sup>discerning and wise as you are.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1236AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1236AD\"></sup>You shall be over my house, and according to your command all my people shall do homage; only in the throne I will be greater than you.”",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>Pharaoh said to Joseph, “See, I have set you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1237AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1237AE\"></sup>over all the land of Egypt.”",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>Then Pharaoh <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1238AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1238AF\"></sup>took off his signet ring from his hand and put it on Joseph’s hand, and clothed him in garments of fine linen and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1238AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1238AG\"></sup>put the gold necklace around his neck.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>He had him ride in his second chariot; and they proclaimed before him, “Bow the knee!” And he set him over all the land of Egypt.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>Moreover, Pharaoh said to Joseph, “<i>Though</i> I am Pharaoh, yet <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1240AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1240AH\"></sup>without your permission no one shall raise his hand or foot in all the land of Egypt.”",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>Then Pharaoh named Joseph Zaphenath-paneah; and he gave him Asenath, the daughter of Potiphera priest of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1241AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1241AI\"></sup>On, as his wife. And Joseph went forth over the land of Egypt.",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>Now Joseph was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1242AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1242AJ\"></sup>thirty years old when he stood before Pharaoh, king of Egypt. And Joseph went out from the presence of Pharaoh and went through all the land of Egypt.",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>During the seven years of plenty the land brought forth abundantly.",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>So he gathered all the food of <i>these</i> seven years which occurred in the land of Egypt and placed the food in the cities; he placed in every city the food from its own surrounding fields.",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>Thus Joseph stored up grain in great abundance like the sand of the sea, until he stopped measuring <i>it</i>, for it was beyond measure.",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>Now before the year of famine came, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1246AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1246AK\"></sup>two sons were born to Joseph, whom Asenath, the daughter of Potiphera priest of On, bore to him.",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>Joseph named the firstborn Manasseh, “For,” <i>he said</i>, “God has made me forget all my trouble and all my father’s household.”",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>He named the second Ephraim, “For,” <i>he said</i>, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1248AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1248AL\"></sup>God has made me fruitful in the land of my affliction.”",
			"53": "<sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup>When the seven years of plenty which had been in the land of Egypt came to an end,",
			"54": "<sup class=\"versenum\">54 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1250AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1250AM\"></sup>the seven years of famine began to come, just as Joseph had said, then there was famine in all the lands, but in all the land of Egypt there was bread.",
			"55": "<sup class=\"versenum\">55 </sup>So when all the land of Egypt was famished, the people cried out to Pharaoh for bread; and Pharaoh said to all the Egyptians, “Go to Joseph; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1251AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1251AN\"></sup>whatever he says to you, you shall do.”",
			"56": "<sup class=\"versenum\">56 </sup>When the famine was <i>spread</i> over all the face of the earth, then Joseph opened all the storehouses, and sold to the Egyptians; and the famine was severe in the land of Egypt.",
			"57": "<sup class=\"versenum\">57 </sup><i>The people of</i> all the earth came to Egypt to buy grain from Joseph, because <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1253AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1253AO\"></sup>the famine was severe in all the earth."
		},
		"42": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">42 </span>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1254A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1254A\"></sup>Jacob saw that there was grain in Egypt, and Jacob said to his sons, “Why are you staring at one another?”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He said, “Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1255B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1255B\"></sup>I have heard that there is grain in Egypt; go down there and buy <i>some</i> for us from that place, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1255C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1255C\"></sup>so that we may live and not die.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then ten brothers of Joseph went down to buy grain from Egypt.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>But Jacob did not send Joseph’s brother <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1257D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1257D\"></sup>Benjamin with his brothers, for he said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1257E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1257E\"></sup>I am afraid that harm may befall him.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>So the sons of Israel came to buy grain among those who were coming, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1258F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1258F\"></sup>for the famine was in the land of Canaan <i>also</i>.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1259G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1259G\"></sup>Joseph was the ruler over the land; he was the one who sold to all the people of the land. And Joseph’s brothers came and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1259H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1259H\"></sup>bowed down to him with <i>their</i> faces to the ground.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>When Joseph saw his brothers he recognized them, but he disguised himself to them and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1260I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1260I\"></sup>spoke to them harshly. And he said to them, “Where have you come from?” And they said, “From the land of Canaan, to buy food.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>But Joseph had recognized his brothers, although <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1261J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1261J\"></sup>they did not recognize him.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Joseph <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1262K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1262K\"></sup>remembered the dreams which he had about them, and said to them, “You are spies; you have come to look at the undefended parts of our land.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then they said to him, “No, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1263L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1263L\"></sup>my lord, but your servants have come to buy food.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>We are all sons of one man; we are <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1264M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1264M\"></sup>honest men, your servants are not spies.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Yet he said to them, “No, but you have come to look at the undefended parts of our land!”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>But they said, “Your servants are twelve brothers <i>in all</i>, the sons of one man in the land of Canaan; and behold, the youngest is with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1266N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1266N\"></sup>our father today, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1266O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1266O\"></sup>one is no longer alive.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Joseph said to them, “It is as I said to you, you are spies;",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>by this you will be tested: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1268P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1268P\"></sup>by the life of Pharaoh, you shall not go from this place unless your youngest brother comes here!",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Send one of you that he may get your brother, while you remain confined, that your words may be tested, whether there is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1269Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1269Q\"></sup>truth in you. But if not, by the life of Pharaoh, surely you are spies.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>So he put them all together in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1270R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1270R\"></sup>prison for three days.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Now Joseph said to them on the third day, “Do this and live, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1271S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1271S\"></sup>I fear God:",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>if you are honest men, let one of your brothers be confined in your prison; but as for <i>the rest of</i> you, go, carry grain for the famine of your households,",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1273T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1273T\"></sup>bring your youngest brother to me, so your words may be verified, and you will not die.” And they did so.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then they said to one another, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1274U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1274U\"></sup>Truly we are guilty concerning our brother, because we saw the distress of his soul when he pleaded with us, yet we would not listen; therefore this distress has come upon us.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Reuben answered them, saying, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1275V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1275V\"></sup>Did I not tell you, ‘Do not sin against the boy’; and you would not listen? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1275W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1275W\"></sup>Now comes the reckoning for his blood.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>They did not know, however, that Joseph understood, for there was an interpreter between them.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>He turned away from them and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1277X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1277X\"></sup>wept. But when he returned to them and spoke to them, he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1277Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1277Y\"></sup>took Simeon from them and bound him before their eyes.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1278Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1278Z\"></sup>Then Joseph gave orders to fill their bags with grain and to restore every man’s money in his sack, and to give them provisions for the journey. And thus it was done for them.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>So they loaded their donkeys with their grain and departed from there.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>As one <i>of them</i> opened his sack to give his donkey fodder at the lodging place, he saw his <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1280AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1280AA\"></sup>money; and behold, it was in the mouth of his sack.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Then he said to his brothers, “My money has been returned, and behold, it is even in my sack.” And their hearts sank, and they <i>turned</i> trembling to one another, saying, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1281AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1281AB\"></sup>What is this that God has done to us?”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>When they came to their father Jacob in the land of Canaan, they told him all that had happened to them, saying,",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>“The man, the lord of the land, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1283AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1283AC\"></sup>spoke harshly with us, and took us for spies of the country.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>But we said to him, ‘We are <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1284AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1284AD\"></sup>honest men; we are not spies.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>We are twelve brothers, sons of our father; one is no longer alive, and the youngest is with our father today in the land of Canaan.’",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>The man, the lord of the land, said to us, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1286AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1286AE\"></sup>By this I will know that you are honest men: leave one of your brothers with me and take <i>grain for</i> the famine of your households, and go.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>But bring your youngest brother to me that I may know that you are not spies, but honest men. I will give your brother to you, and you may <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1287AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1287AF\"></sup>trade in the land.’”",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Now it came about as they were emptying their sacks, that behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1288AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1288AG\"></sup>every man’s bundle of money <i>was</i> in his sack; and when they and their father saw their bundles of money, they were dismayed.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Their father Jacob said to them, “You have <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1289AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1289AH\"></sup>bereaved me of my children: Joseph is no more, and Simeon is no more, and you would take Benjamin; all these things are against me.”",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Then Reuben spoke to his father, saying, “You may put my two sons to death if I do not bring him <i>back</i> to you; put him in my care, and I will return him to you.”",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>But Jacob said, “My son shall not go down with you; for his <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1291AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1291AI\"></sup>brother is dead, and he alone is left. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1291AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1291AJ\"></sup>If harm should befall him on the journey you are taking, then you will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1291AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1291AK\"></sup>bring my gray hair down to Sheol in sorrow.”"
		},
		"43": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">43 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1292A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1292A\"></sup>Now the famine was severe in the land.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>So it came about when they had finished eating the grain which they had brought from Egypt, that their father said to them, “Go back, buy us a little food.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Judah spoke to him, however, saying, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1294B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1294B\"></sup>The man solemnly warned us, ‘You shall not see my face unless your brother is with you.’",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>If you send our brother with us, we will go down and buy you food.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>But if you do not send <i>him</i>, we will not go down; for the man said to us, ‘You will not see my face unless your brother is with you.’”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then Israel said, “Why did you treat me so badly by telling the man whether you still had <i>another</i> brother?”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>But they said, “The man questioned particularly about us and our relatives, saying, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1298C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1298C\"></sup>Is your father still alive? Have you <i>another</i> brother?’ So we answered his questions. Could we possibly know that he would say, ‘Bring your brother down’?”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Judah said to his father Israel, “Send the lad with me and we will arise and go, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1299D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1299D\"></sup>that we may live and not die, we as well as you and our little ones.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1300E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1300E\"></sup>I myself will be surety for him; you may hold me responsible for him. If I do not bring him <i>back</i> to you and set him before you, then let me bear the blame before you forever.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>For if we had not delayed, surely by now we could have returned twice.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then their father Israel said to them, “If <i>it must be</i> so, then do this: take some of the best products of the land in your bags, and carry down to the man <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1302F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1302F\"></sup>as a present, a little <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1302G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1302G\"></sup>balm and a little honey, aromatic gum and myrrh, pistachio nuts and almonds.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Take double <i>the</i> money in your hand, and take back in your hand <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1303H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1303H\"></sup>the money that was returned in the mouth of your sacks; perhaps it was a mistake.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Take your brother also, and arise, return to the man;",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>and may <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1305I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1305I\"></sup>God Almighty <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1305J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1305J\"></sup>grant you compassion in the sight of the man, so that he will release to you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1305K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1305K\"></sup>your other brother and Benjamin. And as for me, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1305L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1305L\"></sup>if I am bereaved of my children, I am bereaved.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>So the men took <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1306M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1306M\"></sup>this present, and they took double <i>the</i> money in their hand, and Benjamin; then they arose and went down to Egypt and stood before Joseph.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>When Joseph saw Benjamin with them, he said to his <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1307N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1307N\"></sup>house steward, “Bring the men into the house, and slay an animal and make ready; for the men are to dine with me at noon.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>So the man did as Joseph said, and brought the men to Joseph’s house.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Now the men were afraid, because they were brought to Joseph’s house; and they said, “<i>It is</i> because of the money that was returned in our sacks the first time that we are being brought in, that he may seek occasion against us and fall upon us, and take us for slaves with our donkeys.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>So they came near to Joseph’s house steward, and spoke to him at the entrance of the house,",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>and said, “Oh, my lord, we indeed came down the first time to buy food,",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>and it came about when we came to the lodging place, that we opened our sacks, and behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1312O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1312O\"></sup>each man’s money was in the mouth of his sack, our money in full. So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1312P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1312P\"></sup>we have brought it back in our hand.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>We have also brought down other money in our hand to buy food; we do not know who put our money in our sacks.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>He said, “Be at ease, do not be afraid. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1314Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1314Q\"></sup>Your God and the God of your father has given you treasure in your sacks; I had your money.” Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1314R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1314R\"></sup>he brought Simeon out to them.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Then the man brought the men into Joseph’s house and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1315S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1315S\"></sup>gave them water, and they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1315T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1315T\"></sup>washed their feet; and he gave their donkeys fodder.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>So they prepared <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1316U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1316U\"></sup>the present for Joseph’s coming at noon; for they had heard that they were to eat a meal there.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>When Joseph came home, they brought into the house to him the present which was in their hand and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1317V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1317V\"></sup>bowed to the ground before him.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Then he asked them about their welfare, and said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1318W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1318W\"></sup>Is your old father well, of whom you spoke? Is he still alive?”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>They said, “Your servant our father is well; he is still alive.” <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1319X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1319X\"></sup>They bowed down in homage.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>As he lifted his eyes and saw his brother Benjamin, his mother’s son, he said, “Is this <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1320Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1320Y\"></sup>your youngest brother, of whom you spoke to me?” And he said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1320Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1320Z\"></sup>May God be gracious to you, my son.”",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Joseph hurried <i>out</i> for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1321AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1321AA\"></sup>he was deeply stirred over his brother, and he sought <i>a place</i> to weep; and he entered his chamber and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1321AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1321AB\"></sup>wept there.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Then he washed his face and came out; and he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1322AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1322AC\"></sup>controlled himself and said, “Serve the meal.”",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>So they served him by himself, and them by themselves, and the Egyptians who ate with him by themselves, because the Egyptians could not eat bread with the Hebrews, for that is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1323AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1323AD\"></sup>loathsome to the Egyptians.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Now they were seated before him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1324AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1324AE\"></sup>the firstborn according to his birthright and the youngest according to his youth, and the men looked at one another in astonishment.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>He took portions to them from his own table, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1325AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1325AF\"></sup>but Benjamin’s portion was five times as much as any of theirs. So they feasted and drank freely with him."
		},
		"44": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">44 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1326A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1326A\"></sup>Then he commanded his house steward, saying, “Fill the men’s sacks with food, as much as they can carry, and put each man’s money in the mouth of his sack.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Put my cup, the silver cup, in the mouth of the sack of the youngest, and his money for the grain.” And he did as Joseph had told <i>him</i>.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>As soon as it was light, the men were sent away, they with their donkeys.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>They had <i>just</i> gone out of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1329B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1329B\"></sup>the city, <i>and</i> were not far off, when Joseph said to his house steward, “Up, follow the men; and when you overtake them, say to them, ‘Why have you repaid evil for good?",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Is not this the one from which my lord drinks and which he indeed uses for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1330C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1330C\"></sup>divination? You have done wrong in doing this.’”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So he overtook them and spoke these words to them.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>They said to him, “Why does my lord speak such words as these? Far be it from your servants to do such a thing.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1333D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1333D\"></sup>the money which we found in the mouth of our sacks we have brought back to you from the land of Canaan. How then could we steal silver or gold from your lord’s house?",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1334E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1334E\"></sup>With whomever of your servants it is found, let him die, and we also will be my lord’s <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1334F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1334F\"></sup>slaves.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>So he said, “Now let it also be according to your words; he with whom it is found shall be my slave, and <i>the rest of</i> you shall be innocent.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then they hurried, each man lowered his sack to the ground, and each man opened his sack.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>He searched, beginning with the oldest and ending with the youngest, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1337G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1337G\"></sup>the cup was found in Benjamin’s sack.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1338H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1338H\"></sup>tore their clothes, and when each man loaded his donkey, they returned to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1338I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1338I\"></sup>the city.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>When Judah and his brothers came to Joseph’s house, he was still there, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1339J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1339J\"></sup>they fell to the ground before him.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Joseph said to them, “What is this deed that you have done? Do you not know that such a man as I can indeed practice <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1340K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1340K\"></sup>divination?”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>So Judah said, “What can we say to my lord? What can we speak? And how can we justify ourselves? God has found out the iniquity of your servants; behold, we are my lord’s <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1341L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1341L\"></sup>slaves, both we and the one in whose possession the cup has been found.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>But he said, “Far be it from me to do this. The man in whose possession the cup has been found, he shall be my slave; but as for you, go up in peace to your father.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then Judah approached him, and said, “Oh my lord, may your servant please speak a word in my lord’s ears, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1343M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1343M\"></sup>do not be angry with your servant; for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1343N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1343N\"></sup>you are equal to Pharaoh.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1344O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1344O\"></sup>My lord asked his servants, saying, ‘Have you a father or a brother?’",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>We said to my lord, ‘We have an old father and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1345P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1345P\"></sup>a little child of <i>his</i> old age. Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1345Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1345Q\"></sup>his brother is dead, so he alone is left of his mother, and his father loves him.’",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then you said to your servants, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1346R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1346R\"></sup>Bring him down to me that I may set my eyes on him.’",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>But we said to my lord, ‘The lad cannot leave his father, for if he should leave his father, his father would die.’",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>You said to your servants, however, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1348S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1348S\"></sup>Unless your youngest brother comes down with you, you will not see my face again.’",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Thus it came about when we went up to your servant my father, we told him the words of my lord.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1350T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1350T\"></sup>Our father said, ‘Go back, buy us a little food.’",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>But we said, ‘We cannot go down. If our youngest brother is with us, then we will go down; for we cannot see the man’s face unless our youngest brother is with us.’",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Your servant my father said to us, ‘You know that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1352U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1352U\"></sup>my wife bore me two sons;",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>and the one went out from me, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1353V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1353V\"></sup>I said, “Surely he is torn in pieces,” and I have not seen him since.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>If you take this one also from me, and harm befalls him, you will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1354W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1354W\"></sup>bring my gray hair down to Sheol in sorrow.’",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Now, therefore, when I come to your servant my father, and the lad is not with us, since <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1355X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1355X\"></sup>his life is bound up in the lad’s life,",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>when he sees that the lad is not <i>with us</i>, he will die. Thus your servants will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1356Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1356Y\"></sup>bring the gray hair of your servant our father down to Sheol in sorrow.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>For your servant <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1357Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1357Z\"></sup>became surety for the lad to my father, saying, ‘If I do not bring him <i>back</i> to you, then let me bear the blame before my father forever.’",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Now, therefore, please let your servant remain instead of the lad a slave to my lord, and let the lad go up with his brothers.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>For how shall I go up to my father if the lad is not with me—for fear that I see the evil that would overtake my father?”"
		},
		"45": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">45 </span>Then Joseph could not control himself before all those who stood by him, and he cried, “Have everyone go out from me.” So there was no man with him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1360A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1360A\"></sup>when Joseph made himself known to his brothers.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1361B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1361B\"></sup>He wept so loudly that the Egyptians heard <i>it</i>, and the household of Pharaoh heard <i>of it</i>.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then Joseph said to his brothers, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1362C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1362C\"></sup>I am Joseph! <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1362D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1362D\"></sup>Is my father still alive?” But his brothers could not answer him, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1362E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1362E\"></sup>they were dismayed at his presence.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then Joseph said to his brothers, “Please come closer to me.” And they came closer. And he said, “I am your brother Joseph, whom you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1363F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1363F\"></sup>sold into Egypt.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Now do not be grieved or angry with yourselves, because <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1364G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1364G\"></sup>you sold me here, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1364H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1364H\"></sup>God sent me before you to preserve life.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>For the famine <i>has been</i> in the land <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1365I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1365I\"></sup>these two years, and there are still five years in which there will be neither plowing nor harvesting.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1366J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1366J\"></sup>God sent me before you to preserve for you a remnant in the earth, and to keep you alive by a great deliverance.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Now, therefore, it was not you who sent me here, but God; and He has made me a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1367K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1367K\"></sup>father to Pharaoh and lord of all his household and ruler over all the land of Egypt.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Hurry and go up to my father, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1368L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1368L\"></sup>say to him, ‘Thus says your son Joseph, “God has made me lord of all Egypt; come down to me, do not delay.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>You shall live in the land of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1369M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1369M\"></sup>Goshen, and you shall be near me, you and your children and your children’s children and your flocks and your herds and all that you have.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>There I will also <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1370N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1370N\"></sup>provide for you, for there are still five years of famine <i>to come</i>, and you and your household and all that you have would be impoverished.”’",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Behold, your eyes see, and the eyes of my brother Benjamin <i>see</i>, that it is my mouth which is speaking to you.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Now you must tell my father of all my splendor in Egypt, and all that you have seen; and you must hurry and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1372O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1372O\"></sup>bring my father down here.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then he fell on his brother Benjamin’s neck and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1373P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1373P\"></sup>wept, and Benjamin wept on his neck.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>He kissed all his brothers and wept on them, and afterward his brothers talked with him.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Now when <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1375Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1375Q\"></sup>the news was heard in Pharaoh’s house that Joseph’s brothers had come, it pleased Pharaoh and his servants.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then Pharaoh said to Joseph, “Say to your brothers, ‘Do this: load your beasts and go to the land of Canaan,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>and take your father and your households and come to me, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1377R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1377R\"></sup>I will give you the best of the land of Egypt and you will eat the fat of the land.’",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Now you are ordered, ‘Do this: take <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1378S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1378S\"></sup>wagons from the land of Egypt for your little ones and for your wives, and bring your father and come.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Do not concern yourselves with your goods, for the best of all the land of Egypt is yours.’”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then the sons of Israel did so; and Joseph gave them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1380T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1380T\"></sup>wagons according to the command of Pharaoh, and gave them provisions for the journey.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>To each of them he gave <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1381U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1381U\"></sup>changes of garments, but to Benjamin he gave three hundred <i>pieces of</i> silver and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1381V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1381V\"></sup>five changes of garments.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>To his father he sent as follows: ten donkeys loaded with the best things of Egypt, and ten female donkeys loaded with grain and bread and sustenance for his father on the journey.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>So he sent his brothers away, and as they departed, he said to them, “Do not quarrel on the journey.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Then they went up from Egypt, and came to the land of Canaan to their father Jacob.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>They told him, saying, “Joseph is still alive, and indeed he is ruler over all the land of Egypt.” But he was stunned, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1385W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1385W\"></sup>he did not believe them.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>When they told him all the words of Joseph that he had spoken to them, and when he saw the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1386X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1386X\"></sup>wagons that Joseph had sent to carry him, the spirit of their father Jacob revived.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Then Israel said, “It is enough; my son Joseph is still alive. I will go and see him before I die.”"
		},
		"46": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">46 </span>So Israel set out with all that he had, and came to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1388A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1388A\"></sup>Beersheba, and offered sacrifices to the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1388B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1388B\"></sup>God of his father Isaac.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1389C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1389C\"></sup>God spoke to Israel in visions of the night and said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1389D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1389D\"></sup>Jacob, Jacob.” And he said, “Here I am.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>He said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1390E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1390E\"></sup>I am God, the God of your father; do not be afraid to go down to Egypt, for I will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1390F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1390F\"></sup>make you a great nation there.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1391G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1391G\"></sup>I will go down with you to Egypt, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1391H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1391H\"></sup>I will also surely bring you up again; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1391I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1391I\"></sup>Joseph will close your eyes.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then Jacob arose from Beersheba; and the sons of Israel carried their father Jacob and their little ones and their wives in the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1392J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1392J\"></sup>wagons which Pharaoh had sent to carry him.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>They took their livestock and their property, which they had acquired in the land of Canaan, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1393K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1393K\"></sup>came to Egypt, Jacob and all his descendants with him:",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>his sons and his grandsons with him, his daughters and his granddaughters, and all his descendants he brought with him to Egypt.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Now these are the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1395L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1395L\"></sup>names of the sons of Israel, Jacob and his sons, who went to Egypt: Reuben, Jacob’s firstborn.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>The sons of Reuben: Hanoch and Pallu and Hezron and Carmi.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1397M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1397M\"></sup>sons of Simeon: Jemuel and Jamin and Ohad and Jachin and Zohar and Shaul the son of a Canaanite woman.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The sons of Levi: Gershon, Kohath, and Merari.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The sons of Judah: Er and Onan and Shelah and Perez and Zerah (but Er and Onan died in the land of Canaan). And the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1399N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1399N\"></sup>sons of Perez were Hezron and Hamul.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The sons of Issachar: Tola and Puvvah and Iob and Shimron.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The sons of Zebulun: Sered and Elon and Jahleel.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>These are the sons of Leah, whom she bore to Jacob in Paddan-aram, with his daughter Dinah; all his sons and his daughters <i>numbered</i> thirty-three.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1403O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1403O\"></sup>sons of Gad: Ziphion and Haggi, Shuni and Ezbon, Eri and Arodi and Areli.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1404P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1404P\"></sup>sons of Asher: Imnah and Ishvah and Ishvi and Beriah and their sister Serah. And the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1404Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1404Q\"></sup>sons of Beriah: Heber and Malchiel.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>These are the sons of Zilpah, whom Laban gave to his daughter Leah; and she bore to Jacob these sixteen persons.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>The sons of Jacob’s wife Rachel: Joseph and Benjamin.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1407R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1407R\"></sup>Now to Joseph in the land of Egypt were born Manasseh and Ephraim, whom Asenath, the daughter of Potiphera, priest of On, bore to him.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>The <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1408S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1408S\"></sup>sons of Benjamin: Bela and Becher and Ashbel, Gera and Naaman, Ehi and Rosh, Muppim and Huppim and Ard.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>These are the sons of Rachel, who were born to Jacob; <i>there were</i> fourteen persons in all.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>The sons of Dan: Hushim.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>The sons of Naphtali: Jahzeel and Guni and Jezer and Shillem.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>These are the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1412T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1412T\"></sup>sons of Bilhah, whom <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1412U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1412U\"></sup>Laban gave to his daughter Rachel, and she bore these to Jacob; <i>there were</i> seven persons in all.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1413V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1413V\"></sup>All the persons belonging to Jacob, who came to Egypt, his direct descendants, not including the wives of Jacob’s sons, <i>were</i> sixty-six persons in all,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>and the sons of Joseph, who were born to him in Egypt were two; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1414W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1414W\"></sup>all the persons of the house of Jacob, who came to Egypt, <i>were</i> seventy.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Now he sent Judah before him to Joseph, to point out <i>the way</i> before him to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1415X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1415X\"></sup>Goshen; and they came into the land of Goshen.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Joseph prepared his chariot and went up to Goshen to meet his father Israel; as soon as he appeared before him, he fell on his neck and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1416Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1416Y\"></sup>wept on his neck a long time.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Then Israel said to Joseph, “Now let me die, since I have seen your face, that you are still alive.”",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Joseph said to his brothers and to his father’s household, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1418Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1418Z\"></sup>I will go up and tell Pharaoh, and will say to him, ‘My brothers and my father’s household, who <i>were</i> in the land of Canaan, have come to me;",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>and the men are shepherds, for they have been keepers of livestock; and they have brought their flocks and their herds and all that they have.’",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>When Pharaoh calls you and says, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1420AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1420AA\"></sup>What is your occupation?’",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>you shall say, ‘Your servants have been <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1421AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1421AB\"></sup>keepers of livestock from our youth even until now, both we and our fathers,’ that you may live in the land of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1421AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1421AC\"></sup>Goshen; for every shepherd is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1421AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1421AD\"></sup>loathsome to the Egyptians.”"
		},
		"47": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">47 </span>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1422A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1422A\"></sup>Joseph went in and told Pharaoh, and said, “My father and my brothers and their flocks and their herds and all that they have, have come out of the land of Canaan; and behold, they are in the land of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1422B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1422B\"></sup>Goshen.”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He took five men from among his brothers and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1423C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1423C\"></sup>presented them to Pharaoh.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then Pharaoh said to his brothers, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1424D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1424D\"></sup>What is your occupation?” So they said to Pharaoh, “Your servants are <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1424E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1424E\"></sup>shepherds, both we and our fathers.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>They said to Pharaoh, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1425F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1425F\"></sup>We have come to sojourn in the land, for there is no pasture for your servants’ flocks, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1425G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1425G\"></sup>the famine is severe in the land of Canaan. Now, therefore, please let your servants <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1425H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1425H\"></sup>live in the land of Goshen.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then Pharaoh said to Joseph, “Your father and your brothers have come to you.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The land of Egypt is at your disposal; settle your father and your brothers in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1427I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1427I\"></sup>the best of the land, let them live in the land of Goshen; and if you know any <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1427J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1427J\"></sup>capable men among them, then put them in charge of my livestock.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then Joseph brought his father Jacob and presented him to Pharaoh; and Jacob <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1428K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1428K\"></sup>blessed Pharaoh.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Pharaoh said to Jacob, “How many years have you lived?”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>So Jacob said to Pharaoh, “The <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1430L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1430L\"></sup>years of my sojourning are one hundred and thirty; few and unpleasant have been the years of my life, nor have they attained <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1430M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1430M\"></sup>the years that my fathers lived during the days of their sojourning.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And Jacob <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1431N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1431N\"></sup>blessed Pharaoh, and went out from his presence.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>So Joseph settled his father and his brothers and gave them a possession in the land of Egypt, in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1432O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1432O\"></sup>the best of the land, in the land of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1432P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1432P\"></sup>Rameses, as Pharaoh had ordered.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Joseph <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1433Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1433Q\"></sup>provided his father and his brothers and all his father’s household with food, according to their little ones.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Now there was no food in all the land, because the famine was very severe, so that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1434R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1434R\"></sup>the land of Egypt and the land of Canaan languished because of the famine.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1435S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1435S\"></sup>Joseph gathered all the money that was found in the land of Egypt and in the land of Canaan for the grain which they bought, and Joseph brought the money into Pharaoh’s house.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>When the money was all spent in the land of Egypt and in the land of Canaan, all the Egyptians came to Joseph and said, “Give us food, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1436T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1436T\"></sup>why should we die in your presence? For <i>our</i> money is gone.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then Joseph said, “Give up your livestock, and I will give you <i>food</i> for your livestock, since <i>your</i> money is gone.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>So they brought their livestock to Joseph, and Joseph gave them food in exchange for the horses and the flocks and the herds and the donkeys; and he fed them with food in exchange for all their livestock that year.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>When that year was ended, they came to him the next year and said to him, “We will not hide from my lord that our money is all spent, and the cattle are my lord’s. There is nothing left for my lord except our bodies and our lands.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Why should we die before your eyes, both we and our land? Buy us and our land for food, and we and our land will be slaves to Pharaoh. So give us seed, that we may live and not die, and that the land may not be desolate.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>So Joseph bought all the land of Egypt for Pharaoh, for every Egyptian sold his field, because the famine was severe upon them. Thus the land became Pharaoh’s.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>As for the people, he removed them to the cities from one end of Egypt’s border to the other.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Only the land of the priests he did not buy, for the priests had an allotment from Pharaoh, and they lived off the allotment which Pharaoh gave them. Therefore, they did not sell their land.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Then Joseph said to the people, “Behold, I have today bought you and your land for Pharaoh; now, <i>here</i> is seed for you, and you may sow the land.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>At the harvest you shall give a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1445U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1445U\"></sup>fifth to Pharaoh, and four-fifths shall be your own for seed of the field and for your food and for those of your households and as food for your little ones.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>So they said, “You have saved our lives! Let us find favor in the sight of my lord, and we will be Pharaoh’s slaves.”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Joseph made it a statute concerning the land of Egypt <i>valid</i> to this day, that Pharaoh should have the fifth; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1447V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1447V\"></sup>only the land of the priests did not become Pharaoh’s.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Now Israel lived in the land of Egypt, in Goshen, and they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1448W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1448W\"></sup>acquired property in it and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1448X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1448X\"></sup>were fruitful and became very numerous.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Jacob lived in the land of Egypt <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1449Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1449Y\"></sup>seventeen years; so the length of Jacob’s life was one hundred and forty-seven years.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>When <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1450Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1450Z\"></sup>the time for Israel to die drew near, he called his son Joseph and said to him, “Please, if I have found favor in your sight, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1450AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1450AA\"></sup>place now your hand under my thigh and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1450AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1450AB\"></sup>deal with me in kindness and faithfulness. Please do not bury me in Egypt,",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>but when I <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1451AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1451AC\"></sup>lie down with my fathers, you shall carry me out of Egypt and bury me in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1451AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1451AD\"></sup>their burial place.” And he said, “I will do as you have said.”",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>He said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1452AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1452AE\"></sup>Swear to me.” So he swore to him. Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1452AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1452AF\"></sup>Israel bowed <i>in worship</i> at the head of the bed."
		},
		"48": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">48 </span>Now it came about after these things that Joseph was told, “Behold, your father is sick.” So he took his two sons <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1453A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1453A\"></sup>Manasseh and Ephraim with him.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>When it was told to Jacob, “Behold, your son Joseph has come to you,” Israel collected his strength and sat up in the bed.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then Jacob said to Joseph, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1455B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1455B\"></sup>God Almighty appeared to me at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1455C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1455C\"></sup>Luz in the land of Canaan and blessed me,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>and He said to me, ‘Behold, I will make you fruitful and numerous, and I will make you a company of peoples, and will give this land to your descendants after you for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1456D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1456D\"></sup>an everlasting possession.’",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Now your two sons, who were born to you in the land of Egypt before I came to you in Egypt, are mine; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1457E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1457E\"></sup>Ephraim and Manasseh shall be mine, as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1457F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1457F\"></sup>Reuben and Simeon are.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>But your offspring that have been born after them shall be yours; they shall be called by the names of their brothers in their inheritance.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Now as for me, when I came from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1459G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1459G\"></sup>Paddan, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1459H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1459H\"></sup>Rachel died, to my sorrow, in the land of Canaan on the journey, when there was still some distance to go to Ephrath; and I buried her there on the way to Ephrath (that is, Bethlehem).”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>When Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1460I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1460I\"></sup>saw Joseph’s sons, he said, “Who are these?”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Joseph said to his father, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1461J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1461J\"></sup>They are my sons, whom God has given me here.” So he said, “Bring them to me, please, that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1461K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1461K\"></sup>I may bless them.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1462L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1462L\"></sup>the eyes of Israel were <i>so</i> dim from age <i>that</i> he could not see. Then Joseph brought them close to him, and he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1462M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1462M\"></sup>kissed them and embraced them.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Israel said to Joseph, “I never expected to see your face, and behold, God has let me see your children as well.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then Joseph took them from his knees, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1464N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1464N\"></sup>bowed with his face to the ground.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Joseph took them both, Ephraim with his right hand toward Israel’s left, and Manasseh with his left hand toward Israel’s right, and brought them close to him.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>But Israel stretched out his right hand and laid it on the head of Ephraim, who was the younger, and his left hand on Manasseh’s head, crossing his hands, although <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1466O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1466O\"></sup>Manasseh was the firstborn.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>He blessed Joseph, and said,“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1467P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1467P\"></sup>The God before whom my fathers Abraham and Isaac walked,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1467Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1467Q\"></sup>The God who has been my shepherd all my life to this day,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1468R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1468R\"></sup>The angel who has redeemed me from all evil,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1468S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1468S\"></sup>Bless the lads;And may my name live on in them,And the names of my fathers Abraham and Isaac;And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1468T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1468T\"></sup>may they grow into a multitude in the midst of the earth.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>When Joseph saw that his father <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1469U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1469U\"></sup>laid his right hand on Ephraim’s head, it displeased him; and he grasped his father’s hand to remove it from Ephraim’s head to Manasseh’s head.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Joseph said to his father, “Not so, my father, for this one is the firstborn. Place your right hand on his head.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>But his father refused and said, “I know, my son, I know; he also will become a people and he also will be great. However, his younger brother shall be greater than he, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1471V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1471V\"></sup>his descendants shall become a multitude of nations.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1472W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1472W\"></sup>He blessed them that day, saying,“By you Israel will pronounce blessing, saying,‘May God make you like Ephraim and Manasseh!’”Thus he put Ephraim before Manasseh.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then Israel said to Joseph, “Behold, I am about to die, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1473X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1473X\"></sup>God will be with you, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1473Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1473Y\"></sup>bring you back to the land of your fathers.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>I give you one portion more than your brothers, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1474Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1474Z\"></sup>which I took from the hand of the Amorite with my sword and my bow.”"
		},
		"49": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">49 </span>Then Jacob summoned his sons and said, “Assemble yourselves that I may tell you what will befall you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1475A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1475A\"></sup>in the days to come.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“Gather together and hear, O sons of Jacob;And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1476B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1476B\"></sup>listen to Israel your father.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>“Reuben, you are my firstborn;My might and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1477C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1477C\"></sup>the beginning of my strength,Preeminent in dignity and preeminent in power.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>“Uncontrolled as water, you shall not have preeminence,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1478D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1478D\"></sup>Because you went up to your father’s bed;Then you defiled <i>it</i>—he went up to my couch.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1479E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1479E\"></sup>Simeon and Levi are brothers;Their swords are implements of violence.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1480F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1480F\"></sup>Let my soul not enter into their council;Let not my glory be united with their assembly;Because in their anger they slew men,And in their self-will they lamed oxen.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>“Cursed be their anger, for it is fierce;And their wrath, for it is cruel.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1481G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1481G\"></sup>I will disperse them in Jacob,And scatter them in Israel.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>“Judah, your brothers shall praise you;Your hand shall be on the neck of your enemies;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1482H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1482H\"></sup>Your father’s sons shall bow down to you.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“Judah is a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1483I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1483I\"></sup>lion’s whelp;From the prey, my son, you have gone up.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1483J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1483J\"></sup>He couches, he lies down as a lion,And as a lion, who dares rouse him up?",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1484K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1484K\"></sup>The scepter shall not depart from Judah,Nor the ruler’s staff from between his feet,Until Shiloh comes,And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1484L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1484L\"></sup>to him <i>shall be</i> the obedience of the peoples.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1485M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1485M\"></sup>He ties <i>his</i> foal to the vine,And his donkey’s colt to the choice vine;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1485N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1485N\"></sup>He washes his garments in wine,And his robes in the blood of grapes.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>“His eyes are dull from wine,And his teeth white from milk.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1487O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1487O\"></sup>Zebulun will dwell at the seashore;And he <i>shall be</i> a haven for ships,And his flank <i>shall be</i> toward Sidon.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>“Issachar is a strong donkey,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1488P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1488P\"></sup>Lying down between the sheepfolds.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>“When he saw that a resting place was goodAnd that the land was pleasant,He bowed his shoulder to bear <i>burdens</i>,And became a slave at forced labor.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1490Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1490Q\"></sup>Dan shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1490R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1490R\"></sup>judge his people,As one of the tribes of Israel.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>“Dan shall be a serpent in the way,A horned snake in the path,That bites the horse’s heels,So that his rider falls backward.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1492S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1492S\"></sup>For Your salvation I wait, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1493T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1493T\"></sup>As for Gad, raiders shall raid him,But he will raid <i>at</i> their heels.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1494U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1494U\"></sup>As for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1494V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1494V\"></sup>Asher, his food shall be rich,And he will yield royal dainties.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1495W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1495W\"></sup>Naphtali is a doe let loose,He gives beautiful words.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1496X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1496X\"></sup>Joseph is a fruitful bough,A fruitful bough by a spring;<i>Its</i> branches run over a wall.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>“The archers bitterly attacked him,And shot <i>at him</i> and harassed him;",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>But his <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1498Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1498Y\"></sup>bow remained firm,And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1498Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1498Z\"></sup>his arms were agile,From the hands of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1498AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1498AA\"></sup>Mighty One of Jacob(From there is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1498AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1498AB\"></sup>the Shepherd, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1498AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1498AC\"></sup>the Stone of Israel),",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>From <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1499AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1499AD\"></sup>the God of your father who helps you,And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1499AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1499AE\"></sup>by the Almighty who blesses you<i>With</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1499AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1499AF\"></sup>blessings of heaven above,Blessings of the deep that lies beneath,Blessings of the breasts and of the womb.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>“The blessings of your fatherHave surpassed the blessings of my ancestorsUp to the utmost bound of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1500AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1500AG\"></sup>the everlasting hills;May they be on the head of Joseph,And on the crown of the head of the one distinguished among his brothers.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>“Benjamin is a ravenous wolf;In the morning he devours the prey,And in the evening he divides the spoil.”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>All these are the twelve tribes of Israel, and this is what their father said to them when he blessed them. He blessed them, every one with the blessing appropriate to him.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Then he charged them and said to them, “I am about to be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1503AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1503AH\"></sup>gathered to my people; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1503AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1503AI\"></sup>bury me with my fathers in the cave that is in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1503AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1503AJ\"></sup>the field of Ephron the Hittite,",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>in the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1504AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1504AK\"></sup>cave that is in the field of Machpelah, which is before Mamre, in the land of Canaan, which Abraham bought along with the field from Ephron the Hittite for a burial site.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>There they buried <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1505AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1505AL\"></sup>Abraham and his wife <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1505AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1505AM\"></sup>Sarah, there they buried <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1505AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1505AN\"></sup>Isaac and his wife Rebekah, and there I buried Leah—",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>the field and the cave that is in it, purchased from the sons of Heth.”",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>When Jacob finished charging his sons, he drew his feet into the bed and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1507AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1507AO\"></sup>breathed his last, and was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1507AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1507AP\"></sup>gathered to his people."
		},
		"50": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">50 </span>Then Joseph fell on his father’s face, and wept over him and kissed him.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Joseph commanded his servants the physicians to embalm his father. So the physicians <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1509A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1509A\"></sup>embalmed Israel.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Now forty days were required for it, for such is the period required for embalming. And the Egyptians <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1510B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1510B\"></sup>wept for him seventy days.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>When the days of mourning for him were past, Joseph spoke to the household of Pharaoh, saying, “If now I have found favor in your sight, please speak to Pharaoh, saying,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1512C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1512C\"></sup>My father made me swear, saying, “Behold, I am about to die; in my grave <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1512D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1512D\"></sup>which I dug for myself in the land of Canaan, there you shall bury me.” Now therefore, please let me go up and bury my father; then I will return.’”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Pharaoh said, “Go up and bury your father, as he made you swear.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>So Joseph went up to bury his father, and with him went up all the servants of Pharaoh, the elders of his household and all the elders of the land of Egypt,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>and all the household of Joseph and his brothers and his father’s household; they left only their little ones and their flocks and their herds in the land of Goshen.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>There also went up with him both chariots and horsemen; and it was a very great company.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>When they came to the threshing floor of Atad, which is beyond the Jordan, they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1517E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1517E\"></sup>lamented there with a very great and sorrowful lamentation; and he observed seven days mourning for his father.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Now when the inhabitants of the land, the Canaanites, saw the mourning at the threshing floor of Atad, they said, “This is a grievous mourning for the Egyptians.” Therefore it was named Abel-mizraim, which is beyond the Jordan.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Thus his sons did for him as he had charged them;",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>for his sons carried him to the land of Canaan and buried him in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1520F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1520F\"></sup>the cave of the field of Machpelah before Mamre, which Abraham had bought along with the field for a burial site from Ephron the Hittite.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>After he had buried his father, Joseph returned to Egypt, he and his brothers, and all who had gone up with him to bury his father.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>When Joseph’s brothers saw that their father was dead, they said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1522G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1522G\"></sup>What if Joseph bears a grudge against us and pays us back in full for all the wrong which we did to him!”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>So they sent <i>a message</i> to Joseph, saying, “Your father charged before he died, saying,",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>‘Thus you shall say to Joseph, “Please forgive, I beg you, the transgression of your brothers and their sin, for they did you wrong.”’ And now, please forgive the transgression of the servants of the God of your father.” And Joseph wept when they spoke to him.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then his brothers also came and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1525H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1525H\"></sup>fell down before him and said, “Behold, we are your servants.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>But Joseph said to them, “Do not be afraid, for am I in God’s place?",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>As for you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1527I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1527I\"></sup>you meant evil against me, <i>but</i> God meant it for good in order to bring about this present result, to preserve many people alive.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>So therefore, do not be afraid; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1528J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1528J\"></sup>I will provide for you and your little ones.” So he comforted them and spoke kindly to them.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Now Joseph stayed in Egypt, he and his father’s household, and Joseph lived one hundred and ten years.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Joseph saw the third generation of Ephraim’s sons; also the sons of Machir, the son of Manasseh, were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1530K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1530K\"></sup>born on Joseph’s knees.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Joseph said to his brothers, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1531L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1531L\"></sup>I am about to die, but God will surely take care of you and bring you up from this land to the land which He promised on oath to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1531M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1531M\"></sup>Abraham, to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1531N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1531N\"></sup>Isaac and to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1531O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1531O\"></sup>Jacob.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Then Joseph made the sons of Israel swear, saying, “God will surely take care of you, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1532P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1532P\"></sup>you shall carry my bones up from here.”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>So Joseph died at the age of one hundred and ten years; and he was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1533Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1533Q\"></sup>embalmed and placed in a coffin in Egypt."
		}
	}
};
module.exports = book;